title: oreo cookie delight
directions: Mix butter and cookies together and press into bottom of a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Mix Cool Whip and cream cheese together well and pour evenly over cookie crumb mixture.
Refrigerate 10 to 15 minutes.

title: chewy peanut butter bars
directions: Melt margarine and peanut butter.
Mix in other ingredients. Bake in 9 x 13-inch pan for 20 to 30 minutes at 350°.
May be iced with your favorite chocolate frosting.

title: sausage rounds
directions: Brown and drain the meat.
Add cut up cheese.
Spread over edge of party rye bread.
Put under broiler until brown.
These can be frozen and when ready to use put on cookie sheet and bake at 200° for 10 minutes, then broil until brown.

title: delicious no-sugar apple pie
directions: Place apple juice concentrate in a saucepan.
Bring to a boil. Combine margarine, cornstarch and spices in a small bowl. Add a small amount of apple juice.
Stir until well blended. Stir cornstarch mixture into apple juice.
Pour over apples. Stir carefully to coat all slices.
Pour into unbaked pie crust.
Place top crust over apples. Bake at 425° for about 30 minutes. Reduce temperature to 375° and bake for 30 minutes longer.
(Suitable for freezing.) Makes 6 servings.

title: kabobs
directions: Soak round toothpicks in water for 10 minutes.
Thread toothpicks with chicken, bacon, water chestnut and fruit.
Combine ketchup, honey and mustard.
Brush each Kabob with ketchup mixture.
Place on lightly oiled broiler pan.
Broil, 3 to 4 inches from heat source, for 3 to 4 minutes.
Turn and brush with sauce.
Broil an additional 3 to 4 minutes or until chicken is cooked.

title: guacamole
directions: Blend all ingredients with a hand mixer. Serve with chips.

title: hot dip
directions: Layer ingredients in order given into a 9 x 11-inch dish. Bake at 350° for 1/2 hour. Serve with tortilla chips or crackers.

title: ding dong cake
directions: Prepare German chocolate cake mix as directed on box. Bake in 2 layers and when cool, split each layer to make 4 thin layers. Mix cream cheese, Cool Whip and sugar until well blended. Place mixture between layers. Top cake with Betty Crocker sour cream chocolate frosting.

title: pineapple scallop kabobs
directions: Combine Pineapple Juice, Soy Sauce, Lemon Juice in a large mixing bowl.
Add Scallops and Pineapple Rings; toss to coat. Marinate, covered, in a refrigerator for 1 hour, stirring occasionally.
Preheat broiler.
Remove Scallops and Pineapple Rings from the marinade, discard the marinade.

title: poppy seed cake
directions: Beat together oil, eggs and vanilla. Add flour, baking soda, milk and poppy seeds. Mix well. Pour into a greased and floured Bundt pan or Tube pan. Bake at 350° for 50-60 min. Cool 10 min. and remove from pan.

title: million dollar pie
directions: Mix milk and lemon juice together and then add other ingredients.
Put in two baked pie shells and refrigerate.

title: cheese ball
directions: Mix all together and form into a ball.
Serve with crackers.

title: gooey butter cake
directions: Bring cream cheese to room temperature.
Mix first 3 ingredients and line 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan with mixture.
Mix last 4 ingredients and pour on top of first mixture.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.
Sprinkle additional powdered sugar on top when cool, if desired.

title: no bake cookies
directions: Combine all ingredients in a saucepan; bring to a good boil and let set a few minutes.
Add peanut butter and oatmeal; mix well.
Drop on wax paper.
Refrigerate.

title: homemade potato skins
directions: Quantities of ingredients all depend on how many skins you want to make and how much cheese you like.

title: peanut butter fudge
directions: Put sugar and milk together and stirring constantly bring to rolling boil for 5 minutes.
Remove from heat and add Marshmallow Fluff, peanut butter and vanilla.
Beat for awhile, then pour into a buttered pan and let cool before cutting.

title: cheese fondue
directions: Dice cheese in 1/2-inch cubes; sprinkle with flour.
In a fondue pot or saucepan, heat 1 cup of milk until simmering, but not boiling.
Add cheese by the handfuls, stirring until cheese melts.
Add milk to thin to desired consistency.
Serve with bread cut or torn into chunks.

title: stir-fry (without spices)
directions: Brown meat and onions in cooking oil in large skillet.
Add chopped vegetables, salt and pepper and simmer until vegetables reach desired tenderness, adding water as needed to keep mixture from becoming too dry.
Serve over rice.
Sprinkle with soy sauce if desired.
Serves at least 2.

title: corn casserole
directions: If fresh corn is available, slit center of kernels with sharp knife.
Scrape
into
bowl.
Measure
cups.
If using canned corn pour off excess water from kernel corn.
Beat eggs until thick.
Add
corn.	Combine flour, salt, sugar and Texas Pete in mixing
bowl.
Stir milk into dry ingredients.
Blend in butter. Combine
with corn mixture.
Beat well, adding the browned sausage.
Pour
into
greased
1/2-quart casserole. Bake 1 hour and 20 minutes at 350°.

title: chicken salad
directions: Boil chicken breasts until done; salt and pepper to taste. Chop or tear into small pieces.
Add vegetables and stir in dressing.
If you are industrious, you may make your own Ranch dressing or, if you prefer, you may use mayonnaise.
The really nice part of this is that if you use the low-fat or fat-free dressing, there is almost no fat in this recipe.
It can be served with crackers, small pieces of trimmed bread or larger pieces of raw vegetables.

title: burgundy meat loaf in sourdough
directions: Cut a thin slice from the top of the loaf.
Scoop out most of the bread.
Tear to make 1 1/2 cups soft crumbs (top slice and remaining bread can be used as bread crumbs for other recipes). Brown onion and mushrooms in 1 1/2 tablespoons of the butter. Beat egg with catsup.
Mix in bread crumbs, 1/2 cup of the cheese, wine or broth and seasonings.
Lightly mix in ground beef and onion mixture.

title: cream cheese frosting
directions: Combine cream cheese, butter and vanilla.
Beat at low speed until light.
Gradually add sugar until fluffy.
If necessary, add milk to make spreading consistency.
Frosts one 8 or 9-inch square cake.

title: sweet potato casserole
directions: Mix all
well (can use electric mixer).
Pour in oblong baking dish.

title: cheese, broccoli and rice casserole
directions: Cook rice.
Saute chopped onion and celery in margarine.
In separate bowl, combine cream of mushroom soup, cream of chicken soup and Cheez Whiz.
Add cooked rice and sauteed onion and celery; stir well.
Pour mixture into buttered Corning Ware dish. Bake at 350° for approximately 30 minutes or until bubbly.

title: marinade for meat
directions: Combine all ingredients in pan.
Add meat; allow to stand 2 hours (better if left overnight).
Grill over hot coals.

title: ghivetch(mixed veggie dish)
directions: Put all vegetables in a 13 x 9-inch dish.
Heat last 7 ingredients to boiling point and pour over vegetables.
Cover with heavy foil and bake at 350° for 1/2 hour.

title: gingered pumpkin soup
directions: Combine chicken broth, pumpkin (puree), milk, sugar, ginger and cayenne pepper.
Simmer 5 minutes.
Serve with toasted croutons.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: grilled summer vegetables
directions: Cook potatoes in boiling water to cover 5 minutes or just until tender; drain.
Arrange equal amounts of potato, zucchini, squash, yellow peppers and onion on 4 squares of aluminum foil.
Sprinkle with equal amounts of basil and pepper.
Fold foil over vegetables, sealing securely.
Grill over medium coals 15 minutes, turning once.
Serves 4.

title: chocolate orange passion cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease 3 (8-inch) or 2 (9-inch) round pans or a 13 x 9-inch pan.
Line bottom of pans with waxed paper cut to fit pan.
Grease the paper and flour the pans.
Combine dry ingredients in large mixing bowl on low speed for several minutes to blend thoroughly.
Add oil, milk, eggs, vanilla and orange peel.
Beat for 2 minutes at medium speed, scraping sides of bowl as needed.
Add enough boiling water to orange juice to make 1 cup total.
Stir water and juice into batter until blended.
Batter will be thin.
Pour batter evenly into prepared pans.
Bake for 30 to 35 minutes, or until toothpick inserted near center comes out clean.
Cool on wire rack 5 minutes before removing from pans. Finish cooling on wire rack.
Frost with Creamy Chocolate Orange Frosting; garnish with mandarin orange slices dipped in melted chocolate.

title: fresh blueberry pie
directions: Preheat oven to 425°.
Roll out half the pastry and fit into a pie plate.
Combine sugar, flour and cinnamon.
Arrange berries in the pie shell; cover with sugar mixture and sprinkle with lemon juice.
Dot with butter.
Roll out remaining dough, cutting into strips.
Fit dough over berries in a lattice shape.
Flute.
Bake 35 to 45 minutes.

title: salmon puffs
directions: Pour the juice from the salmon into a glass and set it aside. Add egg and flour to the salmon.
Mix all with a fork.
Do not add salt!
Take 1/4 cup of the salmon juice and add baking powder.
Mix with a fork until it foams up.
Mix and stir into the salmon; fry in deep fryer a small amount at a time.
Cook within 15 minutes after mixing.

title: cheese pie
directions: Make Jell-O ahead of time; chill slightly.
Mix crumbs and butter.
Press into 13 x 9-inch pan.
Whip together cream cheese, cream, sugar and vanilla.
Pour into crust; chill.
Place banana slices on top.
Pour Jell-O over top; chill thoroughly.

title: mama's fried apple pie
directions: Peel and slice apples.
Cook until tender.
Add sugar and spices.
Roll out biscuits into a thin circle.
Fill with 2 teaspoons apple mixture.
Fold into half moons and seal edges together with a fork.
Fry in shortening.

title: green bean casserole
directions: Mix green beans, soup (which has been diluted with the milk) and 1/2 of the French fried onions.
Put in greased baking pan. Bake 15 to 20 minutes at 350°, then put remaining French fried onions on top and bake 5 minutes more.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Steam broccoli.
Put in casserole dish with water chestnuts (drained).
Mix soup and mayo.
Cover broccoli.
Top with cheese and maybe paprika.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes, uncovered.

title: coq au vin
directions: Combine all ingredients and bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes. Good made ahead and refrigerated.

title: meat loaf
directions: Mix all ingredients together except salsa, using salt, pepper and garlic powder to taste. Then add 1/3 bottle salsa, mixing well. Place in microwave oven-safe container with lid. Add remaining salsa over top. Cover. Cook until done.

title: mixed vegetable salad
directions: Cook mixed vegetables on the stove or in the microwave until crisp-tender.
Drain; place in large bowl.
Add kidney beans, celery, onion and green pepper.
In a saucepan over medium heat bring sugar, vinegar and cornstarch to a boil stirring constantly, until thickened.
Cool slightly.
Pour over vegetables and toss. Makes 8 servings.

title: christmas brunch jam
directions: Combine
all
ingredients
in a saucepan.
Cook, uncovered, over medium low heat, stirring frequently until mixture registers 221° on a candy thermometer.
This will take about 1 1/2
hours. Spoon cranberry mixture into hot sterilized jars, leaving 1/4-inch
head
space.
Cover
at
once
with
lids. Process
in boiling water bath for 15 minutes.	Yield:	5 half pints.

title: lemon jello cake
directions: Dissolve Jell-O in hot water.
Mix cake mix and oil; add eggs and seasoning.
Pour gelatin in while hot.
Grease and flour cake mold.
Bake in tube pan in 340° oven, about 1 hour.
Empty out immediately.

title: aunt gertie's coca-cola cake
directions: Combine flour and sugar in mixing bowl.
Heat butter, cocoa and Coca-Cola to boiling point and pour over flour mixture; mix well.
Add buttermilk or sour milk, beaten eggs, soda, vanilla and marshmallows.
Bake in greased and floured 9 x 13-inch pan for 30 to 35 minutes at 350°.
Ice while cake is hot.

title: jo's baked eggs
directions: Melt margarine and pour into a 13 x 9-inch Pyrex baking dish. Spread shredded Cheddar cheese on margarine.
Beat eggs with half and half; pour over cheese.
Bake at 325° for 45 to 50 minutes, or until set.

title: 2 chocolate meringue pies
directions: Mix cocoa, salt, sugar and flour.
Pour milk into 2-quart saucepan.
Beat in egg yolks.
Do not turn heat on until eggs and milk are well mixed. Add dry ingredients and cook over medium heat, stirring continually until thickened.
Scrape bottom and sides of pan to prevent scorching.

title: easy chicken cacciatore
directions: Brown chicken in oil 10 minutes, turning occasionally; drain. Add tomatoes, tomato paste, mushrooms, zucchini and basil.
Salt and pepper to taste, if desired.
Cover and simmer 25 minutes. Serve over pasta.
Garnish with parsley, if desired.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: veggie salad
directions: Mix all together and let stand for a few hours.
It will keep for several days.

title: dump cake
directions: In 9 x 13-inch baking dish, mix together pineapple and cherry pie filling; do not drain.
Sprinkle dry cake mix evenly over the fruit mixture.
Drizzle melted butter over the cake mix.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until golden brown.
Serve warm with Cool Whip, nuts and coconut.

title: chocolate eclair cake
directions: Grease bottom of a 13 x 9-inch pan.
In large bowl, beat the 3 cups of milk and 2 packages of instant vanilla pudding on medium until it thickens.
Blend in vanilla and Cool Whip.

title: easy refrigerator pickles
directions: Alternate layers of cucumbers and onions in a large glass bowl.
In a medium saucepan, combine sugar, vinegar, salt, mustard seed, celery seed and turmeric.
Bring to a boil, stirring, until sugar is dissolved.
Pour vinegar mixture over cucumber mixture and cool slightly.
Cover tightly and refrigerate for at least 24 hours before serving.
Store for up to one month in refrigerator.

title: chocolate raspberry torte
directions: Prepare the cake according to package directions, using three greased and floured 9-inch round cake pans. Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes or until a toothpick inserted near the center comes out clean. Cool for 10 minutes. Remove from pans to wire racks to cool completely.

title: spinach dip
directions: Mix together all of the ingredients.
Serve with chips or raw vegetables.

title: caramelita bars
directions: Mix first 6 ingredients until crumbly.
Press 2/3 of this into 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake 8 minutes or so or until light golden brown.
Spread Eagle Brand on top and chocolate chips if you wish. Put remaining crumbs on top.
Bake 12 to 15 minutes at 350° or until done.

title: potato salad
directions: Peel
potatoes	and dice.
Boil until done, but not too soft. Allow to cool, then add all other ingredients.

title: potato pudding
directions: Beat eggs; add milk, butter and nutmeg.
Grate raw potatoes; combine with other ingredients.
Place in casserole dish.
Bake at 400° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: easy fruit punch
directions: Mix pineapple juice and Big K punch in punch bowl.
Add scoops of pineapple sherbet and stir until frothy.
Delicious and so easy!

title: almond roca
directions: In medium size pot, melt butter.
Add sugar and syrup and cook to hard crack stage on candy thermometer, stirring constantly. Remove from heat and stir in 1 cup of nuts.
Spread in ungreased 9 x 13-inch pan to cool.
Melt chocolate in double boiler.
Remove candy from pan and place on waxed paper.
Pour chocolate over candy and top with remaining nuts.
Cool and then break into very small pieces.

title: crazy cake
directions: Add flour, sugar, cocoa and baking soda in bowl.
Mix with spoon. Take spoon and make 3 holes in mixture. Add vanilla to one, vinegar to another and Wesson oil to the last.
Mix lightly. Add 2 cups water and beat 3 minutes.
Very moist cake. Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: atlanta upside-down cake
directions: Combine the 1/4 cup of light spread and brown sugar, mixing until well blended.
Spread onto bottom of an 8-inch square pan. Arrange peaches on brown sugar mixture.
Sprinkle with pecans.

title: asparagus casserole
directions: Melt butter in small skillet.
Stir in flour; when well blended,
stir
in 2 tablespoons asparagus liquid
to
make
a paste.
Stir in cream; cook and stir
constantly until mixture thickens.	Add salt and pepper.
Stir
in	paprika,
shredded cheese
and
mushrooms;
continue
stirring
until	cheese	is melted.
Line bottom of 2-quart casserole dish
with
half	of the asparagus.	Cover with half of the sauce,
then
the other half of	the
asparagus	and the rest of
the
sauce.
Spread cracker crumbs over casserole.
Bake at 350° about 15 minutes, until top bubbles.

title: green bean casserole
directions: Drain green beans.
Grate cheese.
Mix first 4 ingredients together with small amount of French fried onions.
Bake at 350° for 5 minutes.
Cover the top of casserole with French fried onions and bake an additional 5 minutes.

title: seven layer bars
directions: Melt oleo.
Mix with graham crackers.
Pat mixture evenly into bottom of an ungreased 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking pan.
Layer in order chocolate pieces, marshmallows, peanut butter chips and walnuts. Pour sweetened condensed milk evenly over all.
Bake in 350° oven for 30 minutes.
Cool.
Cut into bars.
Makes 36.

title: apple pound cake
directions: Mix sugar, oil and eggs well.
Sift flour, soda, salt and cinnamon together; add to sugar mixture.
Add remaining ingredients and mix well.
Bake 1 hour and 20 minutes at 350°.

title: pistachio cake
directions: Combine cake mix, pudding, oil, milk and water.
Add eggs one at a time.
Mix well.
Pour into Bundt pan.
Bake at 350° for 50 minutes.

title: nany's sticky chicken
directions: Preheat oven to 425°.
In cast-iron Dutch oven, heat oil and sprinkle sugar in bottom.
As sugar begins to darken (caramelizing), place in several pieces of chicken, skin side down. Brown and turn chicken.
Remove chicken; sprinkle in more sugar and brown the next pieces.

title: bob's chili
directions: Brown onions and ground beef in skillet.
Add contents of chili seasoning mix, tomatoes, hot sauce, chili powder and minced garlic in blender.
Blend until tomatoes are broken up completely. Combine contents of blender to skillet.
Add beer.
Add beans. Simmer 30 minutes.

title: creamed spinach with crunchy topping
directions: Cook spinach according to directions on package.
Drain thoroughly.
Return to hot pan and blend in cream cheese and 1/2 the margarine.
Season with salt, pepper and lemon rind.
Turn into buttered casserole.
Cover.
Refrigerate until ready to bake.
May be prepared in the morning of the day to be served.
About 45 minutes before baking, remove from refrigerator.
Spread bread dressing over top and drizzle with remaining 2 tablespoons melted margarine.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.
Serves 9.

title: homemade vegetable soup
directions: Put all ingredients into a large pot.
Bring to a boil rapidly for about 10 minutes.
Reduce heat to a slow boil.
Cover and cook for at least 2 hours or until all vegetables are tender.
Remove bay leaves before storing.
Average portion: 2 cups soup.

title: pecan brittle
directions: In saucepan, heat sugar, corn syrup, salt and water.
Bring to boil.
Add nuts.
Cook until it reaches 300°.
Remove from heat.
Add butter and baking soda.
Pour at once onto lightly greased cookie sheet.
With two forks, spread mixture.
Let cool, then break into pieces.
Store in airtight container.

title: glazed chicken and grapes
directions: Wash and pat dry chicken.
Spray coat a saute pan.
Heat pan over medium heat.
Add chicken.
Cook 8 to 10 minutes or until no longer pink, turning once.
Transfer chicken to serving plates. Cover to keep warm.

title: railroad pickles
directions: Cover cucumbers with salt and cracked ice and let set for 3 hours.
Drain well.

title: good punch
directions: Blend together and chill.

title: baked ritz chicken
directions: Melt margarine in long casserole dish.
Crush crackers.
Salt and pepper chicken pieces.
Roll each piece of chicken in margarine, then in cracker crumbs and place in casserole dish. Bake for 30 minutes at 400°, then turn chicken over and continue baking for 30 minutes more.

title: updated chili
directions: Saute ground meat, add seasoning kit, tomato paste or tomato sauce, water then precooked pinto beans.
Simmer on heat or high in crock-pot 20 to 30 minutes.
Serve.

title: pieroghi lasagna
directions: Cook noodles.
Place first layer of noodles in a buttered 9 x 13 glass baking casserole.
Spread potatoes.
Top with shredded cheese.
Repeat layers until all ingredients are used.
Cook onion in melted margarine to tenderize.
Pour onion-margarine mixture over lasagna layers.
Bake at 300° for 30 minutes.
Let cool 10 minutes.
Before serving, spoon the onion-butter sauce from bottom of pan onto top layers.

title: fudge
directions: In a 4 quart saucepan, combine first 4 ingredients and mix well.
Bring to a slow rolling boil for 30-40 minutes (soft ball stage).

title: busy day casserole
directions: Brown and drain beef.
Blend in onion soup mix and soy sauce, lemon juice, ginger, pepper and salt.
Layer meat mixture with sliced potatoes in greased baking dish or casserole.
Top with mushroom soup and shredded cheese.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes.

title: pheasant deluxe
directions: Simmer pheasant in salt water until done.
Remove from bones. Cut in pieces.
Mix with other ingredients.
Place in 9 x 12-inch baking dish, topping casserole with grated cheese.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.
Chicken or turkey may be used instead of pheasant.

title: pasta crab salad
directions: Combine all ingredients and serve with your favorite cracker on a leaf of lettuce.
This is also good with a can of small drained shrimp added.

title: salted pecans
directions: Heat nuts in 250° oven until hot.
In large bowl, drizzle butter over nuts.
Salt to taste.
Bake in oven for 1 hour at 250°; turn frequently.

title: frankfurters and potatoes
directions: Slit franks lengthwise;
spread open.
Heap potatoes on center of
franks,
using
cup per frank.
Sprinkle with cheese and paprika.
Place in oven for about 15 minutes.

title: marinated green bean salad
directions: Mix green beans, peas, onions, green pepper, pimento and celery in a bowl. Set aside.

title: taco pizza
directions: On a
pizza
pan
or
cookie sheet, place Boboli bread. Spread a
layer
of refried beans.
Then add the hamburger and cover with layer
of
cheese.
Place
in an oven or Dutch oven and bake
at 325° until cheese is melted, but don't overcook. Remove from
oven and
cover
with lettuce, tomato and salsa. Serve at once.

title: honey cake
directions: Cream shortening with the honey; add eggs, sour milk and flour which has been sifted with baking soda, ginger, cinnamon and salt. Sprinkle nuts on top and between layers as desired.

title: pecan pie
directions: Mix everything, but nuts together.
After mixing, add pecans. Pour into pie shells.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Makes 2 pies.

title: very easy beef stew
directions: Arrange and layer vegetables and stew meat.
Top with 2 cans soup.
Bake at 250° for 5 hours.
Great way to warm your kitchen on a cold day.

title: best canadian butter tarts
directions: Cream egg, brown sugar and butter.
Add vanilla and raisins.

title: mayonnaise cake
directions: Mix ingredients.
Bake at 325° in a greased and floured 9 x 13-inch pan for approximately 35 minutes.
Use toothpick to test for doneness.

title: barbecue ribs
directions: Season ribs with salt and pepper to suit your taste.
Layer ribs in pan.
Pour sauce over ribs.
Bake slowly at 300°.

title: shrimp dip
directions: Allow cream cheese to soften. Mix all ingredients except shrimp until smooth. Add shrimp last. Refrigerate. Allow to soften before serving.
(Serves 50.)

title: hawaiian sweet potatoes
directions: Line a shallow baking dish with sweet potatoes.
Drain juice from pineapple; heat juice and butter in broiler.
When good and hot, stir in cornstarch, slowly, until juice is thickened.
Stir in pineapple and coconut.
Pour over sweet potatoes.
Sprinkle with marshmallows and bake in oven until marshmallows are melted.

title: fruit salad
directions: Combine first four ingredients in medium saucepan. Beat with wire whisk and bring to a boil to thicken.
Stir constantly. Remove and chill.
Drain juice from oranges and pineapple. Combine all fruit and nuts.
Stir in cooled mixture.

title: best ever meat loaf
directions: Lightly mix ground beef, bread crumbs, chopped onion, egg, salt and pepper with 1/2 cup Manwich sauce.
Shape into loaf in baking pan.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Drain fat; spread mustard over.
Pour on rest of Manwich sauce.
Bake at 350° for 35 more minutes.
Baste with sauce several times.
Makes 6 servings.
(Can be microwaved for 9 minutes and 1 more minute with sauce.)

title: toasted pumpkin seeds
directions: Wash seeds in colander.
Spread them out on paper towels to dry for 2 days.
Place seeds in a bowl.
Add margarine and seasonings.
Mix well.
Bake on a cookie sheet in a 300° oven for 20 to 30 minutes.
Shake them occasionally while cooking.

title: apple crisp
directions: Prepare apples in baking pan.
Sprinkle cinnamon over apples; add water over the apples, covering them.
In mixing bowl, add salt, sugar, flour and butter.
Mix until mixture is fine and crumbly.
Sprinkle over apples.
Bake at 350° until golden brown.

title: tuna-cheese burgers
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Mix first 5 ingredients together. Spread hamburger halves with mustard.
Divide tuna mixture on 4 bun halves.
Top with other halves.
Wrap in foil and bake in 350° oven for 20 minutes.
Serves 4.
Also delicious when served cold.

title: baked salmon salad
directions: Drain salmon. Break into large pieces. Combine all ingredients except potato chips and paprika. Place in casserole dish. Top with potato chips; sprinkle with paprika. Bake at 400° for 10 to 15 minutes.

title: cream cheese brownies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Beat first 4 ingredients.
Slice 1 cookie roll in 1/2-inch slices and place on greased and floured 13 x 9-inch pan.
Pour mixture over cookies.
Slice remaining cookie roll and place on top.
Any extra cookies, fill in spaces.
Bake for 45 minutes.

title: jam cake
directions: Mix in order given.

title: grilled seafood salad
directions: Combine teriyaki sauce with 2 tablespoons oil and brush fillets with mixture.
Let stand 15 minutes.
Heat remaining oil until very hot in skillet or griddle.
Saute fish 2 to 3 minutes per side.
Remove from skillet, cool and flake.
In large mixing bowl combine vegetables and half the dressing.
Divide greens among four salad plates.
Top with vegetable mixture and flaked fish.
Drizzle remaining dressing over top of serve separately.

title: rainy day special
directions: Mix all ingredients in a skillet and let simmer for about 45 minutes, stirring often to keep from sticking.
Cook and hope it doesn't rain.

title: taco soup
directions: Brown ground beef and drain.
Pour into taco mix (follow package directions).
Saute onion and celery in same frypan.
In large saucepan, pour in all remaining ingredients except cheese, sour cream and chips.
Simmer 30 minutes.
Serve hot with shredded cheese and sour cream on top of soup.
Scoop with chips.

title: chicken spaghetti
directions: Boil chicken until done.
Set aside to cool.
Boil spaghetti in chicken broth.
Saute celery, onion and pepper in butter until tender.
Mix cream of mushroom soup, tomatoes, cheese and spaghetti.
Add chicken.
Pour into baking dish.
Sprinkle with cheese and bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: sonny's fruitcake
directions: Butter a 9-inch tube pan.
Line with waxed paper; butter again.
Sift flour and baking soda.
Combine eggs, mincemeat, milk, fruit and nuts.
Fold in dry ingredients.
Pour in pan. Bake at 300° for 2 hours until center springs back and top is golden.
Cool.
Turn out and remove paper.

title: fettucine
directions: Cook noodles according to directions on package.
Mix together sour cream, eggs, cheese and cream.
Then toss with noodles.
Pour melted butter over all and toss again.
Serve immediately.

title: parmesan chicken
directions: Combine egg and milk in bowl. Combine Parmesan cheese and bread crumbs in Ziploc bag. Dip chicken in egg mixture, then shake in crumb mixture. Pour 1/3 can tomato sauce in bottom of baking dish. Melt butter and olive oil in skillet. Brown chicken in skillet 2 to 3 minutes each side. Put in baking dish with sauce. Pour remaining sauce over chicken. Bake at 425° for 20 to 30 minutes. Sprinkle Mozzarella cheese over chicken during the last 10 minutes of baking.

title: hershey bar icebox pie
directions: In a double boiler or on very low heat, melt chocolate bars and marshmallows in milk.
Allow to cool thoroughly.
Add half of whipped cream.
Add nuts.
Pour into crust and top with remaining whipped cream.
Refrigerate.

title: turtle sauce piquant
directions: Brown turtle meat in hot oil.
Discard excess oil.
In same pot, saute chopped vegetables.
Add rest of ingredients.
Bring to boil.
Turn down heat to simmer.
Cook for 1 1/2 to 2 hours or until meat is tender.
Serve with hot, cooked rice.

title: grandma brady's chicken
directions: Boil all ingredients for 1 hour.
Take chicken out of broth. Debone chicken. Put back in broth.
Thicken slightly.
Serve over mashed potatoes.

title: dream pie
directions: Prepare whipped topping mix with 1 cup of the milk and the vanilla as directed on pkg. using large mixer bowl. Add remaining 1 3/4 cups milk and the pie filling mix. Blend on high speed for 2 minutes. Chill 4 hours.

title: peasant salad
directions: In a large bowl, mix together lettuce and celery.
Layer all remaining ingredients over lettuce and celery in the order listed. Cover and refrigerate for 8 hours.
Toss together just before serving.
Yield: 8 servings.

title: joann's tuna casserole
directions: Put soup in casserole with milk.
Mix. Add tuna, drained.
Mix. Layer peas, corn and chips, crumbled.
Repeat.
Bake for 25 minutes at 350°.

title: the best chicken fried steak in texas
directions: Cut meat into serving size pieces.
If using top sirloin or round steak, pound well with meat mallet.
Sprinkle meat with unseasoned meat tenderizer.
Mix a batch of flour, salt and pepper in a square pan.
Mix eggs and 2 to 3 cups milk in a bowl.
Heat oil, about 1-inch, in a heavy skillet until very hot.
Dip steak in flour, coating both sides, then in beaten egg/milk and again in flour mixture.
Place pieces in hot oil, adding only enough meat (about 3 pieces) to allow easy turning.
Brown meat on each side adjusting heat so as not to burn, turning often.
Drain on paper towels.
Serve with Country Style Gravy.
Serves 4 to 6 depending on appetites.

title: pasta mexicana
directions: Place onions and chilies into heavy skillet.
Cover and cook over high heat until onions are browned and chilies' skins are charred on all sides (8 to 10 minutes).
Remove chilies; peel, discard skins and seeds.
Chop and return to pan.
Stir in tomatoes and chili.
Cook over medium heat, stirring occasionally, 15 to 20 minutes.

title: bean casserole
directions: Place first five ingredients in casserole.
Add salt if desired.
Cover with tater tots.
Bake 25 minutes at 350°.
Serves 6.

title: sugar-free ginger spice cookies
directions: Beat together oil and margarine.
Add milk, eggs and vanilla. Beat well.
Combine all dry ingredients and blend into liquids. Roll out to 1/8-inch thickness and cut into 2-inch rounds.
Place on baking sheet sprayed with Pam.
Bake at 375° for 7 minutes. Makes 3 dozen.

title: new orleans muffaletta sandwich
directions: Be careful in your selection; do not choose one too young, and take only such varieties as have been raised in a good and moral atmosphere.
When once decided upon and is selected, let that question remain forever settled, and give your time and thought to domestic use.
Some insist on keeping them in hot water.
But even poor varieties may be made sweet and tender and good by garnishing with patience well sweetened with smiles; then wrap them in the mantle of charity.
Keep warm with a steady fire of domestic devotion and serve with peaches and cream.
When thus prepared they will keep for years.

title: sawdust salad
directions: 1st Layer:
Dissolve jello in hot water; add cold water.
Stir in drained pineapple.
Slice bananas and place in layer on top of jello mixture.
Place marshmallows on top of bananas.
Let jell.

title: cool whip pie
directions: Mix pineapple, milk, juice and nuts.
Fold in whipped cream. Pour into graham cracker crust.

title: monster chili
directions: Cook mostaccioli according to package directions.
Cook beef, onion and garlic, drain.
Add tomatoes, tomato sauce, tomato paste, drained mushrooms, salt, sugar, basil, pepper, bay leaf and water. Cover and simmer 30 minutes.
Remove bay leaf, stir in mostaccioli. Turn into 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking pan.
Sprinkle Parmesan over top. Cover with foil, bake at 350° for 35 minutes.
Put thinly sliced or grated Mozzarella on top; bake, uncovered, 5 minutes or until cheese melts.

title: cole slaw
directions: Mix all ingredients together. Cover tightly and put in refrigerator.
It tastes better if made ahead of time.
It will keep several days.

title: caramel brownies
directions: Melt over medium heat caramels and set aside.
Mix together cake mix, butter, milk and nuts and pat 1/2 of mixture into 10 x 13-inch pan.
Pat out, bake for 6 minutes at 350°.
Take out of oven and sprinkle chocolate chips over the top, then pour melted caramels over that.
Crumble the rest of the cake mixture over the caramel, then bake another 15 to 20 minutes.

title: cabbage and kielbasa
directions: In pot, put cabbage, onion, bay leaves, catsup and kielbasa. Fill with water about 1-inch over ingredients.
Cook until cabbage is done (not soft).
Serve as is or over boiled cut up potatoes.

title: apple crisp
directions: Butter a casserole dish and put in apples.
Mix water and cinnamon and pour over apples.
Mix sugar, flour and butter until crumbly.
Sprinkle on top and bake at 400° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: spaghetti-pizza casserole
directions: Mix Parmesan cheese, margarine and pasta together and place in bottom of 13 x 9-inch glass dish.
Pour 1/2 jar spaghetti sauce over pasta.
Layer pepperoni and mushrooms over sauce.
Cover with remaining sauce.
Top with Mozzarella cheese.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: chunky chowder
directions: Cook potatoes, carrots, celery and onion in boiling water for 10 minutes.
While vegetables are cooking, melt butter, stir in flour and cook for 1 minute.
Gradually stir in milk, stirring constantly, until thickened.
Add cheese, stirring until melted. Stir in corn, heat thoroughly, but do not boil.
Add cooked vegetables with liquid; stir and serve.

title: old style butter pound cake
directions: Preheat oven
to
Grease
and flour a 9 x 5-inch loaf pan.
With	mixer
on low speed, cream butter until soft. Slowly add
the
sugar while mixer is running.
Once all sugar has been added, beat until mixture is fluffy.
Slowly add eggs (one at
a time),
mixing
each
well	into
the butter-sugar mixture.
Add flour
and	salt,
mixing
until
smooth.
Add vanilla and milk, mixing until smooth.
Pour into the loaf pan and bake 75 to 90 minutes at 325° or until done.

title: southern cheese souffle
directions: Cook the grits in the water until done.
Add the milk, butter and cheese.
Mix well until all of the cheese is melted.
Fold in well beaten eggs.
Put a layer of sausage in a lightly greased casserole.
Fold remaining sausage into mixture.
Pour in casserole.
Bake at 375° for 45 minutes.

title: good oven chicken
directions: Combine all dry ingredients.
Dip chicken pieces in milk. Coat with meal mixture.
Place chicken, skin side up, in large baking dish.
Drizzle butter over chicken.
Bake in 375° oven 50 to 55 minutes or until done.
Serves 4.

title: diet cake(for people who can't have regular sugar)
directions: Cook raisins in water until soft and then drain. Blend all ingredients together and bake at 350 degrees for 45 minutes in a 9 x 13 inch pan.

title: mexican chicken casserole
directions: Pan-fry chicken and onion.
Combine soup, broth and salsa to make sauce.

In a 9 x 13-inch pan, layer half of Doritos in bottom of pan. Layer chicken on top of Doritos, then top with sauce. Mix cheese and other 1/2 of Doritos and put on top of other layers. Bake at 375° for 30 minutes.

title: peda bread(serves 8)
directions: In large bowl of electric mixer, combine yeast and warm water, stirring to blend; let soften about 5 minutes, then stir in milk, sugar, salt and olive oil.
Add 3 cups of the flour and beat at medium speed for 5 minutes.
Remove beaters and with a heavy spoon, work in 2 1/2 cups more flour.
Spread the remaining 1/2 cup flour on a board; turn dough onto it.
Knead for about 5 minutes or until smooth and elastic feeling.
(If you want to make the dough by hand, stir in 5 1/2 cups flour; knead dough into remaining 1/2 cup flour for about 10 minutes or until smooth.)

title: italian love cake
directions: Prepare cake mix according to directions.
Pour into a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Beat the following until smooth:
Ricotta cheese, eggs, sugar and vanilla.
Pour these ingredients over the cake mix very slowly, making sure it is evenly covered.
Bake as directed. Remove from oven and cool.
Then refrigerate overnight.

title: chicken spaghetti casserole
directions: Break spaghetti
into pieces.
Mix together all ingredients and bake for 1 hour at 350°, covered.
Reserve some cheese and put on top last 10 minutes.
Can use four large or 5 small chicken breasts, cooked in water with 2 chicken bouillon cubes, added for seasoning.

title: pecan delight
directions: Sift sugar, flour and salt. Work in butter and vanilla.
Add nuts and water. Shape into balls (1 teaspoon). Grease cookie sheet. Bake at 350° for 5 to 7 minutes. Roll in powdered sugar when you take them out of the oven.

title: black sapote bread
directions: Mix sugar, shortening, eggs and vanilla well.
Stir in 3 tablespoons buttermilk and sapote pulp.
Sift together
flour, baking powder, soda and salt.
Mix in raisins and nuts.
Pour into waxed paper lined pans.
Let stand 20 minutes before baking.
Bake for 50 to 60 minutes at 350°.

title: english trifle
directions: Prepare cake mix according to package directions using a loaf pan.
Cool and slice into 12 slices.
Cut each slice into 6 small cubes.
Meanwhile, combine pudding with milk according to package directions.
In a 2-quart glass bowl, layer cake cubes.
Sprinkle with 1 1/2 teaspoons sherry, 1 cup fruit and 1 cup pudding. Repeat.
Garnish top with fresh berries.
Chill at least 30 minutes before serving.
Calories 191, cholesterol less than 1 mg; fat 2 g; sodium 311 mg.

title: barbecue (beef)
directions: Put roast in slow cooker with soy sauce and Worcestershire sauce in pot.
Cook on low setting overnight.
Drain off liquid in the morning and separate roast into pieces.
Pour barbecue sauce over meat and warm.
Serve on buns.

title: pepere bousquet's favorite crepes
directions: Beat eggs with fork; add flour and milk.
Mix until batter is smooth.

title: yorkshire parkin
directions: Sift together the flour, baking powder and ginger, and then add the sugar and oatmeal.
Heat the butter and molasses to boiling point, add to the dry ingredients with the egg and milk.
Add the soda dissolved in a tablespoon of hot water.
Beat well; turn into a well-greased, shallow pan and bake slowly about one and one-half hours.

title: sour cream cake
directions: Cream together margarine with sugar.
Add eggs and sour cream until smooth.
In a separate bowl, sift together flour, baking soda and baking powder.
Beat the flour mixture into the sour cream mixture until smooth.

title: best ever cake
directions: Mix ingredients together and place into a 9 x 13-inch pan. Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Let cool.

title: polish mistakes
directions: Cook mixture.
Spread on small pieces bread or crackers, then put in broiler until brown.

title: party punch
directions: Combine liquids.
Add sherbet, a scoop at a time.
Add lots of ice cubes.

title: zucchini chowder
directions: Cook vegetables in salted water for 10 minutes.
Do not drain. Add corn and set aside.
Melt butter and blend flour in until smooth.
Add vegetable mix and cheese.
Heat until very hot, but do not boil.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: chocolate zucchini cake
directions: Mix all ingredients together, except chocolate chips and zucchini.
After blended, add zucchini and pour into greased and floured 9 x 13-inch pan.
Then sprinkle chocolate chips over top of batter and bake at 325° about 40 minutes.

title: egg salad sandwich filling
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Makes 2 cups filling.

title: crazy cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Mix soda in the water; set aside.
Mix together thoroughly the flour, sugar and cocoa.
To dry ingredients, add oil, vinegar and the soda-water mixture.
Bake approximately 45 minutes in a 9 x 14-inch pan.
An easy, moist cake!

title: mom's baked beans
directions: Chop and fry bacon.
Cut onions into rings and saute with bacon.
Add pork and beans, kidney beans and lima beans.
Keep warm.

title: beef stroganoff
directions: Brown hamburger and onion (chopped).
Drain grease.
Add 1 can of mushrooms and cream of mushroom soup.
Cover and simmer for 15 minutes.
Remove from heat; add 8 ounces sour cream.
Serve over rice or noodles.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Serves 4.

title: easy snickers pie
directions: Preheat the oven to 450°.
Bake the pie shell for 7 minutes or until golden.
Remove from the oven and let cool.
Lower the oven temperature to 325°.
Cut the Snickers bars in half lengthwise. Now cut each length into 1/4-inch pieces.
Distribute the pieces over the bottom of the crust.

title: broccoli corn bread
directions: Barely melt butter in pan.
Mix all other ingredients and put in pan.
Bake at 350°.

title: hidden valley pretzels
directions: Mix together oil, dressing mix, dill weed, lemon pepper and garlic powder.
Add pretzels; pour into cookie sheet.
Bake for 10 minutes at 300°.
Stir the pretzels and bake for 10 minutes more.

title: buttermilk salad
directions: Bring jello and crushed pineapple to a boil, let cool.
Add other ingredients, mix well and refrigerate until firm.

title: chocolate chip cake
directions: Grease and flour a 13 x 9-inch pan.
Combine milk and pudding into a medium saucepan.
Stir over medium heat until pudding comes to a full boil.
Remove from heat and stir in dry cake mix.
Do not overstir.
Spread evenly in cake pan.
Sprinkle on chocolate chips.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 45 minutes.

title: pineapple pound cake
directions: Cream shortening, butter and sugar.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating thoroughly after each addition.
Sift flour with baking powder.
Add to creamed mixture, one spoonful at a time alternately with milk.
Add vanilla; stir in crushed pineapple and juice and blend well.
Pour into well-greased 10-inch tube pan. Place in cold oven.
Bake at 325° for 1 1/2 hours.
Let stand in pan 10 minutes and run knife around edge to remove to rack. Combine butter, powdered sugar and 1 cup drained pineapple.
Pour over cake while hot.

title: marinara sauce
directions: In 3-quart saucepan, heat oil and saute garlic.
When garlic is brown, stir in basil, parsley and tomatoes.
Add salt and pepper and simmer for 20 minutes.
Serve with warm pasta and grated Parmesan cheese.

title: creamy baked chicken breast
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Clean chicken and place in a 9 x 13-inch baking pan.
In a mixing bowl, blend together soup and wine.
Then spoon mixture over chicken entirely.
Place Swiss cheese on top of sauce.
Then melt your butter; stir in herb stuffing mix.
Once moistly blended, sprinkle over top of Swiss cheese.
Bake one hour (45 minutes and it may be done).
This dish is easily made ahead of time and refrigerate.
Serve with a fresh vegetable and rice pilaf. Enjoy!

title: southern prune cake
directions: Sift the first 6 ingredients together.
Add remaining ingredients except prunes and pecans.
Beat until smooth.
Add prunes and pecans.
Bake in a greased 13 x 9-inch pan at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: peanut butter fudge cake
directions: Bring to a boil the margarine, water, eggs, cocoa, buttermilk and vanilla.
Pour boiled mixture over sugar, flour and soda.
Mix well with a spoon or low speed on mixer.
Pour into a well-greased pan.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes, or until done.

title: breakfast casserole
directions: Mix together eggs and milk.
Add cheese, sausage, mustard, bread and salt.
Put in casserole dish.
Refrigerate overnight. Bake the next day at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: baked chicken
directions: Melt 1 stick butter; roll chicken in butter, then in crumb mixture.
Arrange in pan, one layer only.
Bake for 1 hour at 350°. Crumb mixture will coat a medium fryer (3 to 4 pounds).

title: better than sex cake
directions: Prepare cake mix.
Bake in sheet pan.
While cake bakes, boil pineapple and sugar.
Puncture cake with fork and pour pineapple over it while hot. Let cool.
Prepare pudding according to directions and spread on cake.
After cake has been cooled completely, spread with Cool Whip.
Then decorate with coconut and nuts.
Refrigerate until ready to serve.

title: brown bread
directions: Combine all ingredients; mix well.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes.
Any flavor fruit is good.
Nuts or raisins may be added. Makes 1 large loaf or 3 cans.

title: frito pie
directions: Pour 1 bag of Fritos in a 9 x 9-inch dish, greased.
Heat both cans of the chili and beans in microwave for 5 minutes.
Pour over Fritos evenly.
Spread both cans of cheese sauce evenly over chili and beans.
Spread sour cream evenly over top of mixture.
Crush the remaining bag of Fritos and sprinkle on top of sour cream.

title: mandarin orange-lettuce salad
directions: Combine first 4 ingredients in a large bowl.
Just before serving, pour dressing over salad and toss.
Yield:
4 to 6 servings.

title: caramel brownies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Melt caramels with 1/3 cup milk in top of double boiler over barely simmering water. Stir frequently. Combine cake mix with melted butter and remaining 1/3 cup milk.
Spread 1/2 of the cake mixture into pan.
Bake 6 to 8 minutes. Remove from oven and sprinkle with chocolate chips and pecans.
Drizzle melted caramels over top; cover with remaining cake batter.
Continue baking for 15 minutes until brownies are firm to touch.

title: enchiladas
directions: Preheat oven to 425°.
Prepare beef according to directions on taco seasoning packet.
Add taco seasoning, water, etc.
When finished, combine the can of refried beans with taco seasoned beef.
Place desired amount of bean/beef mixture in the tortillas and roll.
Place the filled tortillas in a 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.

title: simply delicious salad
directions: Mix together in medium bowl the cottage cheese and orange gelatin.
When well blended add pineapple and Cool Whip.
Mix well and refrigerate in mold or bowl.

title: spanish bean soup
directions: Mix together all ingredients in a large Dutch oven.
Simmer for 2 hours.

title: texas sheet cake
directions: Bring to a boil the margarine, water and cocoa.
Cool slightly.
Mix the remaining ingredients; add cocoa mixture slowly and beat.
Pour thin batter into greased and floured jelly roll pan.
Bake 25 minutes in a 350° oven.

title: blueberry bread
directions: Toss first two ingredients and set aside.
Combine next 4 ingredients.
Combine next 5 ingredients with 1 tablespoon orange rind.
Fold into blueberry mixture.
Pour into greased loaf pan; top with last two ingredients.
Bake in 350° oven for 1 hour.

title: green chili chicken pie
directions: Boil and debone chicken.
Mix chicken, soups, onion, cheese and peppers.
Cook over low fire until mixture starts to bubble. Fry tortillas quickly on both sides until soft.
Layer tortillas and chicken mixture in casserole.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: pan coat(family favorite recipe from the kitchen of gerry ellison)
directions: Blend the ingredients with a mixer.
Store in a plastic container and refrigerate.
Brush on pans, even Teflon ones, before pouring the batter.
Can be used for breads or cakes.

title: sandy's spanish rice
directions: Wash rice 2 to 3 times over running water, draining milky water as much as possible.
Heat oil in skillet and add rice turning over with spatula as it turns whiter and then tan.
Add vegetables and saute along with rice for about 4 to 5 minutes.
Add tomato sauce and enough water or broth to cover rice.
Bring to a boil then back down to simmer and cover but watch occasionally as you may need to add liquid.
When rice has absorbed all broth and is cooked, serve.

title: hamburger chow mein
directions: *Beef bouillon cubes dissolved in 1 1/2 cups water may be used for beef broth.

title: macaroni salad
directions: Cut first five ingredients into small pieces.
Add to remaining ingredients.
Mix well and chill.
Serves 8 to 10.

title: aunt ola's chicken casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients together, except corn flake crumbs, and pour in buttered casserole.
Sprinkle corn flakes on top.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: orange delite
directions: Drain oranges and pineapple; mix all ingredients in a large bowl.
Hand stir until well mixed.
Refrigerate about 1 hour.

title: fudge pie
directions: Melt butter and chocolate.
Beat eggs with a fork and add sugar, vanilla and salt.
Mix flour with nuts.
Combine mixtures and pour into oiled pie pan.
Bake at 300° for 30 minutes.
Cut into pie wedges and serve plain or with whipped cream, Cool Whip or ice cream.
Can be served warm or cold.
It will sink down after you remove it from the oven but that's what makes it good!

title: smoked beef brisket
directions: Wrap brisket in foil and add all ingredients; marinate overnight.
Cook fat side up in oven for 3 hours at 325°.
For a 7 pound brisket, double ingredients and cook for 5 hours.

title: giant stuffed burgers
directions: Mix meat and salt; divide into halves.
Pat one half into bottom of an ungreased 9-inch pie plate.
Mix remaining ingredients; spread within 1 inch of edge of the beef mixture.
In a pie plate shape remaining half into a 9-inch circle.
Place on top of cheese mixture.
Pinch edges together to seal.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 40 to 50 minutes.
Remove and cut into wedges.

title: mom's pie crust
directions: Mix all ingredients together well.
For pie shell, bake at 450° for 10 minutes, then reduce heat to 375° until golden brown, about 1 to 3 minutes.
For pie with top crust, bake at 450° for 15 minutes, then reduce heat to 375° or 400° until golden brown.

title: strawberry delight
directions: Combine sugar and water.
Boil and then add strawberry jello. Stir until dissolved.
Next add strawberries to jello.
Cool mixture until almost set.
While this is cooling, break up angel food cake into pieces and place in a 9 x 13-inch oblong pan. Combine the whipped cream, marshmallows and pecans.
Fold into jello mixture and pour over angel food cake.
Chill and serve.

title: four bean salad
directions: Combine all beans, onion and green pepper in a large bowl. Combine everything else in a jar with a tight lid and mix well. Pour dressing over beans; toss well.
Refrigerate overnight in a covered bowl.

title: marshmal-o-fudge
directions: Mix in	large mixing bowl, Marshmallow Creme and chocolate chips.
Cook
in
large
saucepan
the
sugar,
milk
and margarine.	Bring to
a
boil and cook for 9 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Pour
cooked mixture over other ingredients and beat until stiff.
Add
vanilla
and nuts and stir.
Pour into greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Makes 5 pounds of candy.

title: layered pea salad
directions: In a large bowl, layer the salad, ending with mayonnaise and cheese.
Sprinkle each layer of mayonnaise with sugar.
Fried bacon may be crumbled on top before serving.

title: connie's shish kabob
directions: Combine soy sauce and ginger; place all other ingredients in large bowl.
Pour sauce over and marinate for 4 to 6 hours.
Place onto skewers, alternating items.
Cook on grill over charcoal.

title: mocha meringue puffs
directions: Heat oven to 325°.
In small bowl with electric mixer, beat egg whites, vanilla and salt on medium speed until foamy.
Gradually add sugar, 1 tablespoon at a time, beating at high speed until stiff glossy peaks form.
With small strainer, sift cocoa and espresso powder over meringue mixture; add chocolate chips.
Gently fold into meringue.
Drop by slightly rounded teaspoonfuls 1 inch apart onto ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake for 18 to 20 minutes. Immediately remove from cookie sheet; cool on wire rack.
Makes about 20 cookies.

title: shrimp and scallops
directions: Place
butter, peppers and garlic in heavy cookware and saute over
medium-high
heat
until
tender
but crisp.	Add tomatoes and
parsley
and
cook
3 minutes after returning to boil.
Add shrimp,
scallops, wine and Tabasco sauce and cook until all shrimp are a nice pink, stirring frequently.
Taste the sauce
and add
more	salt,
white
pepper and Tabasco to taste.
I
add Tabasco until it can barely be detected but is not hot.
Serve over a bed of rice.

title: spinach salad sandwiches
directions: Cut each bread slice into assorted shapes.
In a small bowl, combine dressing, eggs, spinach and mushrooms.
Spread evenly on bread.
Top, if desired, with sliced hard-cooked eggs or sliced mushrooms.
Place on damp cloth and refrigerate (covered) until serving time.

title: broccoli soup #3
directions: Cook vegetables with water for 5 to 10 minutes.
Drain.
Save 2 cups of the vegetable water.
Melt butter, stir in flour.
Add onions and salt.
Cook over medium heat 3 minutes, stirring constantly.
Stir in 2 cups hot vegetable water, milk and bouillon cubes.
Add vegetables and heat 20 to 30 minutes.
Before serving, pour in beaten egg in a steady stream, stirring constantly. Garnish with cheese.
Serves 4.

title: fruity cheese ball
directions: Drain fruit cocktail in colander, then smash fruit with a fork to completely drain juice.
Mix fruit cocktail, pudding (dry mix) and orange juice into slightly softened cream cheese. Place on wax paper.
Crush almonds and roll ball-shaped cheese mixture into the nuts.
(Can chill cheese mixture before rolling in the nuts.) Makes 1 large ball or 2 smaller.
Freezes well. Serve with Ritz or Town House crackers.

title: scallops au gratin
directions: Cut scallops in small pieces and saute gently, in 1 tablespoon butter for 1 to 2 minutes.
Stir in soup, season to taste with salt and pepper.
Add a dash of hot pepper sauce; put in small shells (about 8).
Mix cheese with crumbs and remaining butter, melted, and sprinkle over top.
Broil a few inches from heat until lightly browned.
Makes about 8 servings.
May be put in casserole and baked.

title: chocolate brownies
directions: Combine melted chocolate and melted butter in bowl; mix well. Stir in eggs and sugar.
Add flour and vanilla; mix well. Dust pecans lightly with additional flour.
Stir into batter.
Spread in greased 8-inch square baking pan.
Bake at 325° for 25 to 30 minutes or until brownies test done.
Cool.
Cut into squares. Yield:
24 servings.

title: barbecue meat balls
directions: Combine; shape into small
balls.
Place in flat baking dish.

title: dannon muffins
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Grease muffin cups or line with paper baking cups.
In large bowl, combine flour, sugar, baking powder, baking soda and salt.
Gently add yogurt, milk and blueberries. Stir just until dry ingredients are moistened.
Fill muffin cups 2/3 full.
Bake 18 minutes or until brown and toothpick inserted into center comes out clean.
Serve warm.
Makes 12 muffins. Contains 120 calories; 2 grams fat; 5 milligrams cholesterol.

title: sweet and sour meatballs
directions: Mix hamburger, onion, salt and rice together.
Form into balls.
Place balls into baking pan.
Mix together ketchup, sugar, vinegar and water to make sauce.
Pour sauce over meatballs. Cover with foil.
Bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: chocolate chip cookies
directions: Cream together butter, sugar and brown sugar, then add eggs and vanilla.
Mix together flour, oatmeal (in blender, make the oatmeal to a powder), salt, baking powder and baking soda.
Then mix altogether.
Add chocolate chips, Hershey bar (grated) and nuts.

title: pretzel salad
directions: Mix butter, 1/4 cup sugar and crushed pretzels and press in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes; cool.

title: lasagna
directions: Brown hamburger.
Stir in spaghetti sauce.
Cook noodles.
Mix cottage cheese, eggs and Mozzarella cheese.
Drain noodles.
Spray pan with Pam.
Place layer of noodles, layer of meat and layer of cheese.
Continue until pan is full.
Bake at 375° for 45 minutes to 1 hour.
Let sit for 15 minutes and serve.

title: east texas onion pudding
directions: Saute onions in 3 tablespoons oil; cool.
Mix cream, eggs, garlic, salt, pepper and lemon juice and add to onions.
Pour into a 8-inch square pan.
Bake 20 minutes at 300°.
Top with deep fried onion rings, bake another 20 minutes until set in middle.

title: zucchini torte
directions: Mix the first 7 ingredients in blender.
When well blended, add the balance of ingredients.
Place mixture in oiled 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 325° for 30 to 35 minutes.
Don't overbake or it will get dry.
Tastes better cold the next day.

title: squash casserole
directions: Mash squash.
Mix ingredients together.
Pat in baking dish and bake in a 350° oven for 35 to 40 minutes.
Sprinkle more stuffing mix over top.

title: homemade noodles
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Roll out and cut into strips. Drop into chicken broth.

title: glazed potato doughnuts
directions: Dissolve yeast in warm water; combine milk, shortening, sugar and salt.
Cool until lukewarm.
Stir in yeast, potatoes and eggs. Gradually add enough flour to make a soft dough.
Turn onto floured surface; knead until smooth and satiny.
Place in a lightly greased bowl.
Turn over to grease top; cover.
Let rise in a warm place until doubled in size.
Will take from 1 to 1 1/2 hours.

title: carrot bran muffins
directions: In medium bowl, combine V-8 juice, cereal, carrots and raisins; let stand 5 minutes.
Add remaining ingredients; stir until just mixed.

title: sauerkraut salad
directions: Mix all ingredients except sugar, then sprinkle the sugar over top of mixture.
Cover container and refrigerate for 24 hours. Mix well and serve.

title: lemon icing
directions: Grate the rind of the lemon and squeeze the juice.
Use a good boiler and stir the egg yolk, sugar, water, lemon and juice, and cornstarch.
Cook until icing has thickened.

title: garlic spread
directions: In a small bowl, blend together margarine and garlic.
Cover mixture and store in refrigerator. Use to spread roast beef, fried shrimp, lamb or bacon and tomato sandwich; spread on hamburger or hot dog rolls. Makes 1 cup.

title: pumpkin cookies
directions: Pour boiling water over raisins and drain.
Mix all ingredients.
Bake at 300° for 12 minutes on greased cookie sheet. Ice cookies with powdered sugar and 2 or 3 drops maple flavoring.

title: german chocolate cake icing
directions: Combine the evaporated milk, sugar, 3 slightly beaten egg yolks, butter and the vanilla.
Cook and stir over medium heat until thickened, about 12 minutes.
Add the coconut and chopped pecans.
Cool until thick enough to spread.
Makes 2 1/2 cups.

title: dixie chicken salad
directions: Cut chicken in 1/2-inch cubes.
Cut potatoes in 1/2-inch cubes.
Drain oranges.
Cut celery in 1/2-inch cubes.
Mix all together.
Place in refrigerator for 1 hour.
Serve on lettuce. Serves 6.

title: fruit ball
directions: Mix cream cheese, dry pudding mix, orange juice and fruit cocktail until well blended. Chill in refrigerator until able to roll into ball. Roll in chopped pecans. Serve with vanilla wafers or graham crackers. Great appetizer for parties or the holidays.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Grind cranberries and peeled orange.
Mix with pineapple and sugar and let stand while mixing Jell-O according to directions on package.
Add cranberry mixture to Jell-O; add pecans and put in refrigerator to congeal.

title: fancy tomatoes
directions: Place a layer of unpeeled tomatoes in a shallow bowl (8-inch diameter).
Top with a layer of thinly sliced onion, then on top of this, sprinkle a pinch of salt, sugar, black pepper and basil with a tablespoon of olive oil and vinegar.
Cover and refrigerate several hours before serving. This is well worth having on hand for summer meals.

title: bread and butter pickles
directions: Slice cukes and onions, then mix in salt; cover and let stand 3 hours.
Drain well.
Make a syrup of the sugar, vinegar and water, turmeric, cloves and mustard seed.
Pour over cuke slices and place over low heat.
Heat but do not boil.
Pour into hot jars and seal.

title: chop suey cake
directions: Mix all ingredients together until well blended.
Pour in greased and floured 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake 35 to 45 minutes in a 350° oven.

title: zucchini bars
directions: Cream first five ingredients together; add flour, salt, cinnamon and baking powder.
Add dates, coconut, raisins and zucchini.
Bake in 10 x 15-inch greased cookie pan at 350° for 25 to 35 minutes.

title: cheese bites
directions: Beat butter at medium speed with electric mixer until creamy. Gradually add cheese, beating well.
Combine flour, salt and red pepper.
Add to butter and cheese mixture, mixing well.
Cover and chill 1 hour.
Shape into balls and place in freezer until firm. Place on baking sheet and bake in a 400° oven for 12 to 14 minutes. May shape into logs and slice after chilled instead of making balls.

title: chicken salad
directions: Combine
chicken
and
celery.
Combine next 6 ingredients, stirring
well.
Add
to
chicken mixture and toss well. Sprinkle with toasted almonds.
Serve on lettuce; garnish with melon and grapes.
Yields 8 to 10 servings.

title: chilighetti
directions: Brown meat and onion.
Then add beans and spaghetti and put in baking dish or pan.
Pour over the tomato juice and bake for 1 hour in 350° oven (I use a little less spaghetti).	Also use enough tomato juice so it isn't dry; I use more than 3 cups juice.

title: hamburger sauce(for hamburger and hot dogs)
directions: Place meat in boiler and cover with water.
Let boil for 20 minutes.
Add water as needed.
Add other ingredients and boil over medium heat 30 minutes or until cooks down to sauce.

title: millionaire pie
directions: Mix milk and lemon juice.
Add all ingredients.
Pour into pie shells.
Chill.
Makes 2 pies.

title: gerry's vegetable casserole
directions: Cut vegetables into bite-sized pieces.
With exception of peas, steam for 5 minutes.
Place steamed vegetables in 2 1/2-quart casserole.
Add peas.
Mix soup and Cheddar cheese together and spoon over vegetables.
Combine bread crumbs, Parmesan cheese and margarine.
Spread over casserole.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Serves 10 to 12.

title: chicken delight
directions: Mix cracker crumbs, grated cheese, 1/4 c. melted oleo.
Pat into baking dish, spread peas in bottom of dish.
Combine potatoes, pimento and chicken with sauce.
Pour over cracker and cheese crust and peas and bake until bubbly.

title: mold cranberry waldorfs
directions: Bring 1 cup of the cranberry juice cocktail to boiling.
Stir in gelatin until dissolved.
Add remaining cranberry juice and salt.
Chill until partially set.
Stir in apple and celery.
Pour into 1-quart mold.
Chill until set.
Unmold on crisp greens.

title: pineapple cake
directions: In large mixing bowl beat the eggs until light and fluffy.
Add the can (undrained) of crushed pineapple, flour, granulated, brown sugars and the baking soda.
Mix the ingredients by hand.
(If you use a mixer, too much air is beaten in, and this makes it probable that the cake will fall.)
Stir in the walnuts.
Spread the batter in an ungreased 13 x 9-inch pan.
Bake in 350° oven for 45 to 50 minutes or until a toothpick inserted in the center comes out clean.
Frost when cool with cream cheese frosting.
Sprinkle some additional walnuts on the top.

title: chili cheese dip
directions: Mix ingredients.
Microwave until hot, about 5 minutes.
Serve hot with chips.

title: sentz burgers
directions: Mix together all ingredients except soup and Worcestershire sauce.
Form into patties; fry or grill.
In large saucepan mix soup and sauce; warm up.
Add to meat.
Serve on buns.

title: creamy squash casserole
directions: Cook squash in salted
water
until tender; drain well. Add next 7 ingredients.
Melt 3/4 stick of oleo in frying pan. Add stuffing and mix well.
Pack
stuffing
into
bottom
of 2 quart baking dish (reserving some stuffing for the top).
Pour squash mixture over
stuffing
and sprinkle remaining stuffing over top. Dot rest of oleo on top of casserole.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Serves 8.

title: simple stroganoff
directions: Mix together all
but
sour
cream,
bake for 1 hour at 350°, then add sour cream and bake for 30 more minutes.
Serve over rice or noodles.

title: applesauce cake
directions: Add flour, baking soda and salt together.
Add in dates, raisins and nuts.
Cream shortening with spices, cocoa and sugar. Add eggs, 1 at a time and alternate flour mixture and applesauce; add all together.
Bake in cake pan for 45 minutes at 350°.

title: stuffed baked fish
directions: Cook onions in oleo until tender; cook all raw ingredients. Add all ingredients to bread stuffing.
Stir gently.
Stuff fish after seasoning cavity.
Close opening with skewer.
Cook, uncovered, in 350° oven.
Brush occasionally with butter (oleo) and lemon juice.
Bake one and a half hours.
Serves 10 to 12 people.

title: richard petty's stuffed peppers
directions: Prepare stuffing for peppers.
Boil peppers in water for 5 minutes.
Combine ground beef, onion, chili powder, eggs, ketchup, cornflakes, salt and pepper; stuff peppers.

title: german chocolate upside-down cake
directions: Use margarine to grease 9 x 13 baking dish. Pour in pecans. Mix cake mix according to box directions and pour on top of nuts. Soften margarine and cream cheese. Mix with powdered sugar. Spoon on top of cake and bake at 350° for about 50 minutes.

title: brocken
directions: *This can be done in your microwave.

title: orange chiffon cake
directions: Spoon sifted flour into cup.
Add baking powder and salt.

title: chadecki dip
directions: Drain yogurt overnight in cheesecloth placed in colander. Remove yogurt from cheesecloth and drain off water.
To this add the cucumber (shredded) and also drained off water overnight, salt and pepper, dill, minced garlic and olive oil.
Mix all well and refrigerate 3 to 6 hours.
Serve with sesame bread sticks.

title: mrs. claire's jello salad
directions: Pour the juice from the can of pineapple into a 1-cup measuring cup.
Add water to fill cup.
Make jello as directed on package, using the water and pineapple juice mixture instead of just water.
Add pineapple; mix.
Add softened cream cheese; mix on high.
Chill for 15 to 20 minutes, then add Cool Whip.
Chill for at least 2 hours before serving.
Orange jello can be substituted with any flavor jello.

title: do-ahead mashed potatoes
directions: Cook potatoes; mash with electric mixer until there are no lumps.
Mix again, adding all ingredients; cool.
Put in a greased casserole.
Dot with butter.
Cook at 350° for 40 minutes until heated through.
Cook uncovered.
Can be prepared a few days ahead and refrigerated until the day you want to serve them.
Serves 12.

title: mexican bean dip
directions: Combine first 3 ingredients; cook until pepper and onion are tender.
Add the rest of the ingredients and simmer 1 hour.

title: chili con queso
directions: Melt
cheese
in
top of a double boiler.
Add tomatoes and green chilies.
Stir until smooth and creamy.
Serve with tortilla chips or corn chips.

title: funnel cakes
directions: You will need a funnel with 3/8-inch opening.
Heat 2-inches of Crisco in a deep skillet to 375°.
Pour batter in a circular design.
Let brown and turn only once.
Remove from pan, drain and serve hot with powdered or brown sugar.
Makes 2 dozen.

title: seven layer salad
directions: Begin layering ingredients in the order to cover the bottom of the dish you choose.

title: rice and chicken casserole
directions: Melt oleo in casserole dish.
Place rice in bottom of dish. Arrange chicken on top of rice.
Pour soups over chicken; add water.
Bake at 300° for 2 hours or until chicken is done.

title: three cheese chicken bake(layer of pasta, cheese and chicken.  a treat for calorie
directions: Cook lasagne noodles in boiling salt water according to package directions; drain well.
Cook onion and green pepper in butter or margarine until tender.
Stir in condensed soup, mushrooms, pimiento, skim milk and basil.

title: rub for chicken or pork
directions: Mix thoroughly; put in shaker. Shake on chicken or pork 30 minutes before cooking, preferably on a grill.

title: breakfast sausage casserole
directions: Fry sausage, drain well
and
break up.
Break bread in bottom of large greased casserole dish.
Sprinkle sausage over the bread, then
sprinkle
cheese.
Mix
remaining ingredients together and pour
over
mixture
in
dish.
Refrigerate overnight.
Bake at 350° for
minutes to 1 hour, until hot and bubbly and brown on top.

title: party stuffed eggs
directions: Peel and halve eggs.
Place yolks in medium mixing bowl. Blend in remaining ingredients and whip with mixer until
fluffy. Fill egg whites generously.
Top with paprika, sliced olives or tiny shrimp.
Serve at room temperature.

title: cheese biscuits
directions: Cut shortening into flour until mixture is coarse crumbs.
Add milk and stir with a fork until dough leaves sides of bowl.
Turn dough out onto a lightly floured board; knead until smooth.
Roll to 1/2-inch thickness and cut with a floured 2-inch cutter.
Bake in a preheated oven at 450° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: strawberry pie
directions: Cook sugar, water and cornstarch.
Boil until clear.
Remove from heat.
Stir in the package of jello.
Let cool and add strawberries.
Pour into the pie shells.
Put them in the refrigerator to chill.
Serve with Cool Whip topping.

title: french fried batter
directions: Beat together all ingredients.
Chill 1 hour.
Dip shrimp, fish or meat in batter and deep fry in oil.
Drain and serve at once.

title: four layer delight
directions: Cut together first 3 ingredients (like pie crust). Pat into 9 x 12-inch Pyrex dish. Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Let cool completely.

title: swiss steak
directions: Dust each steak piece with flour.
Pound flour, salt and pepper into meat.
Brown on both sides in hot grease.
Slice onions and add garlic powder or salt on top.
Mix water, sour cream, soy sauce and brown sugar.
Pour ingredients over steak.
Bake in a 300° oven for an hour in a casserole dish or pan.

title: crispy baked chicken(the crumbs give this skinless chicken a crispy coating)
directions: Remove all skin from the chicken.
Rinse and dry the pieces thoroughly.
Dip in milk.
Mix cornflake crumbs with rosemary and pepper; roll in the seasoned crumbs.
Let stand briefly.

title: pudding dessert
directions: For crust:
Mix flour, butter and 1/2 cup chopped nuts.
Press into 10 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes; cool.

title: broccoli cheese cornbread
directions: Cook broccoli 5 minutes, drain.
Beat eggs until frothy.
Add cornbread mix, margarine, buttermilk, broccoli, cheese, onion, salt and pepper.
Stir well; then bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: breakfast casserole
directions: Crumble sausage into skillet.
Cook over medium heat until brown, stirring occasionally.
Drain well.
Line bottom of greased 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking pan with crescent dinner rolls, pressing perforations to seal.
Sprinkle with sausage and cheese.
Combine eggs, milk, salt and pepper; beat well and pour over sausage and cheese.
Bake at 425° for 15 minutes, or until set.
Let stand 5 minutes; cut into squares and serve.
Yields 6 to 8 servings.

title: tex mix
directions: Serve with nacho chips.

title: cheese blintzes
directions: Mix cream cheese, egg yolks, 1/2 c. sugar and lemon juice smooth. Trim crust from bread and roll out. Brush one side with melted margarine and place one teaspoon of ingredients on unbuttered side of bread. Roll up and dip in brown sugar and cinnamon mixture. Freeze. When needed, bake at 350° for 10 minutes.

title: bean salad
directions: Drain all beans.
Put in bowl and add green pepper, onion and celery.
Add other ingredients and mix.
Refrigerate 24 hours.

title: salmon cheese pate
directions: Drain the salmon and remove bones.
Blend cheeses, salmon and seasonings until smooth.
Line bowl with plastic wrap and fill. Chill several hours.
Unmold.
Garnish with parsley sprigs or edible flowers, pansies.

title: corn salad
directions: Mix all vegetables together.
Mix oil, vinegar and sugar. Pour over vegetables.
Cover; refrigerate overnight.

title: cheese cake
directions: Preheat oven to 300°.
Reserve 1 cup of dry cake mix.
In large mixing bowl, combine remaining cake mix, 1 egg and oil (will be crumbly).
Press crust mixture evenly into bottom and 3/4 way up the sides of a greased 13 x 9-inch pan.

title: spoon bread
directions: Scald milk.
Stir in corn meal and bring to a boil, making a mush.
Remove from heat and stir in beaten eggs, salt, baking powder and melted butter.
Pour mixture into a buttered baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 45 minutes or until nicely browned. Serves 6.
Serve while warm.

title: squash dressing
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Turn into a greased 2-quart baking dish.
Bake for 35 to 40 minutes at 350°.

title: bean bake
directions: Cook sausage; drain well.
Mix with all other ingredients in large casserole.
Drizzle barbecue sauce on top.
Bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: "ono" pumpkin pie *
directions: Partially thaw yogurt.
Blend sugar, salt, cinnamon, ginger, nutmeg and pumpkin.
Fold in yogurt.
Mound in pie shell and re-freeze.

title: "more" casserole
directions: Put in skillet the oleo, onion and green pepper; brown lightly. Add meat and brown.
Put in a large pot and add remainder of ingredients.
Put in oven.
Bake 1 1/2 hours at 325°.

title: fried chicken fillet
directions: Cover chicken breast with buttermilk; let stand for 2 hours. Batter with flour, garlic salt, sprinkle of lemon juice and Worcestershire sauce.
Oven fry until desired brown.

title: chunky chilli casserole
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Mix stuffing and water in 2-quart casserole.
Press evenly into bottom of casserole.
Set aside. Brown meat and onion in large skillet on medium-high.
Remove from heat.
Stir in chili, 1 cup cheese, corn and olives.
Spoon over stuffing in casserole.
Bake 25 minutes.
Serve over remaining 1/2 cup cheese and sour cream.
Makes 4 servings.

title: toffee bars
directions: Melt margarine in microwave.
Add sugar and vanilla.
Beat well.
Add flour and mix well.
Stir in chocolate morsels and walnuts.
Press in ungreased 10 x 15-inch jelly roll pan.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes or until brown.
While still warm, cut into squares.
Cool and remove from pan.

title: sawdust salad
directions: Dissolve jello in boiling water, add cold water and pineapple. When partially set cover with miniature marshmallows. Cool until set. Cook pineapple juice, sugar, cornstarch and eggs until thick. Cool and pour over jello. Mix cream cheese and cool whip. Spread over mixture and sprinkle with shredded cheese.

title: chicken parmigiana
directions: Pound chicken slightly at thickest parts.
Mix bread crumbs with half of the Parmesan cheese.
Dip chicken in beaten eggs and coat with crumbs.
Add chicken to heated frypan with oil and butter.
Brown chicken on both sides

title: chicken croquettes (or salmon or tuna)
directions: Mix together chicken or fish, lemon juice, rice or leftover peas, salt, onion, egg, milk and bread crumbs.

title: crackers
directions: Rub the butter into flour.
Dissolve soda into the glass of buttermilk.
Strain through a fine sieve into the flour.
Add salt and beat well.
Roll thin and bake.
If not crisp when first baked, put them in again and bake over again.

title: tuna casserole with biscuits
directions: Saute green pepper and onion in cooking oil.
Add flour, chicken with rice soup and milk.
Add lemon juice and tuna or other meat.

title: summer beef stew
directions: Put first 5 ingredients into pan.
Mix remaining ingredients. Pour over meat.
Add vegetables.
Cover and bake 4 hours at 250°.

title: biscuits
directions: Blend flour and 1 stick margarine with pastry blender. Mix in buttermilk. Knead 8-10 times. Roll out and cut with biscuit cutter. Bake in 425° oven for 10 minutes. Brush with melted butter and brown. Makes 10-12 biscuits.

title: squash croquettes
directions: Cook squash until tender, then drain well; mash squash and add other ingredients.
Add more bread crumbs if necessary to handle. Form into oblong croquettes and roll in corn meal.
Fry in deep fat until brown.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Simmer celery and onions in butter.
Mix in the chicken, soup and noodles.
Put in greased casserole.
Before baking, add the milk.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: pina colada fruit dip
directions: Combine first four ingredients in blender.
Process until well blended.
Chill, covered, overnight.
Serve with your favorite fresh fruit.
Makes 2 cups.

title: veggie beef bake
directions: In a frying pan, place ground beef and cook until brown.
Add macaroni and spaghetti sauce and cook for about 10 minutes.
Stir in frozen mix vegetables, onions and garlic powder.
Cover and simmer for about 15 minutes.

title: crabmeat canapes(easy)
directions: Mix cheese, salt, garlic powder, butter and mayonnaise.
Fold in crabmeat.
Spread on 6 English muffin halves.
Place on cookie sheet and cover with foil or plastic wrap.
Freeze.
When ready to use, cut each muffin into quarters while frozen.
Place under broiler until bubbly and brown.

title: tempah-popcorn rice
directions: Boil water with Vegex.
Add rice.
Reduce heat.
Cook until water is absorbed and rice is tender; set aside.

title: squash and corn casserole
directions: Slice squash very thinly and cook in covered saucepan with 1/4 cup water until very soft.
Drain.
Saute onions in butter just until browning.
Remove both from heat and combine with cream of chicken soup and mushroom soup, eggs, 1 cup bread crumbs, corn and 1 cup of cheese.
Put in buttered 9 x 9 dish.
Combine remaining bread crumbs and cheese and cover top.
Sprinkle paprika over the contents and bake in a preheated 350°
oven for 30 minutes, or until the casserole is firm and the top is slightly brown.

title: baked brie
directions: Press out four crescent rolls.
Place Brie in the middle and wrap Brie with surrounding crescent rolls.
Top crescent rolls with butter, garlic and parsley.
Bake at 325° for 15 to 20 minutes, until brown.
Serve with crackers.

title: strawberry salad(serves 10)
directions: Dissolve jello in hot water.
Mix in fruit.
Pour half of mixture into a mold; chill, leaving other half out of refrigerator.
When mixture is set in mold, spread with sour cream.
Carefully spoon other half of mixture over the sour cream and let set.

title: noodle candy
directions: Combine morsels together
in saucepan.
Stir constantly until melted on low heat.
Remove
from
heat, stir in noodles and peanuts.
Mix quickly.
Spoon onto wax paper and let cool.

title: spinach balls
directions: Cook and drain the spinach.
Mix all ingredients.
Let stand overnight. Shape into balls.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes. Serve warm (can be reheated in microwave).

title: microwave toffee candy
directions: Have ready a piece of foil (12 x 16-inches).
Spread nuts on foil.
Combine water, sugar, butter and salt in a large Pyrex bowl with lid.
Cook, without stirring, for 9 to 11 minutes until mixture is lightly browned.
Stir right quick and pour over nuts on foil.
When cold and hard, spread with melted chocolate.
Cool. Break into pieces.

title: hot spiced tea
directions: Put juices and water in percolator.
