Put rest of ingredients into basket and perk 10 minutes or until spices permeate.
Serve hot.
Yields 8 to 10 cups.

title: vanilla fruit salad
directions: Mix all ingredients together and chill.

title: pecan pie
directions: Mix first 5 ingredients well.
Pour in unbaked pie shell. Bake at 400° for 10 minutes, then at 300° for 30 minutes or until center is set.

title: golden door baked macaroni and cheese
directions: In a large saucepan, melt the butter.
Blend in the flour. Gradually add the milk, stirring constantly.
Add the seasonings. Cook until the sauce is thickened.
Add 1 cup of cheese and stir until melted.
Add the cooked macaroni.
Turn the mixture into an 8-inch square baking dish.
Sprinkle the top with the remaining grated cheese.
Bake in a 375° oven for about 15 minutes.
Heat under the broiler until the cheese is bubbly and lightly browned. Serves 4 to 6.

title: delicious prune cake
directions: Cream sugar, shortening and eggs.
Add flour and rest of ingredients.
Cook at 325° until done.

title: no cook refrigerator pickles
directions: Peel and slice cucumbers.
In a large mixing bowl, combine all other ingredients.
Stir for about 1 or 2 minutes.
Add sliced cucumbers.
Stir with large serving to coat all slices with wet mixture.
Cover with Saran Wrap.
Refrigerate for 4 to 5 hours (stir every hour or so).
Transfer to French canning jars.
Store in fridge.
They will keep for several weeks.

title: dad's special cherry freezer ice cream
directions: Chop cherries and juice (or other desired fruit) in blender or food processor.
Add egg, sugar, evaporated milk, condensed milk and vanilla to cherries in blender container; blend all together. Pour into freeze container and fill container to "fill line" with whole milk.
Cover container tightly with lid.
Process in ice cream freezer with salt and ice until cream is firm.
Enjoy!

title: sweet potato delight
directions: Mix pretzels and butter and pat into 9 x 13 baking dish. Bake 15 minutes at 350°. Mix cream cheese, Cool Whip and sugar. Spread on first layer. Mix mashed sweet potatoes, 1 cup sugar, egg, cornstarch and vanilla. Beat real good and add to second layer. Let set overnight.

title: sisser's peach cobbler
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Melt stick of margarine in baking dish. Add peach juice to sugar, flour and baking powder.

Mix well. Pour batter into baking dish but do not mix with margarine. Combine peaches and cinnamon then, using a slotted spoon, place peaches evenly over batter in pan but do not mix with batter. Bake in preheated 375° oven for 30 minutes.

title: peanut butter pie
directions: Mix together until smooth and pour into graham cracker or chocolate crust.
Chill overnight.

title: oven omelet
directions: Heat oven to 325° in oven.
Melt butter in 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Tilt and coat bottom of dish.

title: corn casserole
directions: Drain corn, reserving 1/4 cup juice for recipe.
Beat eggs. Add the rest of the ingredients.
Pour into a greased 9 x 12-inch pan. Bake at 325° for 1 hour.

title: potato chip cookies
directions: Mix all ingredients; drop by teaspoon onto ungreased cookie sheet.
Press flat.
Bake at 325° for 10 to 15 minutes.

title: mississippi mud sauce
directions: In small bowl, stir together sugar and cocoa.
Stir in evaporated milk.
Cook and stir over medium heat until boiling. Remove from heat.
Stir in peanut butter.
Serve warm over ice cream or sliced pound cake.
Yields 1 1/2 cups sauce.

title: bombay chicken
directions: Salt, paprika and flour chicken.
Brown in oil.
Place chicken in baking dish.
Mix remaining ingredients and pour over chicken. Cover chicken with aluminum foil.
Bake at 375° for 45 minutes.

title: cheese puffs with olives
directions: Cream together Cheddar cheese and soft butter.
Add rest of ingredients and work into a stiff dough.
Chill until firm enough to handle.
Take pieces, pat in hand, place a whole stuffed olive in center.
Roll dough around it.
Bake 15 minutes at 400°.
Makes 20 puffs.

title: barbecue patties
directions: Cook and drain ground beef.
Combine bread crumbs and milk. Add to ground beef.
Sprinkle salt and pepper to taste.
Shape into patties and place in baking dish.
Pour barbecue sauce over patties.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 45 minutes or until done.

title: scalloped corn
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Mix all together and put in a 1 1/2-quart casserole dish.
Bake 1 hour.

title: treasure island salad
directions: Combine the pineapple, carrots, raisins and sunflower seeds in large bowl.
Combine yogurt, lemon juice and orange rind.
In small bowl or jar, mix or shake until well blended.
Pour over the salad.
Serve in individual bowls.
Garnish with orange slices. Serves 4.

title: creamy cole slaw
directions: Stir together Miracle Whip, vinegar, salt, sugar, pepper and onion.
Just before serving, toss mixture with cabbage.
May be prepared the day before, pour on dressing when ready to serve. Refrigerate.

title: old fashion peach cobbler
directions: Steam peaches, fresh or frozen, until tender.
Add no water. Add sugar and 2 tablespoons flour and 1/2 of the oleo.
Pour into a baking dish.
Make a pastry of the 1 cup flour, shortening, salt and milk.
Roll out and cut in strips.
Pout on top of peaches. Spoon remaining oleo over strips and bake 45 minutes at 350°.

title: rice-corn casserole
directions: Mix ingredients (I cook corn a little while rice is cooking). Put grated cheese on top and bake long enough to melt cheese.

title: pear marmalade
directions: Peel pears; cover with water.
Cook until done; drain.
Mash pears; measure out 4 cups.
Add sugar and jello.
Cook until it starts to boil, stirring constantly.
Cook 20 to 25 minutes.
Pour into heated jars.
Seal with hot lids and rings.
Makes 3 to 4 pints.

title: mexican lasagna
directions: Saute onion, garlic and pepper in oil.
Add salsa, pepper, chili powder and cumin.
Heat thoroughly and then simmer until sauce is reduced to 4 cups.

title: honey mustard chicken
directions: In a bowl mix cornstarch, broth, honey and mustard until smooth.
Set aside.

title: buttermilk salad
directions: Put the Jell-O and pineapple in saucepan and bring to a boil. Let cool and add the buttermilk and Cool Whip.
You can add nuts, if desired. This makes 2 dishes.

title: macho nacho(microwave)
directions: Spoon chili over chips.
Sprinkle with cheese.
Heat in microwave until cheese melts (1 to 2 minutes).

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli 5 minutes in salted water; drain.
Mix soup, mayonnaise, eggs, onions and cheese.
Pour over broccoli.
Cover with crushed crackers.
Bake for 30 minutes at 350°.

title: peanut butter oatmeal goodies
directions: Mix sugar, cocoa, margarine and milk in a pan on stove.
Bring to a rolling boil (heavy bubbling).
Remove from burner and add peanut butter, vanilla and oatmeal, in that order, mixing well after each addition.
Drop by teaspoon on wax paper.
Cool and serve.
These keep well for up to a week in a sealed container in the refrigerator.

title: ham and noodle casserole
directions: Cook noodles in salt water until tender, drain.
Fry onion and green pepper in fat until tender but not brown.
Combine all ingredients except crumbs.
Put mixture in a greased baking dish; top with crumbs.
Bake for 20 minutes at 375°.
Yields 4 servings.

title: fruit dip
directions: Mix and chill a few hours before serving.
Use with sliced fruits, use as you would with veggies and ranch dip.

title: idiot's delight
directions: Melt marshmallows with milk in a double boiler.
Cool in refrigerator for several hours or overnight.
Add remaining ingredients to cooled mixture.
Keep refrigerated.
Serves 10 to 12.

title: chocolate chip muffins
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Grease 12 muffin cups.

title: brown sugar cookies
directions: Beat all ingredients except flour together, then add flour. Pinch off balls the size of walnuts and bake on lightly buttered cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for about 8 minutes.

title: carrots
directions: Peel and slice carrots in 1/8-inch.
Cook in salted water until tender, about 15 minutes.
Cool.
Place half of carrots in bowl.
Separate onion slices into rings.
Arrange on top of carrots and peppers.
Arrange the remainder of carrots on top. Mix soup or bisque and other ingredients until smooth.
Pour over carrots and let stand overnight.

title: key lime pie
directions: Dissolve gelatin in boiling water; add lime rind and juice and pour slowly into beaten egg yolk, stirring continually.
Add condensed milk and Bitters and chill until slightly thickened. Stir to avoid gelatin settling on bottom of bowl.
Beat egg white until stiff peaks form.
Fold into gelatin mixture.
Add food coloring.
Pour into pie shell and chill until firm (about 3 hours).
Garnish with whipped cream or whipped topping and lime slices if desired.

title: mexican chicken soup - chicken caldo
directions: Using a large pot, add chicken, quartered onion, carrots, bay leaf, 2 tsp. salt.
Bring to a boil, then simmer 45 minutes.

title: artichoke dip(a favorite)
directions: Combine ingredients and pour into 1 1/2-quart baking dish. Bake at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes or until heated through.
Serve warm with crackers.

title: my mother-in-law's homemade noodles
directions: Use amount of flour and water according to amount of noodles wanted.
Mix up thoroughly.
Roll and cut.
Put into seasoned broth.

title: nancy's no cholesterol salad dressing
directions: Mix all together.
Shake well before using.

title: swedish meat balls(appetizers)
directions: Have meat ground together (twice).
Pour cream over crumbs. Saute onion in butter.
Add to crumbs.
Combine meat, egg, seasonings and crumbs.
Mix well but do not knead.
Use a teaspoon of meat mixture for each ball.
Brown them in 2 tablespoons butter or margarine.
Remove from skillet.
Add 2 tablespoons flour and 1 cup water for gravy.
Add 2 beef bouillon cubes for flavor and return meat balls to skillet.
Let simmer 15 to 25 minutes.
Serve with toothpicks from chafing dish.

title: clam dip
directions: Mix cheese with
clams	using
only 1/2 the clam juice. Mix in electric mixer.
Use with crackers or potato chips.

title: rice pilaf(serves 6 to 8)*
directions: Use a pan that can go from stove to oven with lid.
Put water, bouillon, butter and seasonings in pan.
Bring to boil.
When butter is melted, add rice and browned vermicelli.
Bring to a boil.

title: inside-out chocolate bundt cake
directions: Combine pudding mix, cake mix, chocolate chips, milk and eggs in a very large bowl.
Mix by hand until well blended (about 2 minutes).
Fold in pecans.
Bake in greased Bundt pan in preheated 350° oven for 50 to 55 minutes or until cake springs back when lightly pressed with fingers.
Cool 30 minutes in pan, then remove.
The cake may be cut into pieces and frozen so small portions may be used at a time.

title: almond candy
directions: Melt butter in heavy pan.
Stir in sugar and almonds.
Cook over medium heat for 8 to 12 minutes.
Stir so sugar dissolves and almonds pop.
Pour out into cookie sheet.
Spread about 1/2-inch deep.
Cover with chocolate chips.
Spread evenly when melted. Cool.
Break into pieces.

title: creamy peanut butter fudge
directions: Boil for 2 minutes confectioners sugar, butter and milk. Remove from heat and add peanut butter, marshmallow cream and vanilla.
Place in greased square cake pan.

title: cookies kids can make
directions: Mix cake mix and "goodie" pieces together and make a "well" in center.
Add vegetable oil and eggs to "well."
Mix very well by hand.
Drop by teaspoonfuls on slightly oiled cookie sheet, or make jaw breaker-sized balls by hand.
Bake at 325° for 10 to 12 minutes.
Makes 4 to 5 dozen.

title: lima bean and beef ball casserole
directions: Soak bread in milk.
In another bowl mix 1 teaspoon salt, 1/4 teaspoon pepper, egg and garlic.
Squeeze excess milk out of bread.
Add egg mixture and beef.
Stir lightly with a fork. Pinch off balls (size of walnut).
Handle lightly.
Brown on all sides in 1 tablespoon of margarine.

title: pineapple punch
directions: Mix 1/2 container or more of sherbet to a bottle of ginger ale.
It's better when creamy.
Put the frozen pineapple in and when it starts to melt you also have chunks of pineapple in the punch.

title: cherry pineapple cobbler
directions: In a 9 x 13 1/2-inch pan.
Spray with Pam.
Spread pineapple (undrained), then spread cherry pie filling over pineapple. Sprinkle cake mix over mixture in pan.
Sprinkle pecans on top of cake mix.
Melt margarine and pour over top of cake evenly.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.
Do not overcook.
May be served cold or warm with ice cream.

title: pommes lyonnaise
directions: Brush base and sides of a large casserole dish with some of the butter.
Make 3 layers, each using some of the following:
potato slices (overlapping), spots of butter, onion, cheese, salt and pepper and the cream, in this order.
Cover with a lid or buttered greaseproof paper/foil.
Bake at 190°C for 1 1/2 hours.
Dish should be bubbling.
Pierce potatoes at top.
Transfer to grill for 5 minutes to brown cheese at top.

title: hawaiian chicken
directions: Brown chicken, remove and sprinkle with salt and pepper. Drain pineapple and reserve juice.
Cook onion for 3 minutes in drippings.
Add broth, pineapple juice and lemon juice. Mix soy sauce, cornstarch and mustard; add to hot liquid, stirring until clear and thickened.
Add chicken.
Cover and simmer for 20 minutes with rice, green pepper, pineapple and water.

title: red beans and rice
directions: Rinse kidney beans twice.
Discard any that look bad.
Put beans in a big heavy pot, at least three-quart size (four-quart is better.)Add water, ham and sausage.
Set uncovered on a burner at medium heat.
While the beans are soaking and warming, chop and add scallions, green pepper, celery and onions.
Then add thyme and bay leaves. When the mixture boils, reduce heat and cover. Stir every 20-30 minutes for three hours.
Then, with a wooden spoon, mash about one-fourth of the beams against the side of the pot.
If they don't mash easily, try again after half an hour. Forty minutes after mashing the beans, taste and season with cayenne pepper or tabasco sauce.
(Don't use too much; this is supposed to be delicious but subtly flavored.)
Cook for another half an hour while preparing white rice. Ladle beans and sauce over rice and serve.
6 servings.

title: tomato pie
directions: Mix
mayonnaise and cheese together.
Line pie pan with biscuits. Slice 4 or more tomatoes over biscuits.
Saute green pepper
and
onion; sprinkle over tomatoes.
Spread cheese and mayonnaise over top. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes. Serves 6.

title: hickory nut cake
directions: Beat the eggs separately.
Mix the butter and sugar together; add egg yolks, then milk, flour, whites of eggs, cream of tartar and soda and lastly, fruit.

title: 4 layer plain cake
directions: Cream sugar, shortening and eggs.
Add flour and milk alternating.
Mix well and stir in vanilla.
Bake in 4 round 8-inch cake pans at 350 degrees for 30-35 minutes.

title: spinach and strawberries
directions: Prepare salad dressing according to package using balsamic vinegar and olive oil.
Wash, trim and cut spinach into thin strips.
Slice strawberries.
Toss all ingredients together and serve.

title: tuna salad
directions: Mix well. Spread on refrigerator wheat bread. Top with sprinkle of paprika.

title: my kid's favorite chocolate chip cookies
directions: *Omit baking soda and salt if using self-rising flour.

title: cheese crunch
directions: Mix all ingredients together. Roll into small balls and bake at 350° for 10 to 15 minutes.

title: maw maw's apple crunch
directions: Arrange apples in buttered 8 or 9-inch square baking dish. Rub remaining ingredients into crumbs.
Pack down on top of apples.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes or until apples are tender. Serve warm.

title: orange-apricot salad
directions: Drain apricots reserving juice.
Puree in blender.
Add water to juice to make 1 1/2 cups.
Boil.
Stir in jello until dissolved.
Add orange juice and apricots.
Place in mold to set. Takes 3 hours.

title: spaghetti salad
directions: Cook spaghetti, let cool.
Cut up vegetables.
Mix all the ingredients together.

title: banana salad
directions: Cook first four ingredients in double boiler until thick. Serve warm over bananas; sprinkle nuts on top.
It should be made just before eating.
It is served at a famous smorgasbord on the Gulf.

title: chocolate zucchini cake
directions: Cream together the first 4 ingredients.
Add the remaining ingredients; mix well (about 2 minutes with hand mixer).
Pour into greased and floured 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake for 40 to 45 minutes at 350°.
Frost with your favorite frosting.

title: salmon patties
directions: Flake salmon and remove all skin or bones.
Add bread crumbs, cornmeal and eggs; mix well.
Make in patties and fry until brown on both sides.
Sprinkle with pepper, if desired.

title: fri-chik casserole
directions: Cut chicken into bite size pieces.
Cook rice according to package directions.
Mix all ingredients; place in casserole dish and sprinkle with paprika.
Bake 45 minutes to 1 hour at 350°. Serves 8 to 10.

title: fisherman's light fillets
directions: In large skillet, heat lite Italian dressing and cook green pepper and onion over medium heat, stirring occasionally, 5 minutes or until tender.
Add fish and tomato, then simmer covered 10 minutes or until fish flakes.
Serve over hot rice.
Makes about 4 servings.

title: lo-cal tuna salad
directions: Cook and drain macaroni.
Mix all ingredients.
Serve with tomato wedges and/or lettuce.

title: winter root vegetables
directions: Cook vegetables separately in water until tender; drain. Melt butter; stir in remaining ingredients. Combine the vegetables and butter mixture; toss to coat. This has 12 grams carbohydrate.

title: bean dip
directions: Bake 1.
Freeze 1
(thaw and then bake).
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Serve with Doritos, etc.

title: thumbprint cookies
directions: Mix thoroughly the first 4 ingredients.
Sift and stir in flour and salt.
Roll into 1-inch balls; dip in slightly beaten egg white and roll in finely chopped nuts (3/4 cup).
Place 1-inch apart on ungreased cookie sheet.
Press thumb in center of each.
Bake at 375° for 10 to 12 minutes.
Cool.
Fill centers with candied fruit, jelly or tinted confectioners sugar icing. Makes about 2 dozen (1 1/2-inch) cookies.

title: chocolate chip cookies
directions: Cream together butter and sugars.
Add vanilla.
Mix in dry instant pudding.
Add eggs.
Gradually mix in baking soda and flour.
Stir in chocolate chips and nuts.
Drop by teaspoonfuls on an ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 375° for 8 to 10 minutes. Makes 4 dozen.

title: e-z lasagne
directions: In large saucepan, blend sauce mix, tomato sauce, water and olives.
Bring to boil on medium-high, then cover and simmer about 20 minutes.
Brown ground beef; drain and add to sauce.
Heat oven to 350°.
In large baking pan (about 12 x 16-inch, with nonstick finish), pour thin layer of meat sauce.
Next, layer lasagne noodles.

Spread layer of cottage cheese on noodles, then a good layer of Mozzarella and finally, another layer of meat sauce. Repeat these layers until pan is full, then cover tightly with foil and bake for about one hour.
Remove from oven and (preferably), let sit for 30 minutes.
(Of course, this is absolutely best the next day, covered with Parmesan!)

title: m&m cookies
directions: Bake at 375° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: savory party crunch
directions: Melt margarine in 9 x 13-inch pan in oven.
Add Parmesan cheese, Worcestershire sauce and salt.
Stir.
Add cereal, pretzels and peanuts.
Stir.
Bake 20 minutes in 325° oven.
Stir at least once while baking.
Stir while it is cooling so it won't stick. Store in airtight container.

title: "better than sex" cake
directions: Bake cake according to package directions.
As soon as it is done, punch holes in it with a wooden spoon handle.
While hot, drizzle with milk and ice cream topping, mixed.
Sprinkle a little of Heath bar on top.
After cake cools, spread with Cool Whip and sprinkle rest of the Heath bar on top.
Best when made a day before needed.
Store in refrigerator.

title: barbecued beans
directions: Fry meat and onion.
Add other ingredients.
Combine in casserole.
Bake at 350° until bubbly, about 30 minutes.

title: irish soda bread
directions: Place all ingredients in a large bowl and mix with wooden spoon.
Mix just until blended.
Do not overbeat.
Bake in a 10-inch tube pan which has been greased and bake at 350° for about 35 minutes.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Day before serving:
Grease 2 (9 x 5-inch) loaf pans.
In large bowl with fork, mix flour with next 7 ingredients using a fork.
Add remaining ingredients and mix until blended.
Turn batter into pans.
Bake 1 hour at 350° or until toothpick comes out clean.
Cool on wire racks for 10 minutes.
Remove and cool completely.
Wrap and store at room temperature until time to serve.

title: lasagna
directions: Brown meats and chopped onion.
Add tomato products and seasonings.
Simmer gently for 1 hour.
Cook noodles.
Place 3 cooked noodles on bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan.
Now alternately layer: sauce, each cheese, noodles, etc.
When all layered, a little tomato juice may be desired to liquify.
Bake in 350° oven for 45 to 60 minutes.

title: pretzel salad
directions: Melt oleo in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Add pretzels, mixing well. Bake 8 to 10 minutes at 350°.
Cool.
Mix the cream cheese and xx sugar.
Fold in Cool Whip.
Spread over cooled, baked pretzels. Add Jell-O and 2 cups hot water until dissolved completely.
Add frozen strawberries and let partially jell, then pour over cream cheese mixture and let completely jell.

title: brunswick stew
directions: Mix all ingredients in a large pot; let come to a slow boil, stirring often.
If you are not careful, it will stick.
After it comes to a boil, turn to simmer for about 10 to 15 minutes.

title: strawberry pie
directions: Mix sugar and cornstarch in 1 cup water and heat to boil. Make thick enough to boil.
Fill a prebaked pie crust half full with strawberries.
Pour sauce over them. Add remaining berries and pour rest of sauce.

title: easy potato soup
directions: Combine first four ingredients in a Dutch oven and bring to a boil.
Cover, reduce heat and simmer for 30 minutes.
Stir in soups and milk.
Heat thoroughly.
Garnish with shredded Cheddar cheese or sprinkle with bacon bits.

title: strawberry pretzel salad
directions: Combine jello in 1/2 amount of water usually called for. Bring to boil and dissolve jello and add fruit.
It will thicken, cool slightly and pour over the Cool Whip layer when starting to gel.
Refrigerate.

title: low calorie chili
directions: In a saucepan over medium heat, saute celery, onion, green pepper, meat and garlic in oil until brown.
Stir in beans, tomatoes, salt and chili powder.
Simmer for 40 to 45 minutes.

title: chocolate nut cake
directions: Mix well and bake in two layers at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: blonde brownies
directions: Sift the flour, soda, baking powder and salt.
Melt the brown sugar and margarine over low heat.
Blend in the eggs and vanilla. Add flour mix gradually.
Mix well and spread in a 13 x 9-inch pan. Sprinkle with the chocolate chips and pecans.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Cool in pan and cut in squares.

title: zero calorie salad dressing
directions: Combine ingredients in a jar with tight fitting lid.
Shake well before using.
Refrigerate unused portions.

title: halston's gelatin surprise
directions: Spray the ice cube trays with nonstick cooking spray.
Follow box directions for mixing jello.
Place 1 gummy worm in each ice cube section.
Pour gelatin mixture over gummy worms.
Refrigerate for 1 hour or until firm.
Run knife around edge of each square. Remove from trays.

title: this and that cake
directions: Mix cake mix as directed; pour into pan.
Mix brown sugar, coconut and nuts.
Sprinkle over cake mix.
Bake as directed.
In saucepan mix margarine, evaporated milk and sugar.
Boil until sugar dissolves.
Pour over cake.

title: layered reuben salad
directions: In a mixing bowl, combine cabbage, lettuce, 1/4 cup Thousand Island dressing and caraway seed.
In the bottom of a medium bowl or an 8 x 8 x 2-inch dish, place half of the cabbage mixture. Layer in the following order:
half of the corned beef, remaining cabbage mixture, remaining corned beef, hard-cooked egg slices and cheese. Spread remaining Thousand Island salad dressing evenly over top of salad.
Cover tightly with clear plastic wrap. Chill up to 24 hours.
Before serving, top with crushed Melba toast. Makes 4 main dish servings.

title: heavenly breakfast casserole
directions: Mix all together and sprinkle cheese on top.
Use a 9 x 13- inch pan or slightly smaller.
Cover and refrigerate overnight. Bake for 45 to 55 minutes at 350°.
Serve immediately.
Serves 10 people.
Can half recipe.

title: apple coffee cake
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Spray rectangular pan (13 x 9 x 2-inch) with Pam.
Mix pie filling and cinnamon; reserve.
Beat flour, granulated sugar, milk, softened margarine, baking powder, salt and eggs in a large bowl on low speed, scraping bowl constantly for 30 seconds.
Beat on medium speed, scraping bowl frequently for 2 minutes.
Pour half of the batter (about 2 cups) into pan. Spoon half of the pie filling mixture (about 1 cup) over batter in pan.
Repeat with remaining batter and pie filling mixture. Sprinkle brown sugar and nuts over pie filling mixture.
Drizzle with melted margarine.
Bake until wooden pick inserted in center comes out clean, 45 to 55 minutes.
Serve warm.
Yields 12 to 16 servings.

title: beef burgundy
directions: Cut tops off of bell peppers; remove core and seeds.
Wash peppers.
Remove and discard the stems from pepper tops and chop the tops.

title: barbecue chicken or pork chops
directions: Sprinkle pork or chicken with salt and pepper to taste.
Bake in covered dish at 350° until tender and juices run clear. Combine other ingredients until well blended.
Pour over pork chops or chicken and continue to bake covered at 350° for 30 more minutes.

title: buffalo chip cookies
directions: Cream oleo and shortening.
Add the sugars, eggs and vanilla. After sifting the flour and baking powder, add to mixture.
After mixing well, add the rest of the ingredients; mix well.
Use 1/4 cup or an ice cream scoop per cookie.
Put on ungreased cookie sheet; 6 to a sheet.
Cook for about 15 minutes at 350°.
Let cool on cookie sheet for 15 minutes to prevent breakage.

title: cream cheese pound cake
directions: Cream margarine, sugar and cream cheese until light and fluffy.
Add dash of salt and vanilla.
Beat well.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each addition.
Stir in flour. Spoon mixture into greased 10-inch tube pan.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour and 30 minutes.
Serves 20 to 25.

title: 9 minute fresh fruit pie
directions: In covered blender, blend 1 cup fruit at high speed 30 seconds.
In 2-quart pan, mix cornstarch and water until smooth. Add mashed fruit, syrup and lemon juice.
Stirring constantly, bring to boil over medium heat and boil 1 minute.
Turn into bowl; cover surface with waxed paper.
Cool 1 hour.
Fold in remaining fruit.
Spread cream onto bottom and sides of pie crust.
Fill with fruit mixture.
Chill 3 hours or until set.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: swedish "osta kaka"
directions: Stir 1 cake Rennet, 2 cups flour and 2 eggs into 2 cups milk. Add to 3 gallons lukewarm milk.
Continue stirring until the milk starts to curdle, with the milk held constantly at lukewarm temperature.
Then let stand for 20 minutes, still lukewarm.

title: fresh apple salad
directions: Mix in large bowl and chill.

title: tex-mex broccoli
directions: In a large saucepan, combine milk and flour and whisk over medium heat until no lumps remain (about 1 minute).
Stir in mustard, salt, black pepper and cayenne.
Cook, stirring frequently, until lightly thickened and no floury taste remains (about 4 minutes).
Stir in the Pepper Jack cheese and remove from heat.
Meanwhile, bring a large pot of water to boil.
Add broccoli and cook until crisp-tender (about 3 minutes).
Drain well and transfer to a serving dish.
Pour in cheese sauce and toss to coat well.
Makes 4 servings.

title: no bake cheese cake
directions: In spring-form pan, line bottom and sides with ladyfingers. Trim bottom of ladyfingers that stand around the sides.
Use tips to fill in spaces on bottom.
Follow directions on no bake cheese cake and add cream cheese (soften in microwave).
Refrigerate for 1 hour.
Remove and add fruit topping when ready to serve.

title: apple-cranberry crisp
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Place apple pie filling in lightly greased 9-inch square baking dish.
Wash cranberries and remove stems. Drain well.
Chop coarsely.
Stir into pie filling.

title: butter ball cookies
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add remaining ingredients and mix well.
Let stand 1/2 hour, then form into balls in the palm of your hand.
Place on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake 10 minutes at 350°.
While still warm, roll in powdered sugar.
Wonderful Christmas cookies.

title: applesauce fig spice bars
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease 9 x 13-inch pan.
Combine butter, brown sugar and egg; beat until fluffy.
Stir in orange peel. Combine flour, pumpkin spice, baking soda and salt; blend into butter mixture alternately with applesauce.
Stir in figs and walnuts.
Spread into greased pan.
Bake for 20 to 25 minutes or until golden brown.
Cool 5 minutes.
Combine powdered sugar, milk and vanilla; mix well.
Spread over warm uncut bars.
Cool completely before cutting.
Yields 2 dozen.

title: pretzel salad
directions: Mix pretzels, 3 tablespoons sugar and oleo.
Press into 9 x 12-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.
Let cool.

title: banana split
directions: Press into a 10 x 3-inch pan graham cracker crumbs, sugar, butter after mixing well.
Mix eggs, 2 sticks butter and confectioners sugar for 20 minutes and spread on crust.
Spread pineapple on mixture.
Then slice bananas on top of pineapple. Spread Cool Whip on top of bananas and top with crushed nuts.

title: chili rellenos
directions: Clean and de-seed chilies without tearing each chili.
Stuff chili by inserting a sliver of cheese.
Beat eggs.
With a little oil in a frypan, put in a large spoonful of eggs and spread out enough to be able to place stuffed chili in center.
As it cooks, wrap egg around chili, turning over to seal.
Microwave with enchilada sauce.

title: "quick drop" doughnuts
directions: Mix dry ingredients.
Beat eggs, milk and Crisco together. Stir into dry ingredients.
Blend well.
Drop by teaspoonfuls into hot oil in deep fryer.
Cook until golden brown.
Drain on paper towel lined cookie tray or dish.
Dust with granulated sugar, confectioners sugar or a mix of cinnamon and sugar.
Makes 42 to 48 doughnut holes.

title: creamy lemon pie
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
In medium bowl, beat egg yolks with Eagle Brand milk, lemon juice and food coloring.
Pour into a baked pie shell.
Bake 30 minutes.
Cool.
Chill.
Spread with whipped cream.

title: cornbread salad
directions: Bake cornbread according to directions.
Cool in pan and crumble.
Mix radishes, green pepper, onions and tomatoes with crumbled cornbread.
Stir in Miracle Whip, mustard and cucumber dressing. Chill.

title: toasted peanut butter sandwiches
directions: Mix the peanut butter and honey together.
Spread mixture on four slices of bread.
Top with the remaining slices to make sandwiches.
Mix the eggs and the milk together.
Melt the margarine in a frying pan over medium heat.
Dip each sandwich in the egg mixture and place in frying pan.
Brown the sandwiches on both sides.

title: pie crust mix
directions: Mix the flour and salt.
Cut in Crisco thoroughly and finely. Add remaining ingredients; mix well.
Refrigerate and use as needed.
Makes 5 crusts.
Crusts freeze well.

title: delicious and light artichoke dip(from american heart association)
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In an ovenproof dish, combine artichokes, chilies, mayonnaise and all but 2 tablespoons of the Parmesan cheese.
Mix well.
Sprinkle remaining cheese on top and bake about 50 minutes or until top is lightly browned.
Serve with fat free cracker or tortilla chips.

title: pita chips with sesame
directions: Slice bread into triangles. Grind sesame in mill. Sprinkle over triangles.
Bake 15 minutes until crisp and light in 325° oven.

title: chocolate pecan pies
directions: Mix together first 5 ingredients.
Add pecans.
Pour into 2 unbaked deep dish pie crusts.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 50 minutes.

title: rice with black beans
directions: Heat oil in large skillet on medium high heat.
Add onion and garlic; cook until tender, but not browned.
Stir in tomatoes, beans, water and oregano.
Bring to boil.

title: easy chicken casserole
directions: Remove papers from tamales; slice in halves lengthwise.
Cut up chicken meat.
Place tamales, chicken, rice, onion and cheese in separate layers in casserole.
Combine soup, tomato soup and chili powder.
Pour over top.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: sausage casserole
directions: Brown sausage and drain.
Beat eggs.
Press out package of crescent rolls in pan.
Blend sausage, eggs and cheese; spread out over rolls in pan.
Press other package of crescent rolls over that.
Baste with butter.
Bake at 375° for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: super bowl beer and cheddar soup
directions: Saute vegetables in oil until golden.
Add to boiling soup stock and simmer 45 minutes.
Dredge cheese in flour and add to stock, stirring constantly until thickened.
Add all other ingredients, stirring until hot and garnish with parsley.
You may add sliced cooked sausage, if desired.
Serve with bagels and beer for a whole meal.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Layer chicken in a 9 x 14-inch casserole dish.
Mix 2 cups broth with chicken soup.
Combine all ingredients
except cheese; pour over chicken.
Sprinkle with cheese.
Top with margarine and cracker crumbs.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes (45 minutes if it has been refrigerated).

title: banana wheat bread
directions: In large bowl blend all ingredients at low speed; beat 3 minutes at medium speed.
Pour into prepared pan (greased and floured loaf or tube pan).
Makes 3 mini loaves.
Bake at 325° for 50 to 75 minutes, depending on pan or until toothpick inserted comes out clean.
Remove from pan immediately.

title: peanut butter crisps
directions: Mix with hands.
Roll into little balls; place on ungreased cookie sheet.
Press with fork.
Bake for about 10 minutes at 375°.

title: graham cracker toffee
directions: Spray jelly roll pan with Pam. Lay crackers in pan, completely covering pan. Boil butter and sugar for 2 minutes. Add vanilla. Pour over nuts and crackers. Bake at 350° for 10 minutes. (Watch closely.) While still hot, sprinkle chocolate chips over top. When melted, spread into thin covering.

title: hamburger casserole
directions: Brown onion and pepper in butter.
Add beef and cook until brown.
Add remaining ingredients, except cheese.
Mix and put half in casserole.
Add cheese.
Add rest of mix and top with cheese.
Cover and bake for 45 minutes.

title: million dollar pie
directions: Mix altogether and pour into a graham cracker crust.
Chill for 2 hours.

title: texas caviar
directions: Mix all ingredients in large bowl suitable for dipping.
Serve with tortilla chips as an appetizer.
Great with Mexican food!

title: filled jumbo drops
directions: Mix thoroughly shortening, brown sugar, eggs. stir water, vanilla. Sift together and stir in flour, soda, salt and cinnamon. Drop with teaspoon onto ungreased baking sheet.
Place 1/2 tsp filling on dough, cover with 1/2 tsp dough.
Bake 10-12 minutes. Makes 5 - 6 dozen.

title: shrimp and chive tarts
directions: Pat shrimp dry.
Chop shrimp and combine with mayonnaise, minced chives, lemon juice, mustard and pepper to taste.
Mound into tartlet shells.
Makes 2 dozen.

title: tropic isle brownies
directions: Heat oven to 350°. Grease baking pan, 13 x 9 x 2-inch.
Mix all ingredients except confectioners sugar. Spread in pan. Bake 35 minutes. Cool. Sprinkle sugar over top. Cut into bars, 2 x 1-inch. Makes 4 dozen cookies.

title: lemon meringue pie
directions: Mix egg yolks, lemon juice and milk and pour into prepared graham cracker crust.
Beat egg whites and sugar until stiff peaks form and spread over lemon mixture in pie crust; and bake in 350 degree oven until meringue is light brown.
Cool, and serve.

title: shrimp dip
directions: Soften cream cheese and blend all ingredients well. Refrigerate for several hours.
Best served with Town House or wheat crackers.
Can substitute salmon or crab.

title: chili
directions: Brown ground beef or turkey and drain.
Add other ingredients. Add spices to taste and simmer on very low heat.
The longer you cook it the better.

title: pumpkin pound cake
directions: Mix each ingredient separate and beat well.
Bake in tube pan at 350° for 1 hour and 20 minutes.

title: quick and easy salmon patties
directions: Drain salmon; set aside 3 tablespoons of the liquid.
Mix salmon, egg and the onion until sticky.
Stir in flour.
Add baking powder to the 3 tablespoons of juice; stir until it foams up.
Add salmon mixture.
Form into small patties and fry until golden brown, about 2 1/2 minutes each.

title: corn fritters
directions: Carefully watch
the
amount of flour added, that it is not too
stiff.
Add
1/4-inch oil in frypan.
Add more oil as needed. Combine ingredients; drop by tablespoon into hot oil.

title: peanut butter cups
directions: Pat into 9 x 13-inch pan. Melt 2 cups milk chocolate chips and frost over top. When chocolate has set, cut into squares.

title: sweet and sour carrots
directions: Cook carrots; drain and cool.
Add green peppers and onions; set aside.
Combine remaining ingredients in saucepan and cook over low heat until sugar is dissolved.
Pour over carrots and refrigerate for 1 day.
Delicious hot or cold.

title: choc-o-bit cookies
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Cream shortening, sugar, vanilla, water and egg until light and fluffy.
Mix flour, soda and salt.
Blend into creamed mixture.
Stir in nuts and choc-o-bits.

title: barbecue ribs
directions: Layer ribs in pan.
Cover with foil.
Bake at 300° for 3 hours.
Take out of oven and drain juice from pan.
Use Open Pit barbecue sauce and add brown sugar.
Pour over ribs.
Cook 1 hour longer.
Use by itself or add Texas Barbecue Sauce.

title: russian tea
directions: Mix all ingredients together in a sealed container.
Spoon 2 to 3 teaspoons of mixture into a cup of boiling water.
Sweeten to taste.
Makes 1 serving.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Make your favorite dressing, using canned broth to moisten (leave very moist).
Put dressing in baking dish.
Place boned chicken breast on top of dressing.
Pour soup over chicken and dressing and bake until golden brown.
This dish may be enlarged for groups.
You may substitute turkey for chicken.

title: cheese cake
directions: Roll crackers and mix with butter.
Bake for 5 minutes. Dissolve Jell-O in hot water and let cool.
Add sugar and mix with cream cheese and vanilla.
Let chill in refrigerator for 20 minutes.
Whip milk until stiff and add Jell-O and cream, folding in cheese.
Pour to cool.
Top with cherry filling or strawberry.

title: white rice browned
directions: Melt butter in large frying pan; add rice.
Cook over very slow fire, stirring often, until rice is golden brown.
Place in 2-quart casserole.
Sprinkle on seasonings.
When ready to bake, add consomme, water and nuts.
Mix gently.
Cover and bake at 300° for 1 hour and 15 minutes.
Do not stir.
Serves 10.

title: orange cookies
directions: Cream Crisco and sugar.
Add eggs and salt.
Add orange juice and grated rind of orange.
Alternate liquid with flour, baking powder and soda.
Bake on greased sheet at 350°.

title: fourth of july barbecued chicken
directions: In saucepan, cook onion and garlic in oil until tender.
Stir in tomato paste, water, brown sugar, vinegar, Worcestershire sauce, 2 teaspoons salt, 1/4 teaspoon pepper and mustard. Simmer, uncovered, for 20 minutes.
Sauce may now be refrigerated until ready to use.

title: popcorn balls
directions: Butter a mixing bowl and pour in popped popcorn.
Mix sugar, water, corn syrup, vinegar, vanilla and salt.
Heat to boiling and stir until sugar melts.
Cook slowly to hard boil stage.
Remove from heat.
Immediately but slowly pour in fine stream over popcorn, mixing as you do this.
After fully coated, put butter on hands and mold into balls.

title: deedee's chocolate chess pie
directions: Mix dry ingredients together.
Mix wet ingredients together. Combine and pour into pie shell.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes. Great topped with homemade whipped cream or ice cream.
(Double ingredients.
Make two pies; freeze one.)

title: hershey bar cake
directions: Melt
candy
bars.
Cream oleo with sugar; add eggs one at a time, and beat well.
Add melted candy to creamed mixture and mix well.
Add
buttermilk
alternately with sifted flour and soda. Add
Hershey syrup, vanilla, salt and pecans.
Bake at 350° for 1 1/2
hours
or
until
done.
Can
be
baked in greased and floured Bundt pan.

title: potato cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add eggs, one at a time.
Add mashed potatoes to egg mixture.
Add cocoa to flour and baking powder. Add cinnamon, allspice and nutmeg, then combine dry ingredients with egg mixture.
Bake in tube pan at 350° until done or about an hour.
Test for doneness.

title: filled cookies
directions: Cream sugar and shortening together; add milk, then egg.
Mix well.
Put flour, soda and cream of tartar into flour sifter and sift into the batter.
Then mix or beat until all is well mixed. Chill the dough; overnight is best, but for a few hours at least. Then roll it thin, cut with floured cookie cutter and place on greased cookie sheet.

title: homemade noodles
directions: Mix egg with salt and cold water.
Gradually add enough flour to make a very still dough.
(At first stir in flour with fork then work in flour with hands.)
Knead dough until smooth, round up into ball.
Cover with cloth and let rest 15 minutes.
Roll out dough on floured cloth until very thin.
Let stand 30 minutes to dry slightly.
Roll up and slice with a sharp knife.
Drop noodles into boiling broth or water; cook until tender.

title: tater tot casserole
directions: Mix hamburger with onion.
Pour into bottom of casserole dish. Add soup over meat mixture.
Add slices of cheese on top, then add Tater Tots on top and bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: cabbage casserole
directions: Melt butter.
Add corn flakes.
Spread 1/2 cup of this mixture in a large casserole dish.
Top with shredded cabbage.
Pack down. Top with chopped onion.
Top with grated cheese.
Mix mayo and milk and soup.
Pour over casserole.
Top with remaining corn flake mixture.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: pistachio cake
directions: Combine all ingredients and mix well.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes in greased and floured pan.
Sprinkle with powdered sugar.

title: scented decoration
directions: Mix spices together and add to applesauce.
Stir until thoroughly mixed.
Roll out to 1/4-inch thickness.
Cut with cookie cutters.
Punch hole with straw to hang.
Allow to dry 4 to 5 days.

title: sweet potato surprise
directions: Put sweet potatoes in greased baking dish.
In pan, cook brown sugar, juice from apricots and cornstarch until thickened.
Add apricots, butter, pecan halves, orange peel, cinnamon and salt. Pour over sweet potatoes.
Bake, uncovered, at 375° for 25 minutes.

title: garlic-parmesan rolls
directions: Cut dough into 16 pieces; shape into balls.
Place on a floured surface, cover and let rise in a warm place for 10 minutes.

title: cheese ball
directions: Cream the softened cream cheese.
Add grated Cheddar cheese; mix until well blended.
Add other ingredients; mix well.
Shape into small ball.
Sprinkle ball with paprika.
Wrap and chill for 24 hours.
Garnish with olives.
Serve with crackers.

title: mushroom quiche
directions: Layer first 4 ingredients.
Beat eggs; add milk, salt and pepper.
Pour over layers.
Bake 15 minutes at 425°; turn to 350° and bake 30 minutes more.
Serves 6.

title: ida's baked beans
directions: Mix and simmer.
Great, especially at barbecues!

title: cheese cakes
directions: Mix crumbs, butter and sugar. Press into 9-inch pan.
Bake at 325° for 10 minutes.

title: chicken dijon
directions: In 10-inch skillet, over medium-high heat, in 1 tablespoon hot margarine, cook chicken 10 minutes or until browned on both sides. Remove; set aside.
Reduce heat to medium.
In same skillet, in remaining 1 tablespoon hot margarine, cook onion until tender, stirring often.
Stir in soup, apple juice, parsley and mustard. Heat to boiling.
Return chicken to skillet.
Reduce heat to low. Cover; cook 5 minutes or until chicken is no longer pink, stirring occasionally.
Serve with noodles.
Garnish with parsley and apples, if desired.
Makes 4 servings.

title: tater tot casserole
directions: Brown meat; add salt.
Put in buttered casserole dish.
Layer remaining ingredients in order given, mixing soup with liquid drained from beans.

title: curry divan chicken
directions: Cook broccoli according to package directions until almost tender.
Put in a greased 2-quart baking dish.
Place chicken on top.
Mix cream of chicken soup, mayonnaise, milk, cheese, lemon juice and curry powder and pour over chicken.
Sprinkle a mixture of butter and bread crumbs over sauce.
Bake near center of 350° oven 20 to 30 minutes or until thoroughly heated.
Decorate with pimento strips.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: lemon tarts
directions: Put sugar and butter in top of double boiler.
Add the beaten eggs and lemon juice.
Keep the water boiling.
Stir often to keep it from framing around the pan.
Cook until thick.
Put filling in baked tart shells.

title: lebanese stuffed grape leaves(warak inib)
directions: Wash rice & squeeze out excess water.
Place in large mixing bowl. Add chopped meat, salt, pepper, cumin & garlic powder.
In a pan, melt butter. Lightly brown the pine nuts (stirring so it will not burn). Add to rice mixture. Mix well.
Spread grape leaves flat with stem facing you & smooth sides down.
Place approx. 1 tsp. of rice mixture width-wise across the grape leaf (more or less according to leaf size).
Roll leaf away from you after firming mixture into a roll and tuck in each side of grape leaf. Continue to roll.
Squeeze rolled grape leaf gently to help firm filling and distribute evenly.
Line a large 6 qt. stainless steel pot with flat grape leaves.
Layer the rolled leaves in alternate directions for easy layer to facilitate even cooking.
Fill pot with rolled leaves, add whole green onion & mint leaves.
Chopped garlic on top.
Cover with water and a heavy dinner plate.
Bring to a boil and lower heat to medium.
Simmer for 20 mins.
Add lemon juice & cook for additional 15 mins.

title: chocolate pound cake
directions: Cream shortening, margarine and sugar.
Sift flour, cocoa, salt and baking powder together.
Add eggs, one at a time.
Add milk and dry
mixture alternately, beating thoroughly.
Bake at 350° until done, about 1 hour and 15 to 30 minutes.

title: blueberry banana bread
directions: Wash and thoroughly drain blueberries; toss with 2 tablespoons flour.
Sift together remaining flour, baking powder, soda and salt.
Cream butter or margarine; gradually beat in sugar until light and fluffy.
Beat in eggs, one at a time.
Add flour mixture and bananas alternately in three parts.
Stir in blueberries and nuts.
Spoon into greased 10 x 6 x 3-inch loaf pan.
Bake at 350° for about 50 to 60 minutes or until done.
Makes 1 loaf.

title: blintz souffle
directions: Grease a 9-inch deep baking dish.
Put frozen blitzes on bottom.
Put ingredients in blender and blend until creamy.
Pour over blitzes.
Bake at 375° for first 15 minutes, then reduce heat to 350°.
Continue baking 35 to 45 minutes or until fluffy and brown.

title: cabbage rolls
directions: Parboil cabbage leaves in water (enough to cover).
Drain. Moisten crumbs with the water and combine with meat, half the onion, salt and pepper.
Shape into 6 small rolls.
Wrap each in a cabbage leaf.
Melt butter in frying pan.
Add cabbage rolls, rest of onion, green pepper, paprika and tomatoes.
Cover and simmer for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: cookie press cream cheese cookies
directions: Mix the cream cheese, butter and sugar.
Add egg yolks, vanilla and flour; mix well.
Put in cookie press.
Press out cookies on ungreased pan.
Bake at 425° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: mom's holiday salad
directions: Soften cream cheese and Cool Whip.
Put cream cheese in mixer and beat.
Add Cool Whip and everything else.
Mix and chill.

title: chicken crunch(preparation time: 15 minutes)
directions: In a shallow dish, combine 1/3 can of soup and 1/4 cup of milk.
On waxed paper, lightly coat chicken with flour, then dip into soup mixture.
On another piece of waxed paper, coat chicken with stuffing crumbs.
Arrange chicken on a baking sheet; drizzle with margarine.
Bake at 400° for 20 minutes or until chicken is done.
Serves 4.

title: german kuchen
directions: Stir yeast into warm water.
Mix in 1 cup flour.
Set in warm place until bubbly (30 minutes).
In a large bowl, mix butter, sugar and flavorings until fluffy.
Beat in eggs, then add yeast mixture; blend in rest of flour.
Pour into a greased 10-inch tube pan.
Let rise until batter is 1/4-inch from top.
Bake at 375° for 50 to 60 minutes.

title: slush punch
directions: (Use the color Kool-Aid you wish your punch to be. You may add food coloring, if needed.)

title: apple pan walnut cake(this is a pillsbury bake-off recipe from 1966.)
directions: Spread pie filling in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Combine flour, sugar, soda and salt.
Sprinkle over the pie filling. In a mixing bowl, combine the eggs, vanilla, oil and 1/2 cup nuts; mix well.
Pour over the ingredients in pan and stir only until evenly blended. Smooth batter in pan.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 50 minutes or until cake springs back when lightly touched.
Make a topping and pour over the cake while hot.

title: cheese ball
directions: Combine ingredients.
Roll in chopped pecans or walnuts. This can be frozen. Thaw in refrigerator.

title: english pea casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients well and top with more cracker crumbs. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: pizza casserole
directions: Brown, drain and fix meat into casserole.
Pour pizza sauce on top.
Add shredded cheese.
Mix Bisquick, milk and eggs to a thin batter.
Pour over top and bake for 1 hour or until done.

title: jam cake
directions: Mix sugar, Crisco, eggs, jam, spices, soda, vanilla and cocoa together.
Add flour and buttermilk, alternately.
Add nuts last. Bake at 350° in 3 (8-inch) pans or 2 (9-inch) pans.

title: frozen salad
directions: Cream softened cheese with sugar.
Add remaining ingredients. Freeze.
Set out just before serving.

title: millie's mini cheese cakes
directions: Put cupcake papers in muffin tins.
Place 1 vanilla cookie in each.
Mix cream cheese and rest of ingredients until smooth.
Pour over wafers filling 3/4 full.
Bake at 325° for 25 minutes.
Remove from pan when cool.
Chill.
Top with fruit, preserves, nuts or chocolate.
Be creative!

title: clam casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Bake at 325° for about 50 minutes.
Sprinkle with paprika.

title: fannie's nutty fruit cake
directions: Coat fruits and nuts with the flour; mix well.
Set aside. Beat eggs and sugar together until smooth.
Mix fruits and nuts with eggs and sugar.
Pack with hands into 2 loaf pans.
Mixture will be very thick.

title: caramel corn
directions: Put popcorn in baking pan.
Remove any unpopped kernels. Measure brown sugar, butter, corn syrup and salt into a 1 1/2-quart saucepan.
Put pan on burner on medium heat.
Stir until melted and continue cooking until mixture starts boiling.
Cook for 5 minutes.
Remove from heat.
Stir in baking soda and vanilla.
Pour mixture over popcorn and coat all kernels.

title: chocolate-oatmeal cookies
directions: Mix sugar, cocoa, milk and margarine.
Heat to boiling; let boil 2 minutes.
After mixture reaches boiling, remove and cool. Beat and add vanilla, oats and peanut butter.
Drop by spoonfuls on waxed paper.

title: bread dough
directions: Mix yeast and water thoroughly.
Add salt, sugar and eggs, one at a time.
Stir in shortening until completely melted.
Add flour, one cup at a time.
When all mixed, let rise for 1 hour. Divide evenly into 3 sections.
Will make 3 or 4 loaves of bread.

title: old timey pound cake
directions: Cream butter, Crisco and sugar until creamy.
Add eggs, one at a time; beat well.
Sift flour and baking powder and add alternately with milk and flavoring, ending with flour.

title: homemade banana ice cream
directions: Beat eggs.
Add sugar, vanilla and Milnot.
Beat well.
Stir in mashed bananas.
Pour this into a 4-quart freezer and add whole sweet milk up to fill line.
Freeze.

title: sweet dill pickles
directions: Cut pickles long way into quarters and drain all juice out. Place pickles into jar.
Bring sugar, water and vinegar to boil. Pour over pickles and let set for approximately 2 weeks.

title: baked pork chops
directions: Brown pork chops and place in oven pan.
Pour soup, water and barbecue sauce over chops.
Cover and bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: scalloped corn
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Pour
into a buttered 9 x 13-inch pan. Bake at 425° for 20 to 30 minutes or until golden brown.
Great side dish!

title: shortcake
directions: Sift together the baking powder, flour, salt and sugar.
Cut into shortening.
Add milk and egg.
Bake for 15 to 20 minutes at 400° in a 9 x 13-inch pan.

title: three step strawberry pizza
directions: Combine flour and sugar.
Add melted butter and mix well.
Pat into 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes or until crust is lightly brown.
Cool.

title: lemon-buttered new potatoes
directions: Prepare and cook new potatoes as follows.
Heat 1 inch of salted water (1 teaspoon salt to 1 cup water) to boiling.
Add potatoes; cover and heat to boiling.
Cook 20 to 25 minutes or until tender.
Keep potatoes warm.

title: greek pizza(serves 1)
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Saute onion in pan prepared with nonstick spray until soft.
Add spinach, salt and pepper and cook 5 minutes more.
Add Feta cheese and cook 1 more minute until well mixed.
Place all of spinach mixture on top of pita.
Top with 1/4 to 1/2 cup tomato sauce and sprinkle Mozzarella cheese on top. Bake 5 to 10 minutes until cheese is melted.

title: chinese chicken salad
directions: Chop cabbage and onions.
Crush Ramen noodles.
Add crushed noodles and chopped chicken to cabbage mixture.
Season with garlic powder and Greek seasoning and Accent to taste.
Mix oil, sugar and rice vinegar.
Pour over cabbage mixture.

title: holiday cranberry salad
directions: In a bowl, dissolve jello in water.
Let partially set.
Add remaining ingredients and let set overnight in mold.

title: banana breakfast drink
directions: Combine all ingredients in a blender.
Blend until smooth. Serve at once in chilled glass.

title: chicken breasts and sour cream
directions: Mix flour with sour cream.
Combine with all other ingredients except chicken.
Place chicken in a baking dish and pour the mixture over them.
Bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: sparkling candy cane cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Cut open cookie mix and mix according to package.
Divide dough in half.
Squeeze food coloring in one-half. Stir until dough is evenly tinted.
Dough wil be pink; use more coloring.
Rolling in red sugar will give brighter color.
Form plain dough and red dough into balls about size of mini marshmallows (next step).
Pour sugar crystals into 2 small bowls. Roll tinted dough balls in red sugar crystals.
Roll plain dough in white sugar.
Place balls on wax paper.
Roll balls in sugars one color at a time so your fingers won't have both colors on them and make cookies look messy.
For each cane, use 4 plain balls and 4 red balls, alternating each.
Place red white so edges are touching forming canes.
Flatten slightly with fingers.
Keep sides straight; keep canes 2-inches apart to allow room to spread when baking.
Bake for 5 to 7 minutes.
Cool 1 minute, then remove and cool.

title: caesar salad dressing
directions: Combine Egg Beaters, vinegar, and the next 5 ingredients in a container of an electric blender; top with cover and process 10 seconds.
Combine hot water and bouillon granules, stirring until granules are dissolved.
With blender running, gradually add bouillon mixture and Butter Buds in a slow, steady stream.
Cover and chill thoroughly.
Yields 2 cups.

title: pierogi casserole
directions: Cook lasagna noodles.
Make 10-12 serving of instant mashed potatoes.
Dice onion and saute in margarine.
In casserole dish, layer onions with margarine, then 3 lasagna noodles, then half the mashed potatoes, then half the Cheddar.
Repeat layering, ending with noodles. Cover with foil and bake at 350 degrees for 45 minutes.

title: pumpkin pie(makes two 8-inch pies)
directions: Put sugar, pumpkin, milk, cinnamon, salt and nutmeg in pan. Add butter and cook over low heat until butter is melted.
Beat eggs and add to mixture.
Pour into unbaked pie shells and bake at 400° for 30 minutes.
Can also put coconut in bottom of pie shell before you put mixture in.

title: cool pink salad
directions: Heat pineapple, jello and water.
Allow jello to dissolve. Pour into dish and chill.
Mix Cool Whip and buttermilk.
Combine jello mixture with buttermilk mixture and beat.
Chill.

title: praline confections
directions: Line a 10 x 15-inch pan with graham crackers.
Combine brown sugar and butter in heavy saucepan.
Bring to a rolling boil. Boil for 2 minutes, stirring constantly.
Remove from heat.
Cool slightly.
Stir in pecans.
Spoon mixture over graham cracker layer.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.
Cool slightly before cutting into small squares.
Yield: 80 servings.

title: hamburger casserole
directions: Add the ingredients to hamburger.
Place in casserole dish. Slice canned biscuits in half and place on top.
Bake in oven until biscuits are cooked.

title: sugar popcorn
directions: Cook sugar and water until it spins a thread.
Add vanilla and food coloring.
Stir through popcorn.

title: pizza dip
directions: Mix peppers, tomatoes and chili powder.
Layer in an ovenproof dish (approximately 2-quart). Start and end with cheese.
Bake uncovered at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes or until bubbling.
Let stand for 5 minutes before serving with tortilla chips.

title: oven barbecued pork chops
directions: Sprinkle frypan with salt and brown pork chops.
Put in casserole.
Wipe out skillet.
Mix all remaining ingredients and pour into skillet. Simmer 1 or 2 minutes, stirring to deglaze pan. Pour sauce over the chops. Cover and bake at 325° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: cucumber relish
directions: Chop all vegetables fine and mix sugar, vinegar and turmeric together with vegetables.
Boil for 1 hour.
Put in jars and seal. Makes 10 pints.

title: beef stew
directions: Cut beef into small cubes.
Heat oil on medium heat.
Brown beef.
Add water, salt and pepper; cover and simmer over low heat for 1 1/2 hours.
After meat is tender, add remaining vegetables and continue cooking until vegetables are tender.
Mix butter and flour; stir into hot liquid.
Cook until thickened.

title: snow biscuits
directions: Dissolve yeast in water (let set 5 minutes). Sift flour.
Add sugar and salt.
Mix well, slowly.
Add yeast water and melted oleo, mixing well.
Let rise 30 minutes.
Knead out on floured cloth.
Cut into biscuits. Bake 30 minutes at 425°.

title: chicken viva
directions: Combine salsa, soups, black olives and milk.
Put 1 cup sauce in bottom of casserole; layer 5 tortillas (in pieces); layer 1/2 of chicken; layer 1/2 of remaining sauce; layer 1/4 pound Monterey Jack and 1/4 pound Cheddar cheese.
Top with remaining tortillas, chicken, sauce and cheeses.
Refrigerate overnight.
Set out 1/2 hour before baking.
Bake 1 hour at 300°.

title: carrot cake
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease bottom and sides of rectangular pan, 13 x 9 x 2-inches or 2 round pans, 8 x 1 1/2 or 9 x 1 1/2-inches with shortening; lightly flour.
Beat sugar, oil and eggs in large bowl on low speed about 30 seconds.
Add remaining ingredients except carrots, nuts and Cream Cheese Frosting.
Beat on low speed 1 minute.
Stir in carrots and nuts.
Pour in pan.
Bake in rectangular pan 40 or 45 minutes until toothpick comes out clean. Cool 10 minutes or completely.
Frost with Cream Cheese Frosting; covered in refrigerator.

title: fruit salad
directions: In large bowl, combine buttermilk and pudding.
Fold in whipped topping.
Place 1/2 of fruit mixture in a serving bowl.
Top with pudding mixture.
Place remaining fruit on top.
Makes 12 servings.

title: golden punch
directions: Bring sugar and water to a boil and stir until sugar dissolves.
Stir in frozen orange and lemonade concentrates until melted.
Stir in pineapple juice and 3 cups cold water.
Freeze in ice cube trays or 9 x 13-inch baking pans.
If using baking pans, cut into squares.
Put frozen cubes in plastic bags until ready to use.
Mix with ginger ale until slushy.
Makes about 2 gallons slushy punch.

title: blueberry dessert
directions: Cream sugar and cream cheese.
Beat eggs and add to mixture; blend well.
Put over crumb crust and bake at 350° for 10 or 15 minutes.
Cool.
Then cover with blueberry pie filling.
Top with Cool Whip.
Chill overnight.

title: healthy cocktail delight
directions: Spray Bundt pan with Pam.
Mix all ingredients together.
If you want almonds on top, put a handful on bottom of Bundt pan. Pour in mix.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: joan crawford's meat loaf
directions: Combine meats, unbeaten eggs, chopped onion, chopped pepper, 1 tablespoon seasoned salt, 1 teaspoon steak sauce and 1 tablespoon Worcestershire.
Mix well.

title: cinnamon-spiced apple jelly
directions: Combine apple juice, water, lemon juice, food coloring, pectin and cinnamon candies in a large saucepan.
Tie cloves and cinnamon stick in a cheesecloth bag.
Add spice bag to juice mixture. Bring mixture to a boil, stirring constantly, until cinnamon candies dissolve.
Stir in sugar; return to a rolling boil.
Boil hard 1 minute, stirring constantly.
Remove from heat; discard spice bag.
Skim foam, if necessary.
Reserve 1/4 cup apple jelly for muffins; cool and allow to set.

title: one year old fruit cake
directions: Mix flour, salt and baking powder; sift over fruit.
Beat eggs. Stir in sugar with beaten eggs, flour over fruit and dry mixture; mix well.
Pour in pecans and mix well.
Bake at 250° for 1 1/2 hours.
I put mine in an iron frying pan (medium size).
Put a pan of water in oven so cake won't dry out.

title: sunflower seed bread
directions: Grease bottoms only of bread pans.
Dissolve yeast with 2 tablespoons honey and small amount of warm water.
Set until bubbly.
Add to milk and rest of honey, 4 tablespoons margarine and salt.
Add 10 cups flour, one cup at a time; stir in until soft dough forms.
Stir in seeds.
Spread elastic and has a sort of "sheen."
Add flour as needed.
Let rise until double (1 to 2 hours).
Shape into loaves (4).
Let rise until double.
Brush with remaining margarine.
Bake at 375° about 45 minutes.

title: caramel corn
directions: Combine in saucepan:
butter, corn syrup and brown sugar.
Boil 5 minutes.
Add vanilla and baking soda.
Stir to mix well.
Place popcorn in deep baking pan and pour syrup over it.
Bake 1 hour at 250°, stirring every 15 minutes.

title: sugar cookies
directions: Cream all ingredients through vanilla; add flour, salt, soda and cream of tartar.
Drop by teaspoon on cookie sheet; bake at 350° for 10 minutes.

title: ham biscuits
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Slice the entire pans of rolls through the center.
Lift off the top half.
Spread the mixture on bottom half.
Put the top on.
Wrap the pans of rolls in foil.
May freeze or refrigerate.
Bake at 375° for 15 minutes (if thawed) or 30 minutes (if frozen).

title: salmon patties
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Shape into patties.
Dip into additional beaten egg, mixed with 1 tablespoon of water and extra bread crumbs.
Fry in butter.

title: curry-cajun chicken
directions: In 3-quart baking dish, combine honey, water, mustard, melted margarine or butter, Cajun spices, curry powder, lemon juice and garlic; mix well.
Add chicken breasts in single layer, coating with sauce.
Bake, uncovered, in 350° oven for 30 minutes or until chicken is no longer pink.
Serve chicken and pan drippings with rice.

title: chicken and dressing casserole
directions: Take chicken off the bone and place in a 2-quart casserole dish.
Melt margarine and add soups and milk.
Pour over chicken in casserole dish.
Mix stuffing with broth and spoon over mixture in casserole dish.
Do not stir layers together.
Bake at 425° for 25 minutes or until brown.

title: 4 layer chocolate delight
directions: Mix together; press into 9 x 13 x 2 pan.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.
Cool completely.

title: skillet chicken and rice
directions: Cut chicken breasts into 3-inch strips.
Brown lightly (5 minutes) in oil over high heat.
Add mushrooms, carrots, onions, parsley flakes, savory or thyme leaves, salt, pepper, apple juice and bay leaf.
Stir well.
Cover and simmer 15 to 20 minutes until vegetables are tender-crisp.
Stir in instant rice.
Cover and simmer an additional 10 minutes until rice is tender.
Remove bay leaf.
Good served with a little soy sauce.
Makes 6 servings at 240 calories with 4 grams fat.

title: party cookies
directions: Blend shortening and brown granulated sugar in large bowl. Beat in vanilla and eggs.
Sift remaining ingredients together, add to sugar, egg mixture, blending well.
Stir in candies. Reserve some for decorating.
Drop on top of a ungreased cookie sheet.
Decorate with remaining candies.
Bake in moderate oven, 375° for 10 minutes or until golden brown.
Remove cookies with spatula to wire racks, cool completely.

title: steak
directions: Cut steak in strips and cook. Simmer for 1 hour in onions, sour cream, and mushroom soup.

title: broccoli and cheese pasties(penny's health favorite)
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Steam broccoli.
Cool.
Mix with next 4 ingredients in medium bowl.
Season with pepper.
Unfold crusts and cut them in half, making 4 half circles.
Mold 1/4 of the filling on half of each pastry, press filling until it is compact. Brush pasties with glaze.
Fold the second half of the pastry over.
Press into triangles.
Using a fork, crimp the pasties and pierce several times.
Place on large baking sheet.
Brush with glaze.
Bake for 22 minutes and let stand.
Makes 2 servings.

title: italian zucchini crescent pie
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
In a 10-inch skillet, cook zucchini and onions in margarine until tender.
Stir in parsley and seasoning.

title: brownie candy cups
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Line 30 muffin cups with foil baking liners or place on baking sheets.
Combine brownie mix, fudge packet from mix, eggs, water and oil in large bowl.
Stir with spoon until well blended, about 50 strokes.
Place 2 level measuring tablespoons batter in each foil liner.
Bake 10 minutes. Remove from oven.
Push one peanut butter cup candy in center of each cupcake until even with surface of brownie.
Bake 5 to 7 minutes longer.
Remove to cooling racks.
Cool completely.

title: orange sherbet salad
directions: Dissolve Jell-O in boiling water.
Add orange sherbet; stir until melted.
Add oranges, marshmallows and nuts.
Chill and serve.

title: chicken pot pie
directions: Cook chicken breasts.
Cook frozen vegetables according to package.
Heat soup and add 1/2 can water plus chicken broth mixed with gravy mix.
Heat to blend.
Tear chicken into pieces and add to soup mixture.
Then add vegetables.
Pour into 9 x 12-inch pan and top with biscuits made from Bisquick.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes, until biscuits are done and brown.

title: crab cakes(serves 4)
directions: Combine eggs with the green pepper, mustard, salt, pepper, cracker crumbs and mayonnaise.
Fold in crabmeat; shape into cakes.
Coat with additional crumbs; refrigerate for 1 hour, or until ready to cook.
Saute in butter over medium heat for about 3 minutes per side, or until delicately browned.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Simmer chicken in water with onions and celery tops until tender, about 25 minutes.
Strain broth and save.
Remove skin from chicken and break meat into chunks.
Cook macaroni.
Put into greased 2-quart casserole.
Sprinkle cheese over macaroni.
Cover with chicken and sprinkle with cashews.
Pour soup thinned with 2/3 cup broth over the chicken.
Top with crushed crackers and bake uncovered at 350° for 30 minutes or until bubbly.

title: chocolate cookies
directions: Mix brown sugar and lard, then add eggs, milk and 1/4 cup cocoa.
Add 1 teaspoon vanilla and then the dry ingredients.
Bake at 375°.

title: cinnamon pull aparts
directions: Melt margarine, ice cream and sugar. Cut biscuits in quarters or halves.
Roll biscuits in cinnamon and sugar.
Pour melted ingredients over biscuits.
Bake at 400° for 20 minutes.
Use a 9 x 13-inch pan or Bundt pan.

title: party snack
directions: In skillet, pour jelly and chili sauce.
Add 1 or 2 packages cocktail hot dogs.
Heat until hot dogs are warm.

title: chicken parmesan
directions: Dip chicken in egg and buttermilk.
Coat in Italian bread crumbs.
Fry in oil until brown.
(This may be done the day before and refrigerated until needed later.)
Layer chicken breasts in large baking dish.
Cover with Prego spaghetti sauce.
Bake about 30 minutes until heated through.

title: minnesota wild rice salad
directions: Blend first 4 ingredients; combine next 6 ingredients and pour dressing over all.
Just before serving, fold in grapes and cashews.

title: kathy's spanish bean soup
directions: Put 10 cups water in a Dutch oven.
Mix onion, ham, etc. Simmer until meat falls off bone.
Add cabbage; cook until done.

title: moist pumpkin bread
directions: Mix the margarine, eggs, sugar, pumpkin and water.
Add the flour, salt, vanilla, baking soda and nutmeg.
Stir and add 1 cup chopped walnuts.
Put in greased loaf pans. Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Makes 3 loaves.

title: pecan chess pie
directions: Melt margarine; add sugar and vinegar.
Bring to boil; add the mixture to beaten eggs, salt and vanilla.
Beat well.
Pour into unbaked pie shell.
Gently place pecans halves over the top of pie filling.
Bake at 325° for 40 to 45 minutes.

title: sunset gel salad
directions: Dissolve jello and salt in boiling water.
Add pineapple and lemon juice.
Chill until thick, then fold in carrots and pecans. Pour into a 9 x 13-inch pan; chill until firm.

title: raw potato klushki or halushki
directions: Grate potatoes.
Drain water from potatoes.
Mix remaining ingredients.
Knead until smooth and hands are clean of dough. Drop by teaspoonfuls into boiling salted water.
Cook until Klushki float on top or until tender.
Drain.

title: ultimate chocolate chip cookies
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Combine Crisco, light brown sugar, milk and vanilla in large bowl.
Beat at medium speed of electric mixer until well blended.
Beat egg into creamed mixture.
Combine flour, salt and baking soda.
Mix into creamed mixture just until blended.
Stir in chocolate chips.

title: heavenly orange fluff
directions: Dissolve Jell-O in boiling water.
Add orange juice concentrate, oranges and pineapple with juice.
Put into oblong dish and congeal.
Spread with topping and refrigerate until topping is set.
Slice into squares to serve.

title: peanut butter balls(candy)
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients well. Roll into balls and chill.
Melt the chocolate morsels and paraffin over hot water.
Keep warm and dip balls.
Place on waxed paper and cool.
Serves too many.

title: pistachio nut salad
directions: Drain pineapple well.
In bowl mix pudding and pineapple. Let stand 5 minutes.
Stir in Cool Whip.
Mix in marshmallows.

title: peanut butter shake
directions: Combine all ingredients in blender; process until smooth. Serve at once.
Serves 4.

title: salmon steaks teriyaki
directions: Thaw fish, if frozen.
Place salmon in a 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking pan. Combine the oil with the remaining ingredients.
Pour over steaks.
Marinate, covered, in refrigerator overnight, turning occasionally. Drain, reserving marinade.
Bake, uncovered, in a 350° oven about 18 to 20 minutes or until fish flakes easily with a fork.
Brush occasionally with marinade during baking and again just before serving.
Garnish plate with parsley and lime peel, if desired.
Yields 4 servings.

title: herb crackers(great for parties or special activities)
directions: Mix well dressing, oil and seasonings.
Pour over crackers and mix well.
Store in airtight container.

title: caramel cake
directions: Combine all ingredients except eggs. Blend thoroughly, then beat 2 minutes. Add eggs and beat 2 more minutes. Bake in 2 layer pans 30 minutes at 350°.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Place all dry ingredients in a large mixing bowl.
With spoon, make a deep well in center.
In this well add all the other ingredients, stir carefully, just enough to dampen all the dry ingredients.
pour into 2 greased and floured 9 x 5 x 2 3/4 inch loaf pans.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour or until toothpick inserted in the center comes out clean.
I always add some chopped nuts and sprinkle some sugar over the top before baking.

title: chicken marsala with mushrooms
directions: Pound chicken with mallet to tenderize.

title: chicken and dressing
directions: Boil hen and put broth aside.
Boil onion and celery in broth with oleo until tender. To make bread, combine corn meal, flour, baking powder, salt and sugar. Add 4 eggs and buttermilk.
Beat well. Bake bread mixture at 375° until done. Add cooled, crumbled bread crumbs to broth, soups and onions.
Add 6 eggs and mix well. Cook at 350° until browned.

title: fudge pie
directions: Melt margarine and chocolate over hot water.
Beat eggs in a bowl, gradually adding sugar.
Add flour and salt, then add to chocolate mixture.
Pour into ungreased 8-inch pie plate and bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.
Cool, then freeze.
You do not have to thaw before serving.

title: potato pancake
directions: Melt butter in frying pan.
Squish potatoes flat to about 1 inch.
Fry over medium heat until lightly brown, turning once. Serve with more butter if you want.

title: mom's meat balls
directions: Mix ground beef, milk and oatmeal together and roll into small balls.
Place in baking dish.

title: 8 layer green salad
directions: Layer lettuce, peas, onion and green peppers in large salad bowl.
Spread mayonnaise over layers, sealing to edge.
Sprinkle sugar, Parmesan cheese and bacon over mayonnaise.

title: fudge truffle cheesecake
directions: Heat oven to 300°.
Prepare Chocolate Crumb Crust.
Set aside. In heavy saucepan, over low heat, melt chips, stirring constantly.
In a large bowl, beat cheese until fluffy. Gradually beat in sweetened condensed milk until smooth.
Add melted chips and remaining ingredients.
Mix well.
Pour into prepared pan. Bake 1 hour and 5 minutes.
Cool and chill.

title: banana bits
directions: Roll banana chunks in lime juice.
Coat thoroughly with cinnamon and sugar.
Relish for meat course.

title: short-cut broccoli casserole
directions: Prepare broccoli-cheese pouches as directed on package.
In the meantime, prepare rice. Saute onion in oleo in skillet. When cooled enough, open broccoli-cheese pouches into skillet with sauteed onion. Chop broccoli with fork or spoon. Add rice. Add soup.
(For a firmer casserole, add only 1/2 can soup.)
Mix thoroughly in skillet and pour into casserole dish. Bake, covered, in a 350° oven for 25 minutes.

title: puff danish
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Cut 1/2 cup butter into 1 cup flour until it resembles small peas.
Sprinkle 2 tablespoons water over flour, mix it with a fork.
Form a ball; divide in half.
Pat each half into a rectangle, 12 x 3 inches, on an ungreased cookie sheet, about 3 inches apart.

title: crustless coconut pie
directions: Beat eggs; add sugar and flour.
Mix well; add milk, vanilla, melted oleo and coconut.
Mix well.
Pour into greased 9 x 13-inch glass dish or pie plates.
Bake at 350° for 30 or 35 minutes or until knife inserted comes out clean.

title: busy day stew
directions: Put beef in casserole, salt lightly.
Sprinkle with flour and bread crumbs.
Pour red wine and consomme together and then pour over meat.
Slice onion on top.
Cover and bake at 300° for 3 1/2 hours or until meat is done.
Serves 6.

title: cream of broccoli soup
directions: Saute onion in margarine.
Add chicken broth and bring to boil.
Add noodles and cook for 5 minutes.
Add milk and broccoli and cheese, simmer for 8 minutes.
Add pepper and garlic powder to taste.

title: apple kuchen
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Cut butter into cake mix until crumbly. Mix in coconut.
Pat mixture lightly into ungreased 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan, building up slight edges.
Bake for 10 minutes. Arrange apple slices on warm crust.
Mix sugar and cinnamon; sprinkle over apples.
Blend sour cream and egg; drizzle over apples.
Topping will not completely cover apples.
Bake for 25 minutes or until edges are light brown.
Do not overbake.
Serve warm.
Makes 12 to 15 servings.

title: refrigerator sugar tea cookies
directions: Mix together sugars, oleo and oil.
Add egg, flour, baking soda, salt, cream of tartar and vanilla.
Make into a ball. Chill at least one hour, better overnight.
Pinch off 1 teaspoon; put on baking sheet and flatten with fork dipped in sugar.
Bake at 325° for 10 to 12 minutes.
Don't brown too much; watch closely.
Will keep covered airtight in refrigerator up to a week.

title: german chocolate pie
directions: In a saucepan, melt chocolate and butter over low heat, stirring to mix well.
Remove from heat and gradually blend in milk.
Set aside.

title: no fat vegetable soup
directions: In a large pot add first 6 ingredients and simmer 20 minutes. Add remaining ingredients and simmer 1 hour.
Remove from heat and let set 1 to 2 hours, covered.
Overnight is best!

title: three fruit pie
directions: Sprinkle sugar and flour mixture in bottom of pie crust. Alternate with layers of fruit.
Dot with butter and put on top crust.
Seal edges well.
Brush top of crust with butter.
Bake at 350° until crust is brown.

title: golden punch
directions: Chill 2 or 3 hours, then add 12 ounces maraschino cherries or juice only, saving cherries to freeze in ice ring.
Add 3 gallons of water and 2 quarts of dry ginger ale when ready to serve. At the last minute, add an ice ring and 1 pint of pineapple sherbet.

title: 5 layer dessert
directions: Mix flour, butter and nuts.
Pat out in pan.
This makes the crust.
Bake about 20 minutes at 375°; then cool crust.

title: spaghetti sauce
directions: Brown meat, onions, bell pepper and garlic (if using). Add rest of ingredients. Stir well and cook for 1/2 hour on low heat. Serve over cooked pasta.

title: southwest chicken bake
directions: Open cans and drain beans, corn, and tomatoes.
Do not rinse. Add chopped onion and chopped bell pepper.
Mix everything together.
Meanwhile, place chicken breast in a 9x13 inch pan and season to taste with salt and pepper.
Spread the vegetable mixture evenly over the chicken and bake at 350° for approximately 30-40 minutes, or until chicken is done.
Top with shredded monterrey jack cheese (as much or as little as you like) and cook about 5 more minutes or until cheese is melted and bubbly.

title: carrot bars
directions: Mix sugar and cooking oil until blended. Beat in eggs, one at a time. Add cinnamon and baby food. Mix soda, salt and flour together and stir in. Add walnuts. Divide batter into 2 greased and floured 9 x 13 cake pans. Bake at 350° approximately 35 minutes or until toothpick comes out clean.

title: versie's crawfish etouffee
directions: Make a light to medium brown roux. Combine yellow onions with roux and butter in a large pot.
