Cook onions slowly on medium or low heat until they are clear and no longer crunchy; stir continuously. When onions have cooked down, add crawfish tails with their juice. Add green onions, parsley, garlic, salt and seasonings. Add water. Cook on low heat 45 minutes, stirring frequently. Etouffee should be slightly thick but you may add more water to get it to your preferred consistency. Season to taste and serve over a bed of rice. Serves 4 to 6.

title: impossible pie
directions: Blend all ingredients in blender.
Grease 10-inch pie plate and flour it.
Pour mixture into pan.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 50 minutes.
When done it makes its own crust.

title: bean dip
directions: Brown ground beef.
Add refried beans, tomato paste and taco seasoning.
Mix well.
Pour into casserole dish.
Cover with Cheddar cheese.
Place in microwave until cheese is melted.

title: warm, soft chocolate cake
directions: In a double boiler set over simmering water, heat butter and chocolate until the chocolate is almost completely melted. Beat together the eggs, yolks and sugar with a whisk or electric beater until light and thick. Beat together the chocolate mixture with the egg mixture a little at a time as not to scramble the eggs. Then quickly beat in flour, just to combine. Butter and lightly flour 4-ounce molds or ramekins. Tap out the excess flour, then butter and flour them again. Divide the batter among

the ramekins (at this point you can refrigerate the desserts until you are ready to eat). Preheat oven at 450°. Bake the molds on a tray for 6 to 7 minutes. The center will be quite soft, but the sides will be set. Invert each ramekin onto a plate and let sit for about 10 seconds. Unmold by lifting up one corner. The cake will fall out onto the plate. Serve immediately.

title: carrot cake
directions: With mixer, blend eggs and sugar together.
Blend in oil about 2 minutes on medium speed.
Add all other ingredients and mix well.
Pour into 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake in preheated oven at 350° for 1 hour.

title: jumbo candy cookie
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease a 12-inch pizza pan.
In medium bowl with electric mixer, cream butter and sugar until fluffy about 1 minute.
Beat in egg at low and stir in flour and baking soda until well blended.
Evenly spread dough onto prepared pan. Bake 20 minutes or until lightly brown; sprinkle marshmallows and candies on cookie during last 5 minutes of baking.
Cool 10 minutes on pan on wire rack.
To serve, cut cookie into 16 wedges.

title: deviled ham dip
directions: Combine ingredients and shape into a ball.
Chill.
Before serving, sprinkle with parsley.
Serve with crackers.

title: potato casserole
directions: Combine the first 4 ingredients.
Add 1 cup cheese; mix well. Pour into greased 13 x 9-inch baking dish.
Sprinkle remaining cheese over mixture.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes, or until golden brown.

title: banana split
directions: Melt oleo; mix with graham cracker crumbs.
Spread in 13 x 9-inch pan.
Cream 1 stick oleo with powdered sugar; add eggs. Beat for 15 minutes, spread over cracker crumbs.
Chill 1/2 hour.

title: minute cookies
directions: Mix sugar, cocoa, milk and butter in a saucepan.
Bring to a boil.
Boil 1 full minute.
Remove from burner and add remaining ingredients.
Stir and spoon onto wax paper.

title: jam thumbprints
directions: Cream together butter and sugar until fluffy.
Add egg yolks, vanilla and salt; beat well.
Gradually add sifted flour, mixing well.
Shape in 3/4-inch balls; dip in beaten egg whites and roll in walnuts.
Place 1-inch apart on greased cookie sheet.
Press down center of each with thumb.
Bake at 350° for 15 to 17 minutes.
Cool slightly; remove from pan and cool on rack.
Just before serving, use 1/3 cup cherry or strawberry preserves to fill centers of cookies.
Makes 3 dozen.

title: homemade ketchup
directions: Place vinegar in a large pot and bring to a boil. Add spices, celery, onions and peppers.
Turn heat off and cover with lid. Steep for 45 minutes. Take out spices, celery, onions and peppers. Mix liquid with tomato juice.
Add sugar and salt.
Mix well. Cook mixture until thick.

title: ice cream cake
directions: Bake chocolate cake 15 minutes at 350° in a 9 x 13-inch pan. Let cool.

title: hot crab dip
directions: Mix together and put in casserole; sharp cheese on top.
Bake at 350° for 1/2 hour.

title: creamy strawberry dessert
directions: Combine crumbs, 3 tablespoons sugar and butter.
Press into 8-inch round pan.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.
Cool.

title: french cherry pie
directions: Cream first three ingredients.
Fold into whipped cream.
Pour into baked pie shell.
Top with prepared cherry pie filling.
Chill several hours before serving.

title: six cups salad
directions: Mix all ingredients together (with juices?).
Refrigerate and serve.

title: turtle cake
directions: Mix the cake mix according to the directions.
To half of the mixture, add 1/2 cup melted butter and 1/2 can of milk.
Pour into a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake 25 minutes at 350°.

title: jambalaya
directions: Saute onions in butter until tender.
Add tomatoes and tomato paste and cook 5 minutes, stirring.
Add seasons, chopped very fine.
Cook 1/2 hour, stirring frequently.
Stir in ham and cook for about 5 minutes longer.
Add shrimp and continue cooking another 5 minutes.
Stir in cooked rice and season.
Simmer for about 1/2 hour, stirring frequently.

title: chili bean dip
directions: Cook beef in skillet until it loses its red color, stirring to crumble.
Drain fat; add onion and cook until onion is tender. Add undrained beans and mash with fork to blend with meat.
Stir in catsup, chili powder, salt, cumin and cayenne.
Simmer 5 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Stir in cheese until melted. Serve hot as a dip with corn chips or other chips, Melba toast or crackers; or pile the hot mixture in miniature tart shells.
Makes 2 1/2 cups of dip.

title: dollie's biscuits
directions: Mix all dry ingredients together first.
Then gradually add milk of your choosing.
Knead with hands until smooth.
Roll out one time less than the height you want, then turn dough over to make it look like two layers of dough.
Cut with floured glass. Place on greased cookie sheet and bake at 350° until golden brown. You can shape it by hand, but do not double your dough.

title: refrigerator cucumbers
directions: Mix salt with cucumbers and let stand while mixing syrup to make syrup.
Mix sugar, vinegar, celery seed and dill flakes together and bring to boil.
Pour over cucumbers immediately then cool.
Refrigerate.
Keeps up to 6 months.

title: fruit pudding cake
directions: Sift together flour, sugar, baking soda and salt.
Add eggs and fruit cocktail.
Mix well and pour into greased and floured tube pan. Bake 1 hour at 300°.
Cool 15 minutes and then remove from pan.

title: veg-all casserole
directions: Mix all together.
Pour into a 9 x 13-inch baking dish. Sprinkle Veg-All mixture with crushed crackers.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: rolls
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Lightly grease a muffin pan.
Mix all ingredients.
Bake until golden brown.

title: crumb cake
directions: Bake cake mix in jelly roll pan for 20 to 25 minutes at 350°.

title: corn bread
directions: Sift flour once, add soda and salt and sift again.
Add corn meal.
Combine eggs, milk and shortening and add to dry ingredients, stir only until smooth.
Bake at 400° for 30 minutes.

title: tater tot casserole
directions: Brown ground beef in skillet and season to taste with garlic salt and onion flakes.
After ground beef is done, pour into a 9 x 13-inch baking pan.
Sprinkle shredded cheese over the meat.
Next place a layer of Tater Tots over the cheese, then top with soup. Bake for 25 to 30 minutes in a 350° oven.

title: banana nut bread
directions: Mix sugar, shortening and egg thoroughly; add milk and bananas.
Stir in flour, baking powder and salt.
Stir in nuts. Bake in a 350° oven for 70 minutes.

title: anne marie's dill vinaigrette
directions: Place vinegars, wine, salt, egg, pepper, mustard, garlic and honey in food processor.
Process until well blended.
In a slow stream, slowly add the oils.
Turn off machine and stir in by hand the tarragon leaves and dill weed.
Store, covered, in refrigerator overnight to allow flavors to blend.
Makes 1 3/4 cups.

title: lasagna improvise
directions: Mix Ricotta, Mozzarella, beaten eggs, Parmesan or Romano cheese and spices (cheese and spices to taste) in a large bowl.
Add cooked pasta and 1 quart sauce.
(The other quart is used at the time of serving.)
Mix well.
Smooth top layer in a baking pan. Cover with sauce and grated cheese.
Cover with foil.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 60 minutes.
Let set for 15 minutes.
Serve.

title: creamy hash brown bake
directions: In a large bowl, combine the soups, sour cream, butter and onion. Add potatoes and mix well. Pour into greased 9 x 13 baking dish. Sprinkle with crushed potato chips. Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 55 to 60 minutes or until potatoes are tender.

title: sauerkraut salad
directions: Mix together sugar, vinegar and oil.
Heat to dissolve sugar. Pour over sauerkraut and let stand overnight in refrigerator.

title: german chocolate pie
directions: Mix.
Pour into crusts.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: fruit pizza
directions: Place tortilla on ungreased cookie sheet.

title: old fashioned rice custard
directions: In the top of a double boiler, combine rice and 2 cups milk; cook, stirring occasionally, over boiling water until rice is tender and most of water has evaporated, about 45 minutes.

title: white chocolate cream cheese frosting
directions: Melt white chocolate in a heavy saucepan over low heat, stirring constantly.
Remove from heat; cool 10 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Beat cream cheese and butter at medium speed with an electric mixer until creamy.
Gradually add white chocolate, beating constantly until blended.
Gradually add powdered sugar, beating until smooth.
Stir in vanilla.
Yield: about 5 cups.

title: pretzel salad(dessert)
directions: Mix first three ingredients and put in a 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Bake at 400° for 8 minutes.
Set aside.
Beat sugar into cream cheese and stir in Cool Whip.
Pour over pretzels.

title: waffles a la jonne
directions: Mix all the ingredients together thoroughly and place into a waffle iron.
Good appetite!

title: english peas and asparagus
directions: Melt oleo and cheese together, then add mushroom soup and mix. Drain English peas and asparagus.
Add to mixture and heat until heated through.
Do not boil.
Reheat leftovers in oven.

title: brisket
directions: Marinate brisket in bottle of smoke overnight; drain and put into pan with beer, onion soup mix and enough water to cover brisket. Cook 3 to 4 hours depending on size of brisket. Let cool completely overnight if possible. Save juice from brisket and take off fat on top of liquid.

title: peanut butter pie
directions: Mix together peanut butter, sugar, cream cheese and butter; set aside.
Whip together whipping cream and vanilla well, then add to peanut butter mixture.
Spread into graham cracker pie crust.
Melt chocolate chips with a little milk.
Spread over pie.
Refrigerate.

title: peanut butter balls
directions: Roll first 4 ingredients into small balls and chill.
Melt 12 oz. package chocolate chips or butterscotch chips and paraffin wax.
Dip balls in mixture and place on wax paper.

title: roast deer with gravy
directions: Brown roast completely
(either in skillet of under broiler) until it is crusty, but not burnt.
Put roast into pan or Dutch oven large enough for meat to be at least half submerged in gravy. Season both sides of meat with the salt, pepper, garlic powder and MSG.
Pour soups over meat, add water, onions and potatoes, bring to a slow boil.
Then cover and simmer for about two hours, longer if necessary turning meat once.
Meat should be tender and juicy.
This recipe may be cooked in the oven.
Just slow bake covered at 300° for about three hours or longer, depending on size of roast.

title: flavor crispy treats
directions: Grease 15 x 10 x 1-inch pan. Melt margarine in 4-quart saucepan on low heat. Add marshmallows; stir until marshmallows are melted and mixture is smooth. Remove from heat. Stir in drink mix. Immediately add cereal; mix until well coated. Press into prepared pan. Cool; cut into squares.

title: "feta" stuffed chicken
directions: Place each chicken breast half between 2 sheets of heavy plastic wrap. Flatten to 1/4-inch thickness. Coat chicken in bread crumbs. Add 1 tablespoon cheese into each piece of chicken and fold in half. Place folded chicken breast into an 8-inch square baking dish coated with cooking spray. Drizzle margarine over chicken. Bake at 400° for 25 minutes.

title: cheesy cheddar potatoes
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Mix all ingredients, breaking up potatoes with spoon, if necessary.
Spoon into 12 x 8-inch baking dish. Bake 45 minutes or until golden brown.
Makes 6 servings.

title: cheesecake dip
directions: Beat cheese, sugar and milk until well blended.
Fold in Cool Whip and vanilla.
Store in refrigerator.
Use to dip cookies, cake cubes, fresh fruit, pretzel sticks, etc.
Approximately 6 calories per teaspoon.

title: shrimp mold
directions: Heat tomato soup until bubbly.
Add to dissolved gelatin.
Add all other ingredients in order.
May also add Tabasco sauce, Worcestershire sauce, etc.
Grease a mold.
Pour in.
Chill overnight.
Serve with crackers.

title: breakfast casserole
directions: Brown sausage and drain.
Combine eggs and milk.
Beat well. Fold in bread cubes and other ingredients.
Mix well.
Pour into greased casserole dish and refrigerate overnight.
Bake in 300° oven for 40 to 45 minutes or until set and lightly browned.
Let stand 5 minutes before slicing for serving.

title: barb's corn bread(12 servings)
directions: Mix together.
Pour into bread pan and bake at 425° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: chicken dressing
directions: Bake cornbread as directed.
Toast bread and crumble. Mix with crumbled cornbread.
Cook rice in salted water until soft and add to bread mixture.
Saute onions (white and green) and celery in a stick of oleo; add soup to the vegetables and heat.
Pour mixture into bread mixture and mix well. Add spices, apple and eggs. If mixture is not very moist, add a can or two or more of chicken broth until mixture is very moist.
Put in greased casserole dishes and bake at 400° until lightly brown on top.
Makes enough dressing for 10 to 15 people.

title: high protein cookies
directions: Mix well.
Roll in small ball and mash with fork on a greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes, or until lightly brown. Makes 2 dozen.

title: squash casserole
directions: Cut squash in half; scoop out the middle.
Leave enough to make shell firm.
Cut up scooped out squash in bite size cubes. Cut up any vegetables into cubes.
Saute in butter until browned and soft.
Brown sausage and mix with squash and vegetables. Brush squash shells with butter and bake in microwave about 7 minutes.

title: artichoke pie
directions: In large bowl, mix eggs, sliced pepperoni, Mozzarella (cut up), cheese, salt and pepper (optional).
Pour mixture into pie shells and bake for 45 minutes at 350°.
Cool before serving.

title: chicken rotel(student favorite)
directions: Boil chicken.
Remove from bone (save broth).
Break spaghetti into bite size pieces.
Cook in chicken broth.
Drain.
Saute pepper and onion in margarine until tender.
Melt cheese and mix with soup, peas, Ro-Tel and mushrooms.
Add salt to taste.
Add chicken and spaghetti.
Mix everything well.
Bake in buttered 2 or 3-quart baking dish for 15 minutes at 350°.

title: banana nut salad
directions: Mash bananas with lemon juice and add sugar.
Add pecans, cherries and pineapple.
Mix in sour cream and fold in Cool Whip. Chill.

title: overnight butterscotch rolls
directions: The night before, arrange frozen dinner rolls around a greased Bundt pan.
Sprinkle dry pudding mix, then sprinkle with brown sugar.
Pour melted butter over pudding mix and brown sugar. Sprinkle with nuts.
Cover with a towel and let thaw and rise at room temperature overnight.

title: graham cracker brittle
directions: Place graham crackers in large flat pan (cookie sheet) without overlapping.
Sprinkle top of each cracker with nuts. Bring margarine and sugar to a boil.
Boil 3 minutes.
Spoon over crackers.

title: hamburg pie
directions: Brown beef and drain.
Mix milk, mayo, eggs and cornstarch and beat until smooth.
Add cheese, onion and dash of pepper to milk mixture.
Stir in ground beef.
Pour entire mixture into pie shell.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes or until knife inserted in middle comes out clean.

title: soda scones
directions: Stir together dry ingredients and mix with hands.
Add buttermilk to make a soft dough.
Knead on a floured board until dough is free from cracks.
Roll out to 1/4-inch and shape into scones.
Place on greased, floured sheet and bake at 400° for 15 minutes.

title: dumplings(aunt euna's)
directions: Combine all ingredients and roll paper thin.
Cut and freeze. When ready for use, drop into hot broth.

title: four season fajitas
directions: Julienne vegetables and finely dice the jalapeno and garlic. In a skillet heat some olive oil over medium heat and add the onions. Season the onions with salt and pepper. Cook the onions for 5 minutes and then add the bell peppers, garlic, and jalapeno. Cook all the vegetables for an additional 10 minutes over medium heat until the bell peppers are tender and the onions are tender and sweet.

title: mincemeat
directions: Mix together in a large kettle.
Cook slowly until thick.
Can be canned or frozen.
Makes 4 to 5 pints.

title: sweet potato pie
directions: Mix
sweet potatoes, sugars and butter.
Add egg yolks; mix thoroughly.
Add
spices, then add milk.
Beat egg whites (adding 2 tablespoons granulated sugar).
Fold egg whites into potato mixture.
Pour
into
unbaked pie shell.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until done.

title: vegetable casserole
directions: Pour 1/2 milk in saucepan.
Add flour and seasonings and stir constantly to avoid lumps.
Slowly stir in rest of milk, 1/4 cup at a time.
Cook over medium heat until thickened, stirring constantly.
Layer vegetables in casserole dish with green beans on the bottom, then carrots, zucchini and onions on top.
Pour sauce over vegetables.
Sprinkle with crushed cereal.
Cover and bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: bourbon wieners
directions: Cut wieners in bite size pieces.
Combine all ingredients and heat to boiling on stove.
Transfer to crock-pot and simmer for 5 to 6 hours.
Great party snack.

title: strawberry pie
directions: Mix crushed strawberries, sugar and cornstarch, then boil until transparent.
(It will take just a few minutes.) Fill baked pie shell with whole fresh strawberries.
Pour the hot strawberry syrup over the berries and chill.
Makes 1 (10-inch) pie or 8 servings.

title: beer bread
directions: Mix together and place in greased 9 x 5-inch loaf pan.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour.

title: cheese ball
directions: Combine softened cream cheese and Cheddar cheese; mix well. Add remaining ingredients except chopped pecans.
Chill; shape into a ball with greased hands.
Roll in chopped nuts.
Freezes well.

title: divinity
directions: Cook sugar, Karo and water to
soft ball.
Pour half of syrup slowly over stiffly
beaten egg white, beating constantly.
Return rest of syrup to fire and cook to hard ball.
Pour slowly over egg white mixture while continuing to beat.
Beat for 3 to
5 minutes.
Add
chopped nuts.
Pour into well-buttered 9 x 13-inch pan.
When
cold, cut and store in airtight container.

title: overnight butterscotch rolls
directions: Grease a Bundt pan and sprinkle with pecans.
Drop 1 package frozen rolls into pan.
Sprinkle pudding over rolls.
Melt oleo; pour over rolls.
Sprinkle brown sugar over top.
Cover with towel and let stand overnight.
Bake at 300° for 35 minutes.
Flip out of pan onto a platter immediately.

title: hearty chicken bake(winter warmer)
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
In a medium bowl, combine potatoes, 1/2 the cheese and 1/2 the onions; mix thoroughly.
Spoon into greased 1 1/2 quart casserole, spreading across bottom and up sides to form a shell.
In a large bowl, combine chicken, mixed vegetables, soup, milk and seasonings; pour into potato shell.
Bake uncovered 30 minutes or until onions are golden brown.
Let stand 5 minutes before serving.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: creamed ground beef
directions: Cook ground beef in own fat on top of stove.
Crumble while cooking.
Add flour to ground beef while cooking on low heat (mix well, do not brown).
Add milk to beef and flour.
Stir to prevent sticking.
Add salt and pepper to taste.
Serve over toast, hot biscuits or hash brown potatoes.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Dissolve jello in 1 cup hot water.
Chill until partially set. Add remaining ingredients and chill until set.
If using whole berry sauce, dissolve 1 package plain gelatin with the jello.

title: strawberry ice cream
directions: Beat eggs and sugar.
Add rest of ingredients.
Put in a 1/2 gallon freezer and crank until done!

title: cheese potato casserole
directions: Defrost hash brown potatoes and put into a 13 x 9-inch pan. Mix together Cheddar cheese, sour cream and soup.
Spread mixture over potatoes.
Sprinkle Parmesan cheese over the top.
Bake at 300° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: green pea salad
directions: Use a oblong casserole dish. Put a layer of lettuce, layer of sweet peas, layer of onions, layer of celery. Spread mayonnaise on top. Sprinkle sugar on top of mayonnaise then parmesan cheese and bacon bits.

title: broccoli-spinach lasagna
directions: Blend cheeses and eggs.
Cook spinach in the wine; drain well. Cool.
Fold spinach into cheese mixture.
Steam vegetables to underdone.
Spray large casserole dish with Pam cooking spray. Alternate layers of noodles, cheese, spinach and vegetables for 3 layers.
Cover top with tomato sauce.
Bake at 375° for 20 to 30 minutes.
Let stand for 10 to 15 minutes.
Makes 4 to 5 servings. Each serving contains 180 calories.

title: nice and easy nacho dip
directions: Spread package of cream cheese over a dinner plate.
Pour salsa over the spread cream cheese. Sprinkle Cheddar or taco cheese on top. Along border of plate, place nacho chips around and place remainder in a bowl.

title: pull apart bread
directions: Grease tube or Bundt pan.
Sprinkle brown sugar and pecans in bottom.
Dip roll in melted butter and roll in cinnamon sugar mixture.
Place in pan.
Cover with towel.
Let rise in warm place overnight.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes.
Invert on large plate and serve hot.
Pull apart with 2 forks.

title: chicken sabella
directions: Grease a 9 x 13-inch baking pan.
Pound boneless breast slightly.
Lay out in baking dish and cover with slices of Swiss cheese.
Mix cream of chicken soup with cooking wine.
Pour mixture over chicken and top with stuffing crumbs.
Drizzle melted butter over top.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes.

title: strawberry shortcut cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease bottom only of 9 x 13-inch cake pan.
Sprinkle marshmallows evenly over bottom of pan.
Mix flour, sugar, shortening, baking powder, salt, milk and vanilla for 3 minutes.
Pour over marshmallows.

title: chicken salad
directions: Cook chicken breast.
Cool.
Cut up fine.
Cook rice as per package.
Mix together with remaining ingredients.
Serve on lettuce leaf.

title: apple crumb cake
directions: Mix all ingredients by hand.
Bake in tube pan at 350° approximately 1 hour (spray pan with Pam).

title: aunt dene's baked lemon pie
directions: Put yolks and 1/2 cup sugar in double boiler.
Mix well and add lemon juice.
Cook until thick.
Cool.
Beat egg whites until stiff.
Add 1/2 cup sugar.
Fold 1/2 of the egg white mixture into cooled filling.
Put in cooked pie shell.
Top with the other egg whites and brown lightly.

title: amish cake
directions: In mixing bowl, mix sugar, flour and soda.
Add eggs, pineapple with juice and pecans, if desired.
Mix well and pour into a 9 x 13 x 2-inch baking pan and bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes.
Spread with icing.

title: chicken tampico
directions: Mix chicken, soup, salsa, broth and 1/2 bell peppers.
Cut tortillas into strips.
Moisten with chicken broth.
Make 2 layers of tortillas, chicken and cheese.
Top with remaining pepper. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: sugarless fruit cake
directions: Cream the margarine, oil and Sugar Twin.
Add eggs and mix well.
Sift together the flour, soda, salt, cloves and cinnamon; add to creamed mixture.
Stir in applesauce and vanilla, mixing well.
Add dates and nuts and mix well.
Pour into greased and floured Bundt pan.
Bake at 350° for 50 minutes; do not overbake. Serves 16.

title: garlic oyster crackers
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients. Toss into crackers and stir. (Use less garlic if you don't want a strong garlic taste.) To let flavors blend, leave to sit awhile before serving.

title: quick tuna casserole
directions: Cook macaroni and cheese per package directions, then put in casserole dish.
Add remaining ingredients.
Stir well.
Bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: chocolate doughnuts
directions: An Alice Mawhinney recipe.

title: asparagus-artichoke casserole with shrimp(serves 6)
directions: Arrange asparagus, artichokes and shrimp in 2-quart casserole in order stated.
Lightly saute mushrooms in 2 tablespoons butter. Arrange over shrimp.
Melt remaining 4 1/2 tablespoons butter in saucepan.
Stir in flour; cook 2 minutes.
Add cream and milk to flour, stirring constantly.
When thick and smooth, season with salt and peppers.
Stir in sherry and Worcestershire.
Pour over casserole.
Sprinkle with cheese and paprika.
(May do ahead and refrigerate at this point.
Let stand at room temperature 30 minutes before continuing.)
Bake at 375° for 20 minutes.

title: hamburger black bean stew
directions: In 5-quart Dutch oven, brown meat and onions, drain fat.
Add rest of ingredients.
Cook until potatoes are tender.

title: best zucchini bars
directions: Beat together sugar, oil and eggs.
Beat in flour, cinnamon, salt, baking soda, baking powder and vanilla.
Beat 1 to 3 minutes.
Fold in zucchini, carrots, oats and nuts.
Pour in large baking sheet.
Bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes.
Put cream cheese frosting on top.

title: chicken pot pie
directions: Cut up chicken and put in casserole dish.
Add vegetables. Mix chicken broth with soup and pour over chicken.
Mix flour, milk and margarine together.
Pour over chicken.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes or until golden brown.

title: pretzel salad
directions: Let jello mixture partially cool and pour over Cool Whip mixture.
Refrigerate.

title: casserole deluxe
directions: Saute onion, green pepper and celery. Mix all other ingredients. Salt and pepper to taste. Top with crackers, slivered almonds and melted margarine. Bake at 325° for 45 minutes.

title: lemon chess pie
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Combine ingredients and pour into pastry shell.
Bake 25 to 30 minutes.

title: pull apart coffee cake
directions: Prepare hot roll mix according to package directions.
Place dough in a greased bowl, turning to grease top.
Cover; let rise in a warm draft-free place until doubled in bulk, 30 to 45 minutes.
Punch down dough.
Turn dough out onto a lightly floured board; knead 1 to 2 minutes until smooth and no longer sticky. Roll dough into 1-inch balls.
Combine sugar and cinnamon, stirring well.
Dip balls in butter, then roll in sugar mixture. Place a layer of balls in greased 10-inch tube pan.
Sprinkle with about 1/4 cup chopped nuts.
Repeat layers with remaining sugared balls and nuts.
Cover and let rise until doubled in bulk, 30 to 45 minutes.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
If you like, drizzle with 10x sugar for a glaze.

title: shrimp dip or mold
directions: Grind together the cooked shrimp and ham (this is a good way to use the hock portion of a baked ham).
Mix this combination with cheese, mayonnaise and seasonings.
Line a mold with dampened cheesecloth.
Place mixture in mold and let stand overnight. Unmold onto a tray.
Garnish to suit the season or occasion.

title: plain jane chicken pie
directions: Mix broth and soup, pouring into oblong casserole dish.
Pour chicken over top and add eggs.
Mix melted margarine, milk and flour and pour over all ingredients.
Do not stir.
Bake at 450° for 30 minutes or until brown on top.

title: 3-way chili
directions: Heat oil in Dutch oven. Add onion, green pepper and garlic; cook over medium-low heat until vegetables are tender, 8 minutes. If too dry, add water, 1/4 cup at a time. Add beef, chili powder, cinnamon and allspice. Cook, stirring, until meat is no longer pink, 10 minutes. Add tomatoes, chilies, vinegar, salt and sugar. Cover and simmer 1 hour. Cook spaghetti according to package; drain.

title: fruit cobbler
directions: Mix fruit and 1 cup of sugar together.
Put 1 stick of margarine into baking dish; let it melt.
Prepare batter from remaining ingredients.
Pour over melted margarine.
Do not stir. Put fruit mixture on top.
Do not stir.
(Batter will rise to top during baking.)
Bake at 350° for 1 hour, until crispy.

title: spicy chicken with broccoli
directions: Remove bone and skin from chicken, cut into 2 1/2 inch pieces. Toss chicken, cornstarch, salt and white pepper in bowl; cover and refrigerate 20 minutes.
Cut broccoli lengthwise into 1 inch thick stems.
Remove flowerets.
Cut stems into 1/4 inch slices.
Place all broccoli in boiling water.
Cover and boil 1 minute.
Drain and immediately rinse in cold water; drain.
Slice onions into 1 inch pieces.
Heat wok very hot; add 3 tablespoons oil, coat sides.
Add bean sauce, garlic, sugar, ginger root and red pepper.
Stir-fry 10 seconds.
Add chicken, stir-fry until chicken is white.
Add broccoli and onions, stir-fry until broccoli is hot.

title: pound cake
directions: Cream the butter.
Add sugar and cream.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating after each addition.
Fold in flour.
Pour into two 9 1/2 x 5 1/2-inch greased, wax paper lined loaf pans.
Bake at 325° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: red punch
directions: Combine and serve chilled over ice.

title: yummasette
directions: Mix all together and bake for 1 hour at 325°.
Top with cheese.

title: dessert cake
directions: Drain pineapple.
Prepare cake mix according to directions. Spread in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake 12 to 15 minutes.
When cool, spread crushed pineapple on top.

title: basting sauce
directions: Heat oil in saucepan.
Add chopped onion.
Cook until tender, but not browned.
Add all remaining ingredients and cook to a boil, stirring constantly.
Cook another 5 minutes at a very slow boil.

title: caramel pie(club member: keisha hudson)
directions: Boil cans of milk in large boiler on low for 3 hours (simmering). Be careful opening, cans very hot. Pour in pie crust and top with Cool Whip. May top with nuts if desired.

title: brownie gems
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. Grease mini muffin pans. Combine brownie mix. oil, eggs, water and fudge packet; stir with a spoon until well blended. Drop by heaping teaspoon into each muffin cup; top with a candy kiss. Cover candy kiss with 1 tsp. of batter. Bake 15 to 17 minutes; cool 5 minutes. Carefully loosen brownies from pan. Remove and cool completely before frosting. Decorate if desired.

title: kids reese's peanut butter cups
directions: Spread peanut butter on crackers and top with chocolate chips. Kids love to make these themselves!

title: no bake oatmeal cookies
directions: Melt butter, sugar, milk and cocoa in a medium-size pot.
Let come to a boil.
Boil 1 minute.
Remove from heat.
Add vanilla and peanut butter. Stir until melted.
Then add oatmeal.
Stir until mixed well.
Drop by spoonful on wax paper.
Let cool before moving.

title: beef stroganoff
directions: Cut steak into bite size cubes.
Sprinkle with meat tenderizer.
Shake in plastic bag with flour.
Brown with onions in butter.
Add seasonings and water.
Cover and simmer about 45 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Add soup and mushrooms, stir in mix.
Cook until meat is tender, about 30 minutes.
Heat mixture piping hot.
Turn off heat and stir in sour cream.
Serve over rice or wide noodles.

title: apple walnut dessert
directions: Mix first 6 ingredients; stir into unbeaten egg and vanilla. Fold in apples and walnuts.
Turn into a well-greased 9-inch pan. Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes or until brown and crusty. Garnish with whipped cream; sprinkle with cinnamon or top with scoops of vanilla ice cream.

title: apple pie
directions: Heat oven to 425°.
Mix sugar, flour, nutmeg, cinnamon and salt.
Stir in apples.
Turn into pastry-lined pie plate; dot with butter.
Cover with top crust that has slits cut in it; seal and flute.
Cover edge with 3-inch strip of aluminum foil and remove foil during last 15 minutes of baking.
Bake until crust is brown and juice bubbles through slits in crust, 40 to 50 minutes.

title: chocolate marshmallow bars
directions: In a large saucepan, combine chocolate chips, peanut butter and butter.
Heat the mixture, stirring constantly, until chips melt and mixture is well blended.

title: quick and easy fruit cobbler
directions: Melt margarine in 13 x 9-inch pan.
Mix flour, sugar and milk; pour into melted margarine.
Pour fruit on top.
Bake at 400° until crust forms on top and is as brown as you like.
Serve hot with vanilla ice cream.

title: lasagna
directions: Saute onions in hot oil until brown.
Add beef.
Cook until red color is lost.
Mix garlic, salt, pepper, oregano, parsley, tomato paste, water and 1 tablespoon Parmesan cheese.
Simmer, covered, for 40 minutes.
Cook noodles according to package directions.
Drain and cover with cold water.

title: meat balls
directions: Mix onion soup and water in saucepan; simmer 5 minutes.
Pour 2 tablespoons of the tomato sauce into a cup; add garlic salt, thyme, pepper, oregano and parsley; mix well.
Add herb mixture to ground beef and mix until blended.
Add remaining tomato sauce to onion soup mixture.
Shape meat balls about the size of a small egg and place in a 2-quart casserole.
Pour soup mixture over meat balls.
Cover and refrigerate.

title: banana dump cake
directions: Dump margarine, sugar, eggs and bananas in a bowl.
Mix.
Dump in rest of ingredients and mix well.

title: strawberry slush
directions: Mix and freeze all these ingredients.
Remove from freezer about 3 hours before serving.
Put slush in punch bowl, adding ginger ale as needed.

title: fresh apple walnut bread
directions: Combine and bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: bob's dog cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 300°.
Combine all ingredients.
Stir until well blended.
Knead dough 2 minutes on a floured surface using a floured rolling pin.
Roll dough out 1/4-inch thick.
Cut out with cookie cutter.
Bake 30 minutes on ungreased baking sheet.
Cool on wire rack.

title: blue cheese muffins
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Butter 2 1/2-inch muffin cups.
In large bowl, combine flour, sugar, baking powder, salt and cheese.
In small bowl, combine egg, milk and butter until blended.
Stir into flour mixture just until moistened.
Spoon into muffin cups, filling 3/4 full.
Bake 20 to 25 minutes or until golden brown. Remove from pan; serve warm.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli.
Mix all ingredients in a casserole dish. Sprinkle bread cubes or crumbs on top.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 45 minutes.

title: chicken enchiladas
directions: Grease a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Cook chicken and debone.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Place tortillas on flat surface.
On one end of the tortilla, place a small handful of chicken, then onions if desired. Top off with a handful of cheese.
Roll tortilla and place in greased pan.
Continue with this until chicken and cheese are gone or desired number of enchiladas.
Top with 1/2 of red sauce.
Place in oven at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes until cheese is melted.
Top with rest of red sauce.
Makes 8 large enchiladas.

title: baked dressing
directions: Cook celery and onions in butter until soft.
Add seasonings to bread cubes.
Combine celery and onion mixture and bread cubes. Add liquid.
Mix.
Place in a 2-quart glass casserole.
Cover and cook with microwave 7 minutes.
Remove cover; stir.
Cook 4 to 5 minutes longer.
If more browning is desired, cook in a glass ceramic dish and place under broiler of conventional range.

title: chocolate no-bake cookies
directions: Bring sugar, cocoa, butter and milk to a rolling boil; cook 1 minute.
Remove from burner and add oats, nuts, peanut butter and vanilla.
Stir well.
Drop by spoonfuls onto wax paper.
Let cool.

title: quiche
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Cook bacon, mushrooms and onion in butter until onion is tender.
Spread in pastry shell.
Toss cheese with flour and place on top of bacon mixture.
Combine eggs, milk and cayenne and pour over mixture in shell.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 50 minutes.

title: cheese brownies
directions: In a small bowl, combine cheese, 1/4 cup sugar, 1 egg, 1 1/2 teaspoons vanilla and cinnamon.
Beat until smooth.
In a small saucepan, melt butter and chocolate over low heat.
Remove and cool slightly.

title: butterscotch bars
directions: Combine butter, sugar and brown sugar.
Beat well.
Add egg yolks and vanilla.
Beat well.
Stir in oats, 1/2 cup of nuts and coconut.
Spread onto lightly greased 15 1/2 x 10 1/2 x 1-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: quick apple cake
directions: Mix eggs, oil and sugar.
In a separate bowl, mix all dry ingredients (flour, salt, soda, cinnamon and baking powder).
Add to egg mixture and mix well.
Fold in nuts and apples (mixture will be thick).
Spread in a greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Sprinkle chips on top. Bake at 350° for 35 minutes or until cake tests done.

title: spiced peach halves
directions: To syrup, add brown sugar, vinegar and spices tied in cheesecloth bag.
Simmer for 10 minutes.
Pour spiced syrup over peaches, along with bagged spices.
Let stand overnight in refrigerator.
Heat and serve hot the next day.
Discard bagged spices.
Serves 15.

title: broccoli cornbread
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Bake in iron skillet at 350° for 30 minutes or until done.

title: honey nut cookie balls
directions: Cream butter, powdered sugar and honey together thoroughly. Add flour, salt, vanilla and nuts.
Blend well.
Form into balls about 1-inch in diameter and chill.
Place 2 1/2 inches apart on a greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 375° for 10 to 15 minutes.
While still warm, roll in powdered sugar.
Cool; roll again in powdered sugar.
Freeze well.
Makes 4 dozen.

title: cheesy broiled appetizers
directions: Mix cheese, Bac*Os, mayo, pickles and onion.
Spread about 1 tablespoon over each slice bread.
Place on cookie sheet and broil in oven at 500° until cheese is melted (1 to 2 minutes).
Makes about 20 appetizers.

title: swedish rye
directions: Heat first 5 ingredients (water or milk, oil, molasses, brown sugar and salt) to 110° to 120°.
Blend in anise, orange peel, yeast and rye flour.
Let rest 5 minutes. Add 4 cups flour and let rest a few minutes before kneading on floured surface.
Knead about 5 minutes.
Place in greased bowl. Turn greased side up, cover and let rise in warm place about 45 to 60 minutes.
Punch down. Divide into 2 loaves.
Shape and place in bread pans.
Let rise until double in size (45 to 60 minutes).
Bake in a 350° oven for 45 to 50 minutes.
(It will sound hollow when lightly tapped.) Brush warm loaves with butter or margarine.

title: jello delight
directions: Dissolve Jell-O in hot water; mix well and then add ice cream. Stir until blended.

title: sweet potato casserole
directions: Bake at 350° until brown.

title: steak supper in foil
directions: Heat oven to 450°.
Place 24x18 inch piece of heavy duty foil in baking pan.
Place meat on foil.
Stir together mushroom soup and onion soup mix.
Spread on top of meat.
Top with vegetables and sprinkle water on top.
Fold foil and seal securely.
Cook 1 1/2 hours.

title: mexican skillet chicken and rice
directions: Coat chicken with chili powder.
Heat oil in 10-inch skillet over medium-high heat.
Add chicken; stir-fry 4 minutes or until tender.
Add salsa and water; bring to full boil.
Stir in rice. Reduce heat; cover and simmer 5 minutes.
Top with cheese; cover. Remove from heat; let stand 5 minutes.
Sprinkle with onion. Makes 4 servings.

title: beef jerky
directions: Put steak in freezer for about half an hour, just until firm. Slice steak across grain about 1/4-inch thick.
Combine remaining ingredients and marinate steak strips in this for at least 2 hours.
Place slices on rack in pan and dry in oven at 150° for 12 hours.

title: banana bread(very low-fat)
directions: Applesauce tends to give a "time-released" moistness to these bars. Simmons writes that the flavor and texture actually improve upon standing. Walnuts can be substituted in this recipe.

title: fluffy dressing
directions: Mix thoroughly all ingredients except butter and milk.
Add butter slowly.
Then add some milk.
Toss lightly, but do not let dressing become soggy as the turkey will add considerable juice to the stuffing.
Stuff turkey and roast in 325° oven.
Cover with foil and then the lid.

title: biscochitos(biss ko cheat ohs)
directions: Sift flour, baking powder and salt together. Cream shortening. When fluffy, add sugar and beat until creamy.

Add eggs and anise. Mix with the first mixture; add brandy or water. Use only enough to form a stiff dough. Knead a little; roll or pat out 1/2 to 1/4 inch thick. Cut in fancy shapes. Dust top of cookies with mixture of 1/4 cup sugar and 1 tablespoon cinnamon. Place on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes or until lightly brown. Yields 5 1/2 dozen cookies.

title: turtle cake
directions: Melt caramels with 1/3 cup evaporated milk (over low flames). Mix cake mix and butter together.
Grease a 9 x 13 x 2-inch cake pan.
Pat half of the cake mixture in a greased cake pan.
Bake at 350° for 6 minutes.
Remove from oven and spread the melted caramel mixture over the cake layer.

Sprinkle 1/2 cup of nuts and 1 cup of chocolate chips over caramel layer, then drop remaining cake mixture by spoonfuls over the nuts and chocolate chips. Sprinkle 1/2 cup of nuts on top and bake for 20 more minutes.

title: red, white and blue delight
directions: Dissolve 1 package of jello (red) in 2 cups hot water; pour into 9 x 13-inch pan.
Chill until firm.
Soften unflavored gelatin in 1/2 cup cold water.
Place sugar and half and half in saucepan; bring to boiling point.
Do not boil.
Remove from heat; add softened gelatin and cream cheese.
Beat at low speed until smooth.
Add nuts; let cool.
Pour over firm red jello layer.
Chill until firm.
Dissolve remaining red jello in 1 cup hot water; add blueberries and juice.
Let cool and pour over cheese layer; chill until firm.

title: marinated salad
directions: Steam carrots, corn and beans until carrots are just cooked. Transfer to a bowl with other salad ingredients.

title: broccoli cornbread
directions: Mix well and pour into 13 x 9-inch pan and bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until done brown.

title: pink cloud pineapple salad
directions: Drain crushed pineapple and place in mixing bowl.
Add red jello to pineapple and mix.
Add cottage cheese and mix well.
Add Cool Whip and mix all with spoon.
Do not add the pineapple juice or any water to this salad.
Place in a large bowl and refrigerate.
Salad will keep well for about 1 week.

title: icebox rolls
directions: Heat milk to lukewarm.
Add sugar and shortening.
Mix yeast with 1 cup of flour.
Add to warm milk mixture.
Add 5 cups of flour; mix well.
Batter will be thin.
Let set for 1 hour. Mixture will rise.
Add baking powder, soda and salt to the 2 1/2 cups of flour; stir into the risen mixture.
Store in refrigerator overnight.
Remove dough.
Roll, cut and dip in melted butter. Let rise and bake.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Combine 1/2
cup
water,
yeast
and honey.
Set aside. Blend cashews,
honey and water until smooth.
Stir into yeast mixture. Add
remaining ingredients and mix well.
Spoon into floured loaf pan and let rise 30 minutes.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 60 minutes. Let
stand
5 minutes in pan.
Remove and cool on rack.
Makes 1 loaf.

title: tapioca salad
directions: I add some chopped celery.

title: root beer float
directions: Put ice cream in a tall glass.
Fill glass with root beer. Makes 1 serving.

title: pork chop supper
directions: Trim fat from chops.
Cook trimmings in skillet until 2 tablespoons of fat accumulates.
Discard trimmings. Brown chops slowly in hot drippings.
Set chops aside.
Reserve drippings.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Boil broccoli as directed until tender.
Drain and pour into buttered casserole dish.
Mix other ingredients and pour over broccoli and mix well. Top or cover completely with bread crumbs or Ritz crackers.
Dot with butter.
Bake at 375° for 30 minutes, covered. Uncover and cook 10 minutes more.

title: icebox fruitcake
directions: Melt marshmallows in margarine and milk over low heat or in microwave. Crush graham crackers and mix with chopped fruit, nuts and coconut. Pour in liquid mixture and combine with hands until fruit is evenly distributed. Pack into Bundt or tube pan. Refrigerate at least 2 days before cutting.

title: liane's scotch bars
directions: Combine flour, baking powder, baking soda and salt (add nuts if desired).
Melt butter in saucepan or microwave.
Add brown sugar and hot water.
Mix well and cool slightly.
Add egg to butter and sugar mixture.
Next add vanilla and flour mixture.
Mix well and spread in a 7 x 11-inch pan.
Sprinkle chocolate bits over top and bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.
Cool in pan.

title: mock "hot sausages"
directions: Cut hot dogs into quarters.
Combine ingredients and bring to a boil.
Add hot dogs and simmer for 30 minutes.
Cover and let stand 2 to 4 days in refrigerator.

title: country style steak
directions: Brown steak in oil in skillet and remove.
Add flour to hot oil in skillet; add salt and brown flour.
Pour in water and add remaining ingredients, stirring to mix well.
Bring mixture to a boil and cook for 2 minutes or so.
Place steak in slow cooker which has been heated to 250° and pour flour mixture over steak. Put lid on cooker and simmer for 2 hours, or until tender.

title: tasty toffee cheesecake
directions: Preheat oven to 350 degrees.

Slice the cookie dough into 24 slices and arrange on the bottom and the sides of a 9 inch deep dish pie plate that has been coated with non-stick baking spray. Press the dough together, making a uniform crust; set aside.
In a large bowl, with an electric mixer on medium speed, beat the cream cheese, eggs, sugar and vanilla for 1 minute until well mixed. Stir in the candy pieces and pour into the pie plate.
Bake for 40-45 minutes, until the center is firm.
Remove from the oven and allow to cool.
Cover loosely, then chill for at least 4 hours, or overnight.

title: date-nut bread
directions: Chop dates; sprinkle soda over dates.
Pour boiling water over dates and soda; add butter and sugar.
Let cool.
Add flour, eggs, nuts and vanilla.
Pour into buttered loaf pan.
Bake at 325° for 30 minutes.
Raise temperature to 350° and bake until toothpick comes out clean.
Freezes well.

title: brown beef and dumplings
directions: If the beef is very lean, as the butcher for a piece of fat the size of a large egg.
In a heavy bottom pot or roaster, brown the beef and fat together.
Keep turning it over and over until it's quite brown.
Add 2 or more quarts of water and salt (to your taste) and cook until done.
You may have to keep adding water all through the cooking.
If potatoes are desired, add them to the pot just before the beef is done.
Remove the beef and potatoes from pot.
For a family of 4, you will need 3 to 4 quarts of broth. Add dumplings to boiling broth and cook until tender.

title: baked eggplant(yields 4 servings)
directions: Pare eggplant and cut into 1/4-inch cubes.
Sprinkle with pepper, dredge with flour, dip into egg and then into crumbs. Place into casserole, dot with butter and bake in slow oven (325°) about one hour.

title: lime salad
directions: Dissolve gelatin in 2 cups boiling water.
Mash cream cheese in small bowl.
Add hot gelatin mixture and stir until dissolved. Melt marshmallows in 1/4 cup boiling water in top of double boiler and add gelatin mixture.
Add 1 1/2 cups cold water.

title: chocolate eclair cake
directions: Mix the pudding with the milk and the Cool Whip.
Line the 9 x 13-inch pan with the crackers.
Pour half of mixture over crackers.
Put another layer of crackers.
Pour the rest of the pudding mixture over the crackers.
Then put another layer of crackers.
Then spread chocolate frosting over the top and put in fridge overnight.

title: creamy baked cheesecake
directions: Preheat oven to 300°.
Combine graham cracker crumbs, sugar and margarine; press on bottom of 9-inch spring-form pan.
In a mixer bowl, beat cream cheese until fluffy.
Gradually beat in sweetened condensed milk until smooth.
Add eggs and lemon juice; mix well.
Pour into prepared pan.
Bake 50 to 55 minutes until center is set; top with sour cream.
Bake 5 to 10 minutes longer; cool and chill.
Top with pie filling.
Refrigerate.

title: peaches for fried pies
directions: Add sugar and vinegar, using a large heavy container.
Cook, stirring constantly.
(For smaller amounts, sweeten to taste, and a small amount of vinegar.)
Cook until thick enough to spread on dough for pies.
This freezes well or may be canned.

title: mexican corn dip
directions: Mix together and serve with corn chips.

title: watermelon rind pickles(year 1917)
directions: Remove all pink pulp from watermelon rind.
Peel outside peeling from the rind.
Weigh.
Cut in 1-inch circles or cubes. Combine cold water and lime; pour over rind.
Let stand 1 hour. Drain.
Cover with fresh cold water.
Simmer 1 1/2 hours or until tender.
Drain.

title: apple tortillas
directions: Place apples on tortillas and roll. Place in 9x13 pyrex dish. Bring water, sugar, margarine and cinnamon to a boil. Pour over tortillas. Bake at 350 degrees for 40 minutes.

title: fresh strawberry pie
directions: Combine sugar, water and cornstarch.
Cook until slightly thickened.
Add jello and cool.
Fold in strawberries and pour into pie shell.
Refrigerate.
Serve topped with whipped cream or ice cream.

title: seven layer beef casserole
directions: Sprinkle rice and corn with salt and pepper.
Pour over 1 can tomato sauce and one can water.
Add onion, green pepper and meat.
Sprinkle salt and pepper.
Pour over other can of tomato sauce and 1/4 can water.
Place strips of bacon on top.

title: cheesy potato skins
directions: Cut potatoes in half lengthwise.
Scoop out centers, leaving 1/4-inch shell.
Fry shell in deep hot oil, 2 to 3 minutes or until golden brown.
Drain.

title: apple crisp
directions: Butter 10x10 casserole dish.
Arrange apples in dish.
In a separate bowl, mix sugar, flour, baking powder and egg until crumbly.
Spread this over apples, put on pads of butter and spices.
Bake @ 350 degrees for 30 minutes.

title: west coast chowder
directions: In a 3-quart glass casserole, microwave on High the bacon and onion for 3 to 4 minutes.
Add potatoes, clam liquid and water; microwave on High 15 to 18 minutes, stirring every 4 minutes.
Add clams and milk and salt and pepper to taste.
Microwave on High 5 minutes, stirring twice.
Rest 5 minutes.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: apple crisp
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Butter a 9-inch glass pie plate. Arrange apples in pie plate, mounding them in center.
Pour orange juice over apples.
In bowl combine sugar, flour, cinnamon, nutmeg and salt.
Cut in butter until mixture resembles coarse crumbs. Sprinkle over apples.
Bake 45 to 55 minutes until topping is browned and apples are tender.

title: three corn casserole
directions: Drain whole kernel corn.
Mix oleo, sour cream, and egg. Stir in all corn.
Stir in muffin mix.
Pour into a well greased 8 x 8 casserole dish.
Bake at 350 degrees for 1 hour, or until set.

title: ramona pockets
directions: Will also need 16 toothpicks.

title: lazy pie
directions: Mix dry ingredients together.
Add milk and vanilla.
Stir until smooth.
Melt margarine in pan, then pour in batter.
Put your favorite fruit on top.
Bake for 1 hour at 350° or until it turns light brown on top.

title: chocolate delight
directions: Mix and press in bottom of a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 300° for 25 minutes or until golden brown.
Let crust cool completely.

title: ham loaf
directions: Mix and shape into loaf.
Place in baking pan.

title: teddy bear bread(yields 2 bears)
directions: Scald milk.
Add sugar, salt and margarine.
Cool to lukewarm. Dissolve yeast in 1/2 cup warm water.
Add milk mixture and 3 cups unsifted flour.
Beat until smooth.

title: smashed potatoes
directions: Peel and cut potatoes.
Boil.
Drain.
Mash.
Add butter, cream cheese and egg.
Mix.
(Add optionals if you want.) Put in 9 x 13-inch glass dish.
Bake in 350° oven for 25 minutes.

title: old fashioned peanut brittle
directions: Combine sugar, syrup and water.
Cook until it comes to soft ball stage.
Add peanuts.
Cook until mixture turns dark.
Remove from heat; add soda, salt and vinegar.
Stir well and pour immediately onto cookie sheet that has been greased.
Cool.
Break into pieces.

title: fruity snow salad
directions: Soften gelatine in lemon juice over hot water.
Soften cream cheese.
Stir in mayonnaise, gelatine and fruit and pecans.
Whip the cream, adding sugar gradually.
Fold into fruit mixture. Chill until firm.

title: apple cheese salad with lemon dressing
directions: Place in a saucepan the sugar and cornstarch; mix.
Add the lemon juice, egg and water.
Cook until thick.
Cool and keep in the refrigerator until ready to use.
Add a few drops of yellow food color.
Use as a dressing over chopped apples and cheese cubes.

title: spinach cheese pie
directions: Mix together first 5 ingredients.
Grease a 9-inch pie plate. Line the plate with Muenster cheese.
Add the mixture.
Cover the mixture with Muenster cheese.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes or until top is golden.
Slice and serve warm.

title: dump cake
directions: Place in Dutch oven the can of peaches and juice.
Dump over the top the yellow or white cake mix. Stir enough to moisten cake mix.
Dot with butter.
Place coals on top and bottom of Dutch oven and bake for 45 minutes to 1 hour.

title: wolferman cake
directions: Cream shortening and sugar; add eggs and mix well.
Add sour cream alternately with dry ingredients.
Add vanilla and coffee. Grease and flour 9 x 14-inch pan; pour in batter and bake at 350° for 35 minutes.

title: taco dip
directions: Mix sour cream and taco seasoning; spread on a dinner plate. Layer all other ingredients on top of that.
Serve with nacho chips.

title: cocoa mix
directions: Combine all ingredients; mix well.
Store in airtight container.
To use, place 2 heaping teaspoonfuls of mix in cup. Add hot water and stir.

title: chicken and asparagus casserole
directions: Cook chicken in water with celery until tender.
Drain chicken and remove bone.
Shred chicken and place in bottom of dish.
Add soup and asparagus.
Bake at 350° until bubbly, then sprinkle cheese and bread crumbs over top.
Drizzle with butter and return to oven to brown.

title: quick chili-mac
directions: Scramble fry ground beef until browned; drain and set aside. Cook 1 box macaroni and cheese, following directions on box.
Add seasoning and hamburger to macaroni and cheese.
Mix well.
Dice up cheese and mix into other mixture.
Pour into baking dish and bake at 350°, covered, until cheese is melted.
Serves 8.
"Quick and delicious."

title: seasoned catfish
directions: Cook for 10 minutes in microwave, 5 minutes on each side; or broil in oven until center of fish is beginning to flake when tested with fork.

title: delmer shuck's meat loaf
directions: Mix all of the ingredients using enough stuffing mix to make meat mixture workable (about 1/2 to 3/4 cup).
Flatten mixture out on a cutting board and lay 8 slices of sandwich ham and 1 cup shredded Mozzarella cheese on top of meat mixture.
Roll up meat mix and layered ham and cheese tucking ends in so cheese won't melt out.
Wrap roll tightly in aluminum foil and bake at 350° to 375° for 45 minutes.
Uncover and bake another 15 minutes.
Add more barbecue sauce on top of roll during last of cooking time and serve more, warmed, on the side, if desired.

title: apple crisp
directions: Butter a 9 x 9-inch baking dish.
Fill pan 3/4 full with apples.
In a small bowl, beat the egg well.
Add 1 cup of sugar, flour and baking powder; mix well.
Spread over apples.
(Add lemon if not tart enough.)

title: easy cheesy buns
directions: This is a major family favorite that Mother has made for years. Good for at least a 3 pound weight gain!

title: russian tea mix
directions: Add 2 tablespoons to 1 cup hot water.

title: ricotta pancakes
directions: Mix together and cook just like regular pancakes.
(Very filling and good!)

title: bread crumb pudding
directions: Beat all together and pour in large flat glass dish.
Soak bread crumbs in cold water, then crumble.
Crumble bread fine and pour in pudding along with raisins.
Sprinkle nutmeg over top. Bake in 375° oven until done.

title: easy red velvet cake
directions: Combine first 7 ingredients until well blended.
Add soda and vinegar.
Beat 4 minutes at medium speed.
Pour into 3 greased and floured pans.
Bake in 325° oven for about 20 minutes.

title: cold vegetable salad
directions: Drain vegetables well and mix all ingredients.
Prepare the night before.

title: barbecue beef
directions: Cook meat until tender and shred into pieces.
Melt margarine. Add vinegar, then remaining ingredients.
Add 2 cups water or more for desired consistency.
Freezes well.

title: walnut cookies in a hurry
directions: Mix egg, sugar and vanilla. Sift dry ingredients and add to the first mix. When it's smooth, add the walnuts.
In a baking pan, 9 x 13-inch, pour the batter and bake for 25 minutes in a 375° oven until it gets brown but the center is still soft.
Cut into small pieces.
Makes 30 cookies.

title: taco salad
directions: Brown beef and drain.
Just before serving, add the beef and dressing to torn lettuce and grated cheese.

title: chicken barbecue sauce
directions: Mix thoroughly all ingredients.
No cooking or refrigeration is needed.
Makes 1/2 gallon, enough for 100 chicken halves.

title: uncooked cranberry relish
directions: Wash cranberries well and chop them. Chop oranges and add to cranberries; add orange juice and sugar. Mix well. Refrigerate 24 hours before serving. Yields about 4 cups.

title: banana split cake
directions: Prepare cake mix as directed.
Bake at 350° for 12 to 18 minutes in a 13 x 9-inch pan.
Cream together cream cheese, milk and pudding.
Spread mixture on top of cooled cake.
Cover with crushed pineapple.
Slice the bananas on top.
Frost with Cool Whip.
Sprinkle with nuts.
Garnish with cherries.
Store in refrigerator.

title: butter cookies
directions: Cream butter; add sugar.
Beat until fluffy.
Beat in eggs and extracts.
Gradually blend in flour.
Use pastry bag with large decorative tip.
Pipe dough about 2-inches apart on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake 10 to 12 minutes in 375° oven.
Yield:
3 to 3 1/2 dozen cookies.

title: broccoli rabe
directions: In boiling salted water, cook rabe 2 1/2 minutes, until crisp-tender; drain.

title: honey wheat bread
directions: Combine warm (not hot) milk, oil, honey, salt, yeast and half the flour; mix well.
Place dough in well greased bread 'n cake pan.
Cover and let stand for 5 minutes.
Place pan in crock-pot. Cover and bake on High for 2 to 3 hours.
Remove pan and uncover. Let stand for 5 minutes.
Unmold and serve warm.
Makes 1 loaf (for 3 1/2 or 5-quart crock-pot).

title: brownies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Spray or grease a 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking pan.
Mix cocoa, oil, sugar, eggs and vanilla in a large bowl.
Stir in remaining ingredients.
Spread in pan.
Bake 25 to 30 minutes or until brownies start to pull away from sides of pan. Do not overbake.
Cool slightly.
Cut into bars.
If desired, spread with your favorite chocolate frosting.
(For a low fat version of this recipe, substitute 2/3 cup applesauce in place of the oil; omit egg yolks and nuts.)

title: cheese puffs
directions: Melt first three ingredients in top of double boiler.
Fold stiffly beaten egg whites into cheese mixture.
Cut bread into 1-inch cubes.
Dip bread cubes into mixture and place on well-greased cookie sheet and freeze.
When frozen, place in plastic bags.
Bake, unthawed, at 400° for 15 minutes.

title: bread crumb molasses cake(1936)
directions: Put bacon fat into bowl and melt it by pouring boiling water over it.
Next, pour in molasses which has baking soda mixed in it.
Now add dried bread crumbs and raisins.
Now dump in whole wheat flour, salt, ginger and wheat germ.

title: cooked dressing for salads
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Cook until thickens.
Cool to lukewarm before using.

title: tart green beans with bacon
directions: Wash and cut off ends.
Cut green beans into crosswise pieces. Cook 15 to 20 minutes or until tender.
Frozen or canned may be substituted.
Follow directions on package or container for cooking.
Pan brown bacon.
Add to skillet the onion, vinegar, water, sugar, salt and pepper.
Bring to boil.
Simmer 30 minutes. Drain cooked green beans and toss lightly together.
Yields 4 servings.

title: egg custard
directions: Pour in unbaked pie crust. Bake at 350° until set or light brown.

title: strawberry-banana mold
directions: Dissolve gelatin in boiling water.
Add cold water and chill. Add sliced bananas and sliced strawberries.
Put Cool Whip over top and place some strawberries on top.

title: strawberry-rhubarb jam
directions: Cap and crush strawberries and slice the rhubarb thinly, but do not peel.
Place both (which should measure about 4 c.) into a kettle with Sure-Jell and bring to a hard boil.
If a fine consistency is desired, mash fruit as it is cooking.
Add sugar and orange rind and boil again for 2 to 3 minutes, stirring constantly.
Ladle into hot, sterilized jars.
Seal.
Yields 3 pints.

title: three-cheese ball
directions: Blend cheeses and
salad
dressing
in bowl.
Add onion and seasonings.
Shape into ball, wrap in plastic wrap.
Chill until serving time.
Roll in pecans (3 to 4 cups).

title: tortillas (corn meal pancakes)
directions: Combine corn meal, flour and salt.
With pastry blender or 2 knives, cut in shortening until well blended.
Stir in warm water and form mixture into a ball.
Knead on floured board until dough is no longer sticky.
Divide into 2 balls.
Cover and let rest 20 minutes.

title: lemon coconut dessert
directions: Cook the pudding mix (not instant) by recipe except add 1 lemon sliced to pudding while cooking.
Set aside egg whites.
When done, remove lemon and scrape off pudding.
Set aside lemon.
Mix in the coconut.
In Pyrex or Corning Ware baking pan, put vanilla wafers to cover bottom.
Cover these with layer of pudding and alternate with pudding and wafers until pudding is used up.
Beat egg whites left and add 1/4 cup sugar and 1/4 teaspoon cream of tartar.
Beat until stiff peaks form.
Cover pudding and put in oven until brown.

title: cucumber cottage cheese mold
directions: Peel and quarter cucumbers and remove seeds.
Grate cucumbers and strain, reserving juice and shreds.
Soften gelatin in cucumber juice and dissolve it over hot water.
Season with a little salt, onion salt, paprika and white pepper to taste.
Stir in grated cucumbers and let it get cold, but not set.
Fold in cottage cheese and mix well.
Wet mold in cold water.
Turn in mixture.
Chill 2 to 3 hours, until firm.
Unmold on cold platter.
Serve very cold with mayonnaise.

title: herb biscuit loaf
directions: In a shallow bowl, combine the first 5 ingredients. Dip biscuits in butter mixture; fold in half and place in rows in a greased 9-inch square baking pan. Drizzle with remaining butter mixture. Bake at 350° for 27 to 30 minutes or until golden brown. Yield: 8 to 10 servings.

title: dusti's brownies
directions: Melt butter or margarine.
Add to that the cocoa, sugar, eggs, flour, salt and vanilla.
Bake in a greased and floured pan at 350° for 15 minutes.
After 15 minutes if brownies are turning loose from sides of the pan, the brownies are done.

title: party punch
directions: Mix in the order given except ginger ale.
Do not dilute frozen lemonade.
Stir well until sugar is dissolved and lemonade is thawed.
Place in refrigerator to chill.
It will keep well for several days.
Just before serving, add cold ginger ale.
Serves 50 cups.

title: fruit salad
directions: Mix all ingredients except Cool Whip in a medium bowl.
Fold in the Cool Whip.
Chill in refrigerator for 1 hour before serving.

title: quick broccoli-cauliflower soup
directions: Let broccoli and cauliflower thaw if frozen and saute in butter.
Add soups, salt and pepper, milk and water.
Bring to a boil then simmer over low heat for approximately 30 minutes.

title: spanish rice
directions: Combine margarine and rice in pan.
Mix until rice is brown. Add the onion, cut in 4 pieces, for about 2 minutes.
Add tomatoes and stir for about 1 minute. Add garlic salt, salt and water. Stir until boiling. Cover and cook until water is gone and rice is done.

title: meat loaf
directions: Beat eggs slightly, add milk, salt, thyme, mustard and minced onion.
Now add ground chuck, bread crumbs and 1/2 of catsup.
Bake in 400° oven 35 to 40 minutes.
Add remaining 1/2 of catsup 5 minutes before taking out of oven.

title: boston baked beans
directions: Cook until water is gone. Put in oven at 325° for 20 minutes. Can use red food coloring, if desired.

title: brilliant raspberry dip
directions: Blend together all ingredients with mixer.
Refrigerate.
Dip apples, bananas, pears and pretzels.

title: belgian beef stew
directions: Combine flour, salt and pepper, coat meat.
In a large dutch oven, sautee onions and garlic in hot oil until onions are clear and tender.
Remove onions and set aside.
Add meat to oil and brown well on all sides.
Return onions to pan and add beer, Worchestire sauce, steak sauce, bay leaves and thyme.
Bring to a boil, reduce heat and simmer, covered, about 2 hours.
Add potatoes, simmer until done.

title: sourdough starter
directions: Dissolve yeast in 1/2 cup warm water; let stand 5 minutes. Combine flour, sugar and salt in a medium size nonmetal bowl and stir well.
Gradually stir in 2 cups warm water.
Add yeast mixture and mix well.
Cover starter loosely with plastic wrap or cheesecloth; let stand in warm place for 72 hours, stirring 2 or 3 times a day.
Place fermented mixture in refrigerator.
Stir once a day and use within 11 days.

title: pecan crispies
directions: Cream shortening and sugar; add eggs.
Sift together dry ingredients and add to creamed mixture.
Add pecans and vanilla.

title: hashed brown casserole
directions: Mix together first 7 ingredients and add 1/2 cup of the melted oleo.
Spread mixture in 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish.
Combine rest of melted oleo and cornflakes and top mixture.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: banana split delight
directions: Mix together and press into buttered 11 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° until lightly golden. Do not overbake (approximately 10 minutes).
Let cool.

title: randy travis' fried catfish
directions: Mix flour, meal, salt and pepper.
Dip fish in milk and then dredge in flour mix.
Fry fillets 1 1/2 minutes on each side.

title: broccoli casserole(serves 6 to 8)
directions: Cook broccoli until tender-crisp; drain well.
Combine all of ingredients, except stuffing mix.
Pour into 9 x 13-inch buttered casserole.
Sprinkle top with stuffing mix.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes or until set.

title: hawaiian pie
directions: Beat sugar, eggs, flour and Karo together.
Stir in remainder of ingredients and pour into unbaked pie shell.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: beef stew
directions: Combine all ingredients in a heavy pan.
Cover and bake at 300° for 3 to 3 1/2 hours or at 250° for 3 1/2 to 5 hours. Thicken with 2 tablespoons cornstarch, mixed with 1/2 cup water a few minutes before serving.

title: orange cupcakes
directions: Dissolve baking soda in buttermilk.
Mix ingredients together and bake at 350°.

title: oooh la la potatoes
directions: Cook potatoes in skins; cool and peel.
Crumble with a fork. Combine cheese and 4 tablespoons butter in a large saucepan.
Heat and stir until cheese is almost melted.
Remove from heat and blend sour cream, onions, salt and pepper.
Fold in potatoes. Spoon into a 2-quart dish.
Dot with 2 tablespoons butter.
Cover and bake for 25 minutes or until bubbly.

title: little reubens
directions: Unroll crescent rolls.
Place a small portion of all ingredients onto rolls.
Roll crescents up and bake according to directions on package (bake on cookie sheet).
Don't overstuff crescent rolls.

title: impossible garden pie
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
Lightly grease 10-inch pie plate. Sprinkle first 4 ingredients in pie plate.
Beat remaining ingredients until smooth, 15 seconds in blender.
Pour into plate. Bake until golden brown, about 30 minutes, or until knife inserted comes out clean.

title: strawberry parfaits
directions: In 8 (8-ounce) parfait glasses, or any tall glass, spoon 1 tablespoon chocolate syrup, 1 rounded tablespoonful vanilla ice cream, 1 rounded tablespoonful strawberry preserves, 1/4 cup strawberry ice cream and 1 tablespoon marshmallow sauce.
Top each one with 1 scoop vanilla ice cream, then drizzle each with 1 tablespoon chocolate syrup.
Place in freezer.
Mix whipped cream with confectioners sugar.
Decorate each parfait with whipped cream and cherries.
Serve chilled.

title: sour cream potatoes
directions: Peel and slice potatoes 1/4 inch thick.
Combine remaining ingredients.
Place layer of potatoes in 3 layers in pan and spread each layer with 1/3 sauce.
Bake until potatoes are done (30 minutes to check).
Bake at 250°.

title: chicken pot pie
directions: Dice chicken breasts into a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Mix broth with soup.
Pour over chicken.
Add can of carrots and peas without liquid.
Mix Bisquick with milk; pour over all.
Drizzle melted margarine over top.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour and 15 minutes.
Good carry out dish.

title: easy whole wheat bread
directions: Mix dry ingredients.
Stir in milk and molasses and mix thoroughly.
Pour into bread pan and let stand for 1 hour.
Bake at 325° for about 1 hour.

title: yellow cake
directions: Beat the first 4 ingredients for 2 minutes with mixer.
Pour into a greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake for 30 minutes at 350°.
Mix undrained pineapple, pudding mix and Cool Whip together.
Spread on cooled cake.
Refrigerate.

title: scalloped chicken
directions: Cook chicken until done.
Cool.
Debone chicken into coarse pieces.
Mix all ingredients.
Bake in 9 x 13-inch dish 35 to 40 minutes or until done in 350° oven.

title: half-a-pound-cake
directions: Put all ingredients in a large bowl and beat together on medium speed for 20 minutes.
Pour the batter into a well greased 10-inch tube pan and place in a cold oven.
Set the temperature to 350°F. 180°c. gas mark 4 and bake for just 1 hour.

Remove the cake from the oven, immediately invert onto a wire rack and tip it out, if it sticks in the pan, gently loosen the sides with a sharp knife and give the cake pan a good whack(!?!) on the countertop to shake the cake loose!
Cool completely before serving.
Serves 10-12.

title: one dish casserole
directions: Layer all ingredients in baking dish.
Cover with foil.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Garnish with parsley flakes or paprika.

title: lucky cake
directions: Mix and spread over 2nd layer.
Spread remaining Cool Whip over cake.
"Delicious."
Refrigerate.

title: beef ball
directions: Mix all ingredients together well.
Form into a ball. Refrigerate to harden.

title: chocolate trifle
directions: Cut angel food cake into 1-inch squares.
Sprinkle with 3/4 cup Kahlua and set aside.
Mix chocolate fudge instant pudding.
Take frozen Skor candy bars and smash them into small pieces.

title: nibbles
directions: Add 1/2 teaspoon baking soda and stir well until foamy.
Pour hot syrup into popped corn in bag and stir with wooden spoon.

title: cranberry bars
directions: Mix all ingredients together at once. Bake in greased and floured 9 x 13 tin at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes. Put powdered sugar frosting over this.

title: spinach fluff
directions: Combine 1 package spinach and 1 cup milk in container of electric blender; puree.
Add remaining spinach; blend until smooth.
Add remaining milk, eggs, soup, butter, salt and Accent. Blend well.
Stir in onion juice, garlic juice and cheese.
Pour mixture into well-greased shallow 2-quart casserole.
Bake in preheated 325° oven for 1 hour or until inserted knife comes out clean!

title: pecan pie
directions: Mix all ingredients in a 1 1/2-quart bowl.
Pour into a 9-inch pie pan with unbaked pastry. Bake near center of a 375° oven for about 50 minutes or until firm.
Cool before serving.
Walnuts or pecans can be used.

title: sweet potato pie
directions: Combine first 7 ingredients and spices in bowl; mix until smooth.
Pour into pie shell.
Sprinkle with additional nutmeg. Bake at 425° for 15 minutes.
Reduce temperature to 375° and bake for 30 minutes.
Yield:
6 servings.

title: five hour stew
directions: Put stew beef in center of roasting pan.
Place vegetables around meat.
Mix together the soup, water and spices; pour over beef and vegetables.
Sprinkle approximately 3 tablespoons instant tapioca over stew.
Bake at 250° for 5 hours.
Keep cover on roaster while cooking.
Stir and serve.

title: cream cheese bars
directions: Mix thoroughly with spoon and press in 9 x 12-inch cake pan that has been greased with Pam or shortening.

title: easy chicken casserole
directions: Put chicken in a 9 x 13-inch pan. Combine soups and broth and mix well. Pour on top of chicken. Spread Pepperidge Farm stuffing on top of chicken and soup and put butter on top. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: broccoli bread
directions: Mix.
Bake for 35 to 40 minutes at 375°.

title: eastern north carolina pork barbecue
directions: Place pork fat-side down on an unheated broiler pan rack.
Cook in a 350° oven for 40 to 50 minutes per pound or until internal temperature measures 185°.
(Or place meat in a crockery cooker and add 1/2 cup water.
Cover; cook on low heat setting 10 to 12 hours or high heat setting 5 to 6 hours.)

title: lazy pierogi
directions: In a large skillet, melt butter; add onion, pepper and garlic powder.
Saute 5 minutes.
Rinse sauerkraut well and drain.
Add to butter and onion mixture.
Mix well.
Add water and simmer 20 minutes.
Boil noodles.
Drain and add to sauerkraut.
Mix well; simmer, covered, until ready to serve.

title: fall festival "no peep" stew
directions: Cube and mix together meat and vegetables. Season to taste with salt, pepper and seasoned salt.
Place in Dutch oven. Gradually add V-8 juice to flour.
Add water and pour over meat and vegetables.
Stir to coat pieces. Cover.
Bake 5 hours at 250°.
Serve with wedges of your favorite cornbread and green salad.
Yields 6 to 8 servings.

title: rice pudding(crock-pot style)
directions: Put milk, rice, salt and sugar in the crock-pot.
Cook on high for 30 minutes.
Stir.
Cook another 30 minutes.
Stir. Meanwhile, beat eggs; add evaporated milk, vanilla and vanilla pudding.
Add this to rice in the crock-pot.
You may add raisins if you desire; also some cinnamon and nutmeg to taste.
Cook another 20 to 30 minutes.

title: engagement pound cake
directions: Cream margarine.
Gradually add 10x sugar.
Cream well.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each.
Blend in vanilla. Sift together flour, cornstarch, salt and baking powder.
Add milk alternately with the dry ingredients to creamed mixture, beginning and ending with dry ingredients.
Blend thoroughly after each addition.

title: venison stroganoff
directions: Cut venison into 1 1/2 x 1/2-inch strips; place in deep plate. Sprinkle with lemon juice, oil and pepper.
Cover; let stand 30 minutes.
Fry onion in butter until golden brown.
Remove; add meat.
Fry over high heat, turning often.
Add mushrooms, if desired.
Mix flour, sour cream, tomato puree and salt; pour over heat.
Simmer over low fire until sauce is thick and meat is tender, about 10 minutes or longer, if desired.
(After meat is browned, this may all be added to crock-pot and simmered on low rather than cooking on stove, if desired.)

title: coconut cake
directions: Make a layer cake.
Mix ingredients in mixing bowl.
Pour over hot cake layers and put coconut on top.
Let cool and spread Cool Whip on top.
Sprinkle fresh or frozen coconut over top of cake.

title: george washington cherry pie
directions: In a bowl, whip cream.
Add sugar.
In large, square deep dish, layer wafers with cherries (cut in half) with a little of the cherry juice.
Cover layer with whipped cream.
Layer until all wafers, cherries and whipped cream are used, ending with whipped cream on top.
Refrigerate.

title: shallot sauce for oysters
directions: In a small bowl, combine all the ingredients and chill.
Serve with raw oysters on the half shell.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Saute bell pepper and onion in butter.
Mix all other ingredients with already boiled curly roni.
Add one can of water. Stir in bell pepper and onion. Slice Velveeta and lay on top of mixture.
Preheat oven to 400°.
Bake until cheese is melted, about 25 to 30 minutes.

title: granola cookies
directions: Mix all wet ingredients.
Stir flour, soda and salt together. Combine with first mixture.
Stir in granola and optional chocolate chips.
Drop by teaspoons on ungreased cookie sheet and bake at 300° for 20 minutes.

title: broccoli salad
directions: Fry bacon; crumble.
Break broccoli into small flowers and stems.
Chop onion.
Mix broccoli, bacon, raisins and onions.
Mix mayonnaise, vinegar and sugar.
Toss together and serve.
If preparing ahead of time, don't add bacon until serving time.

title: bread pudding
directions: In large bowl, soak bread in milk, water, sugar and vanilla. Let stand 1 hour, stirring occasionally.
Preheat oven to 350°. Grease 13 x 9-inch baking dish.
Add raisins, fruit cocktail, coconut and melted butter.
Beat eggs well and add to mixture, mixing in well by hand.
Pour into baking dish.
Bake 1 hour. Makes 12 to 16 servings.

title: easy mexican chicken fiesta
directions: Prepare Rice-A-Roni as
directed.
Cut
up chicken into bite size pieces.
Saute
onion
and pepper in 1 teaspoon oil. Add tomatoes, chicken, sauteed vegetables and rice mixture.

title: pear butter
directions: Process or grind pears.
Add sugar and let stand for 2 hours. Add pineapple and lemon juice.
Cook until thickened, approximately two or more hours.
Put into sterilized jars. Yields approximately 8 to 12 pints.

title: hawaiian cream cake
directions: Grease and flour a 10 x 15-inch jelly roll pan.
Prepare cake as directed on box.
Pour on pan and bake.
Let it cool for 20 to 30 minutes.
Mix pudding with cold milk and cream cheese.
Spread on cake, then pineapple.
Spread Cool Whip over pineapple.
On top of Cool Whip, spread coconut and walnuts.
Refrigerate until ready to serve.

title: ruby's chocolate pie
directions: Mix well; pour into uncooked pie shell.
Bake at 400° for 30 minutes.

title: heavenly hash
directions: Put gelatine
in
cold	water to dissolve.
Add to milk and heat, but do not boil.
Stir constantly until all gelatine is dissolved.	Then
add
1 1/2 cups sugar.
Let cool until it begins to	thicken.
Add pineapple.
Whip cream and add 1/2 to gelatine mixture.
Color
pink
or
green.
Top with remaining whipped cream.
Makes a lot.

title: cheese ball
directions: Mix together; chill, then mold and roll in chopped nuts. Serve on your favorite crackers.

title: pea and asparagus casserole
directions: Put a thin layer of crushed crackers in bottom of a 2-quart Pyrex dish.
Put peas in next, then asparagus and pimento.
Tear cheese into small pieces and place next.
Pour soup on top. Sprinkle with remaining crackers.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
