title: quick and easy casserole
directions: Put raw hamburger or chicken in bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan. Cover with a layer of stuffing mix.
Pour soups over stuffing mix; milk over soups.
Top with Tater Tots.
Cover with foil.
Bake at 350° for 1 to 1 1/2 hours.

title: chicken cheese ball
directions: Have cheese at room temperature; mix onions and celery with cheese.
Add chicken; put in mixer or blender.
Mix well.
When well mixed, form ball and roll in chopped nuts.
Refrigerate until the cheese is well chilled.

title: party potatoes
directions: Thaw potatoes slightly so they are easier to stir.
In a large bowl, combine all ingredients.
Reserve enough cheese to cover the top of casserole.
Put mixture into a greased 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan; spread remaining cheese on top.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 60 minutes.
Can also be prepared in crock-pot.

title: shrimp provencal
directions: Saute onions in olive oil;
add tomatoes that have been peeled,
cut
and
seeded,	bay leaves, garlic and 2 teaspoons sugar or
to
taste.
Cook	about
1/2 hour; add shrimp, salt, pepper and water and cook about 5 minutes.	Transfer to baking dish;
sprinkle
Feta cheese over shrimp and bake until cheese melts (approximately 10 minutes at 375°).

title: graham cracker squares
directions: Mix brown sugar, margarine and milk in saucepan.
Bring to a boil for 2 minutes; cool.
Mix pecans, coconut and graham crackers and spread mixture between graham crackers.
Mix confectioners sugar and water together for icing and spread on top of crackers and sprinkle with crumbs.

title: spinach salad
directions: The first 5 ingredients are your salad.
Be creative; add or delete any ingredient you want.

title: "leave it to beaver" brownies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease 9 x 13-inch baking pan with vegetable oil spray or butter.
In large saucepan, melt sticks of butter, margarine and baking chocolate over low heat.
Turn off heat.
Stir in sugar.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating until blended.
Stir in flour and vanilla.
Stir in nuts.
Pour into baking dish.
Sprinkle with chocolate chips to garnish.
Bake 30 minutes.
Cool before cutting.

title: harry's favorite peanut butter cookies
directions: Combine flour, baking powder and oats in one bowl.
In another bowl, beat butter and sugar until you form a grainy paste.
Blend in peanut butter, honey, eggs and vanilla.
Add flour mixture, raisins and chocolate chips until combined.
Do not overmix.

title: lettuce dressing
directions: Bring first 5 ingredients to boil, stirring all the time. Add milk.

title: hamburger noodle casserole
directions: Brown meat and onion; drain. Cook noodles until tender; drain. Add remainder of ingredients, except bread and margarine. Combine meat and noodles and remainder of ingredients. Pour into casserole dish. Melt butter, then add light bread crumbs. Sprinkle on top of casserole. Bake at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes.

title: gilda's coffee brownies
directions: Mix (in a large bowl) first 8 ingredients in order, with a spoon.
Pour into a 9 x 13-inch greased cake pan.
Sprinkle one 16 ounce package chocolate chips and nuts on top.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 45 minutes or until well done in middle.
Cool and cut in squares.

title: nutty cheese bars
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease and flour 9 x 13-inch baking pan.
Stir in a medium bowl until well mixed the dry cake mix, butter and 1/2 of the pecans.
Press evenly into bottom of pan. Stir in a medium bowl with a spoon until well mixed the brown sugar and cream cheese.
Spread evenly over mix in pan.
Sprinkle over other 1/2 pecans.
Bake 25 to 30 minutes or until edges are browned and cheese topping is set.
Cool before cutting.
Store in refrigerator in an airtight container.

title: fruit cobbler
directions: Place fruit in bottom of a 9 x 9-inch pan.
In a medium bowl, mix dry ingredients; cut in margarine.
Mix in egg with fork. Sprinkle over fruit.
Bake 25 minutes at 425°.

title: marinated pork tenderloin
directions: Place pork tenderloins in a plastic bag.
Add remaining ingredients.
Seal bag and refrigerate for 1 hour or overnight. Broil about 6 inches from heat.
Baste with remaining marinade. Broil for 5 to 10 minutes, turning once and basting.
(Do not overcook; it will be tough.)

title: chili-chicken stew
directions: Cut chicken into 1-inch square.
Cook chicken, onion, chopped green pepper and garlic in hot oil in a Dutch oven until lightly browned.
Add tomatoes, pinto beans, picante sauce, chili powder, cumin and salt; cover, reheat and simmer 20 minutes.
Top individual servings with Cheddar cheese, sour cream and onion. Yield: 6 servings.

title: authentic chicken enchiladas
directions: Preheat oven to 300°.
Mix chicken, onion, cheese and seasonings in a bowl.
Heat oil in a frying pan.
The oil should be at least 1/4 inch deep.
Roll a portion of the chicken mixture into a corn tortilla, and using tongs, place the rolled tortilla into the hot oil.
Fry on both sides until the tortilla is crisp.
Set the crisped enchilada aside in a shallow baking dish.
Repeat until mixture (or tortillas) are gone.
Cover with enchilada sauce and bake for 1/2 hour at 300°.

title: spinach balls
directions: Cook and drain spinach well.
Cool.
Beat eggs.
Combine all ingredients.
Shape into 1 inch balls.
Bake 10 minutes at 350°. Can be made ahead and refrigerated overnight.
Makes 40 + balls.

title: carrot cake
directions: Beat first 3 ingredients together.
Add remaining ingredients. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes or longer in loaf pan.

title: date drops
directions: Empty contents of both envelopes of date bar mix into mixer bowl.
Add cinnamon, hot water and slightly beaten egg.
Mix well, using low speed.
Add nutmeats and cherries.
Drop by teaspoonfuls on greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 375° for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: fancy cake
directions: Mix cake mix according to directions on package.
Bake in a greased and floured 9 x 13-inch pan as directed on package.
Cool cake.
Spread pineapple on top.

title: garlic cheese biscuits
directions: Sift dry ingredients together 3 times.
Add shredded cheese. Cut shortening until well blended.
Add milk to make a soft dough, then add garlic powder.
Turn out on a lightly floured board.
Roll into 1/2-inch thickness.
Cut with biscuit cutter or into squares with a knife.
Place in a baking sheet and bake at 425° (hot oven) for 12 to 15 minutes.
Makes 12 (2-inch) biscuits.

title: cabbage casserole
directions: Shred cabbage and thinly slice onion.
Cook until tender and drain.
In a greased casserole baking dish, layer cabbage and onion, then chicken soup.
Cover with thinly sliced Velveeta cheese and repeat.
Repeat until ingredients are used.
Top with bread or cracker crumbs.
Bake 35 minutes at 350°.

title: oven-fried vegetables
directions: Spray a cold baking sheet with nonstick spray coating.
Set aside.
Stir together bread crumbs, Parmesan cheese and paprika in a 9-inch pie plate until well mixed.

title: chocolate pound cake
directions: Cream butter and shortening in large mixing bowl.
Add sugar and blend until creamy.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each.
Sift dry ingredients together.
Add to egg mixture alternately with milk, mixing well after each addition.
Add vanilla.
Pour into greased and floured (cocoa can be used in place of flour) tube pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour and 20 minutes. Cool.
Remove from pan.
Top with chocolate icing, if desired.

title: dried beef cheese ball
directions: Combine cream cheese, 1 package of finely chopped dried beef and the other ingredients.
Mix well. Form into ball.
Roll ball in remaining chopped beef. Chill. Serve with crackers.

title: sweet and sour kosher pickles
directions: Boil sugar, vinegar, mustard seed and celery seed for 5 minutes.
Drain and rinse pickles; slice thin lengthwise.
Add pickles to boiled mixture; place in a jar.
Put on cover; let stand for 4 days, turning jar over occasionally.
Very easy and good.

title: pineapple upside-down cake
directions: Melt sugar and butter in skillet.
Place pineapple slices on top of mixture.
Mix all ingredients together.
Beat egg whites and fold into batter.
Pour over pineapple and bake at 350° until golden brown.

title: chicken cognac
directions: Heat oven to 425°.
Dip chicken pieces in milk; drain.
Mix baking mix, salt and paprika.
Coat chicken.
Place chicken, skin side down, in greased baking pan, 9 x 9 x 2-inch.
Bake 30 minutes; turn chicken.
Bake until chicken is tender, 20 to 30 minutes.
Keep warm.

title: oven fried potatoes(low-fat)
directions: Place potatoes separately on greased cookie sheet.
Use Pam on foil, if desired.
Sprinkle red pepper and Butter Buds on each potato piece.
Bake at 350° for about 30 minutes or until brown.

title: chicken delight
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Place chicken in baking pan; put sliced pepper, onion and butter on top.
Season to taste.
Cover and bake for 40 minutes.
Add cream of mushroom soup; cover again and bake an additional 15 minutes.
Serve over rice or noodles with your choice of vegetables.

title: carrot casserole
directions: Cook carrots crisp-tender; drain, reserving 1/4 cup cooking liquid.
Place carrots in baking dish.
Combine next 3 ingredients plus cooking liquid.
Mix and pour over carrots.
Sprinkle cheese over top along with buttered bread crumbs.
Bake uncovered at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: breakfast pizza
directions: Use amounts of green peppers, onions, mushrooms and black olives to suit taste.

title: frosted pumpkin bars
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Pour in greased and floured 16 x 12-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: lemon pound cake
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Beat until smooth, cake mix, jello, oil and orange juice.
Add eggs one at a time, beating well after each addition.
Add lemon extract.
Pour into well-greased and floured Bundt pan or tube pan.
Bake 1 hour or until done.
Cool about 15 minutes and remove from pan.
In 15 to 20 minutes, pour over the confectioners sugar, dissolved in lemon juice.

title: brien's beef burgundy
directions: Trim fat from beef steak.
Cut beef into 3/4-inch pieces. Place margarine and chopped onion in 3-quart casserole.
Cover tightly and microwave on High 3 to 4 minutes or until onion is soft.
Stir in flour and beef.
Cover and microwave 6 to 8 minutes, stirring after 4 minutes until outside of beef is no longer pink. Stir in remaining ingredients except mushrooms.
Cover tightly and microwave 12 to 16 minutes, stirring every 5 minutes, until slightly thickened and boiling.
Stir in mushrooms.
Cover tightly and microwave on Medium (50%), 8 to 10 minutes, stirring after 4 minutes, until beef is tender.
Serve with hot cooked noodles, rice or French bread, if desired.

title: rice crispy chicken
directions: Combine cereal, flour and seasons in Ziploc bag. Melt butter. Dip chicken in butter and toss in cereal mixture. Place in greased 11 x 7 dish.
Sprinkle remaining cereal on top of chicken. Drizzle leftover butter on top of chicken. Bake at 400°, uncovered, 20 to 25 minutes or until chicken is done.

title: homestyle cream of tomato soup
directions: Melt margarine in large saucepan over medium heat.
Add onion; cook 1 to 2 minutes until onion is tender and crisp.
Add remaining ingredients.
Cook, uncovered, 8 to 10 minutes or until thoroughly heated, stirring frequently.
Serve immediately.

title: easy cookie dessert
directions: Sift the first 3 ingredients together; set aside.
Cream the butter and sugar, adding sugar gradually.
Blend in the egg and vanilla.
Add the dry ingredients, mixing well.
Divide batter into 4 parts.
Spread in four 8-inch round layer pans or four 9-inch pie pans, well-greased and lined with waxed paper on the bottom.
Bake at 375° for 8 to 10 minutes or until golden brown. Cool 5 minutes.
Remove from pans.

title: ranch stars
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Brown pork sausage in pan, drain and blot with paper towels to absorb excess oils.
Using a non-stick muffin tin (or non-stick spray), place two wonton wrappers criss-crossed to form a star in each compartment.
Lightly toast wonton wrappers in oven while doing next step. Wrappers should be somewhat toasty, very lightly browned.
Mix all ingredients together in large bowl to make filling.
Remove wrappers from oven, and dip filling into each star in the muffin pan.
When all stars are filled, return muffin tin to oven and cook until wrappers turn darker brown but not burned.

title: sausage and cheese balls
directions: Mix well and roll into small balls.
Bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes on a cookie sheet.
If not serving soon, refrigerate.

title: sawdust salad
directions: Mix first 5 ingredients and let congeal.
Mix vanilla instant pudding; spread on top of congealed mixture.
Mix and spread Cool Whip and cream cheese on top.
Grate cheese on top.

title: brisket roast
directions: Sprinkle both sides of roast with onion, garlic and celery salt.
Add liquid smoke and Worcestershire sauce.
Cover with foil and marinate overnight.
Cook in the same container covered in 275° oven for 3 hours.
Uncover; spread bottled barbecue sauce over.
Cool, uncovered, 1 hour.

title: carrot cake
directions: Blend eggs, sugar and cooking oil.
Add flour, salt, soda and cinnamon.
Stir in grated carrots, chopped nuts, pineapple and vanilla.
Pour into tube pan and bake at 350° for 1 hour and 15 minutes.

title: dark chocolate cake
directions: Grease and flour two (8-inch) cake pans.
Mix together the oleo, salt, eggs and sugar.
Sift together and add the flour, cocoa and baking soda.
Add sour milk, vanilla and boiling water. Pour into pans and bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until a toothpick comes out clean.

title: fruit shake
directions: Combine
all ingredients in blender.
Whir until blended. Pour into tall glass.
Makes 1 serving.

title: enchilada de pollo con chili verde(green chili chicken casserole)
directions: Boil chicken until tender, then shred.
Combine chicken soup, mushroom soup, chicken, salt, garlic salt, green chilies and onion in a medium mixing bowl.
Heat 1/2-inch of shortening in heavy pan at medium-high heat.

title: surprise ham and cheese sandwich
directions: Get bread, put butter on each slice.
Put one slice in pan (butter side down).
Put cheese and ham.
Put other slice on top. Cook on both sides until brown.
Eat.

title: mexican-style skillet supper
directions: In a large skillet, cook ground beef until light brown; drain, leaving in skillet.
Sprinkle beef with salt and pepper.
On top of ground beef, layer half each of the cheese, celery, olives and noodles.
Repeat.
Blend tomatoes, sauce mix from main dish mix and chili powder.
Stir in water.
Pour tomato mixture on noodles in skillet.
Heat to boiling.
Reduce heat, cover and simmer until noodles are tender, about 10 minutes.
Serves 6.

title: chocolate chess pie
directions: Blend first 4 ingredients by hand in medium size mixing bowl. Add eggs and vanilla; melt margarine and add slowly to other mixture.
Blend well.
Pour into pastry shell.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour.

title: tuna soup
directions: Drain tuna.
Combine all ingredients.
Cook over medium heat, stirring constantly, to get out all lumps.
Put on low and simmer for 10 to 15 minutes or until soup is bubbly hot.

title: easy orange fruit salad
directions: Mix all together and let set up in the fridge for a while.

title: hot and spicy tofu
directions: Heat oil in wok or skillet at high heat and saute tofu for 3 minutes. Reduce to medium and add garlic, curry, dill weed, turmeric, basil, thyme and cumin. Stir well. Increase heat to medium high and add soy sauce. Stir well until thoroughly heated. Transfer to serving dish and sprinkle cheese on top. Toss until cheese melts and serve.

title: old-fashioned butterscotch pie
directions: *Caution:
Use regular butter or margarine; the light margarine will not congeal well.

title: swiss steak
directions: Roll steak in flour and fry in large skillet until brown on both sides.
Then add remaining ingredients.
Reduce heat, cover and let simmer about one hour until meat is tender.
Stir often.

title: southern fried chicken
directions: Season chicken breasts with salt and pepper.
Coat each piece with flour.
Dip in buttermilk.
Coat again with flour.
In deep skillet, heat to 350°.
Reduce heat to keep 325°.
Cook chicken, a few pieces at a time, in deep hot oil for 10 minutes.
"Turn ???." Drain well on paper towel.
Keep warm until serving time.
Makes 12 servings.

title: strawberry dip
directions: Mix cream cheese, powdered sugar and lemon juice with mixer until smooth and creamy.
Add milk.
Stir in Cool Whip; mix well. Wash strawberries, but do not cap.
Arrange on a serving platter, dip berries in mixture and enjoy.

title: peanut butter pie
directions: Mix together well.
Put in graham cracker crust.
Place in freezer until ready to serve.

title: baked pineapple
directions: Add sugar to pineapple in pan and cook to boil.
Mix cornstarch and water and add to pineapple until pineapple thickens.
Take off stove and add vanilla and beat eggs; mix together.
Pour in buttered casserole dish.
Dot with butter and sprinkle with cinnamon.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: blueberry muffins
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
In mixing bowl, beat egg; stir in milk and oil.
Mix in flour and sugar; make sure you don't stir too much. Batter should be lumpy.
Fold in blueberries.
Fill muffin cups sprayed with Pam 2/3 full.
Bake 20 to 25 minutes or until golden brown.

title: lipton onion roast
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Place meat on foil.
Sprinkle with soup mix; top with mushrooms.
Seal foil.
Roast in shallow pan 1 to 2 hours or until tender.

title: oatmeal cake
directions: Pour water over oatmeal.
Cream Crisco and sugars.
Add eggs, one at a time.
Sift flour, salt, soda, cinnamon and nutmeg.
Add vanilla to oatmeal and whip.
Add to creamed mixture.
Add flour gradually.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: "faux tuna" cheese spread
directions: Soften cream cheese and mix in other ingredients. Refrigerate until firm and serve with your favorite cracker.

title: no bake cookies
directions: Boil sugar, milk, cocoa and butter for 1 minute.
Pour over peanut butter; stir until blended, then add oats and stir.
Drop by large spoonfuls on wax paper.

title: jean edlin's casserole
directions: Mix all together.
Bake at 350 degrees uncovered for 30 minutes.

title: jumbo pudding
directions: In saucepan over low heat, beat egg yolks; add sugar, milk and vanilla. Cook on low heat, stirring constantly until mixture thickens slightly. Layer wafers in bottom of casserole dish. Sprinkle coconut over wafers, then layer raisins. Repeat for second layer.

title: sweet potato pie
directions: Mix potatoes, sugar and oleo well.
Add other ingredients and mix well.
Pour into crusts.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.	Makes 2 pies.

title: chocolate dream
directions: Prepare cake mix as directed and bake in a 9 x 13-inch pan. Take out of oven and spread with caramel topping.
(Mrs. Richardson's is best.)
When cool, spread with Cool Whip. Sprinkle chopped Heath bar on top.

title: michael's gypsy stew
directions: Dice onions, fry in fat until brown. Mix ham and rice into well-beaten eggs.
Form in very small balls.
Flour each ball and cook in fat until done. Add salt, pepper and garlic (to taste) while meat and rice balls are cooking.
When almost done, pour vegetable soup over them.
Cover and heat thoroughly.
Serves 12. Fast and easy.

title: cracklin corn bread
directions: Mix all ingredients in a large bowl.
Beat 1 minute.
Grease a 12-inch skillet or a 13-inch Pyrex dish with oil.
Pour mixture in pan and bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes or until golden brown.

title: taco salad
directions: Brown ground beef and drain; add red beans (drained). Meanwhile, tear head of lettuce, mince green onions, chop tomatoes and crush corn chips.
Toss all together and use favorite dressing or taco sauce.
Makes 8 to 10 servings.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Dissolve gelatin in hot water.
Add sugar, lemon juice and pineapple syrup.
Stir to dissolve.
Chill until partially set. Add remaining ingredients.
Serves 8.

title: waldorf salad
directions: Cut cored, unpeeled apples into small pieces.
Add remaining ingredients.
Cover with Miracle Whip.
Mix thoroughly and chill.

title: mama's dumplings
directions: Mix all the ingredients into flour. Mix until you can handle; roll out on a floured board. Cut and put into boiling broth.

title: taco dip
directions: Layer in this order:

title: party punch
directions: Mix lime, pineapple, sugar and water well.
Chill.
Add ginger ale right before serving.
Add scoops of ice cream if desired.

title: popsicles
directions: Mix Kool-Aid and Jell-O with sugar and hot water to dissolve and add cold water.
Pour in popsicle molds and freeze.
The leftover mixture can be kept in a covered container in refrigerator and use as needed.
Will thicken in refrigerator.

title: marguerite cake
directions: Pour hot water over dates, add baking soda and let cool. Cream shortening and add sugar.
Beat eggs, add to shortening and cream well.
Sift flour, cocoa and salt together.
Add dry ingredients to cream mixture & add vanilla.
Lightly fold in date mix and put in greased 13x9
pan. Then sprinkle the top with the package of chocolate chips and nuts.
Bake in a 350 degree oven for 40 to 45 minutes.

title: 3 pound fruit cake
directions: Cream shortening,
sugar and eggs; mix well.
Add flour (sifted),
nutmeg and cinnamon alternately with juice, beating well after	each addition.	Dredging fruit and nuts in the 1/2 cup flour,
fold
in
fruit,
nuts
and
molasses.
Pour
into 10-inch tube
pan
that has been greased and floured.
Bake in 275° oven 2 to
hours with pan of water on bottom rack for moisture.

title: roast chicken
directions: Wash chicken and pat dry.
Place chicken, breast side down on microwave roasting rack in 12 x 8-inch dish.
Microwave 10 minutes on High.
Reduce setting.
Microwave 14 minutes on Medium. Combine honey, Worcestershire and soy sauce.
Baste chicken with glaze.
Turn breast side up.
Brush with glaze.
Microwave 22 minutes on Medium.
Let stand 15 minutes tented with aluminum foil.

title: chicken and rice casserole
directions: Combine all ingredients and bake in uncovered casserole at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.
Remove bay leaf.

title: pineapple boat salad
directions: Cut pineapple in half lengthwise, leaving leaves intact. Using a grapefruit knife, cut around edge of pineapple and down through the center of core without cutting through shell.
Scoop out pineapple.
Cut into cubes.
Reserve shell.
In a bowl, combine pineapple, chicken, ham, bananas, avocado, celery, walnuts and cherries.
Cover and chill about 1 hour.
When ready to serve, arrange fruit mixture in pineapple shells.
Serves 4.

title: no bake cookies
directions: Mix sugar, cocoa, margarine and milk and boil for 1 minute. Add salt, vanilla and peanut butter.
Cook until peanut butter is melted, then add oatmeal.
Mix thoroughly.
Drop by tablespoon on wax paper.

title: chocolate pie(2 pies)
directions: Beat 4 egg yolks and 1 whole egg; add sugar, cocoa, milk and vanilla.
Pour into unbaked pie shell.
Bake at 325° until knife inserted comes out clean, about 35 minutes.

title: zucchini casserole
directions: Grate zucchini into colander; let drain.
Saute onions in a little butter.
Add zucchini and cook 5 minutes.
Add 2 teaspoons of butter and sprinkle flour on top.
Cook 1 minute.
Add half and half, salt and pepper; remove from heat.
Add cheeses and mix well.
Pour into casserole dish and sprinkle with remaining butter and bread crumbs.
Bake 45 minutes at 375°.
Serve with steak and potatoes.

title: graham cracker stack cake
directions: Layer graham crackers in pan.
Spread apple butter over these. Continue to stack in layers.
Let set for a while.
Eat and enjoy.

title: orange cake
directions: Put all ingredients in a large mixing bowl and beat for 3 minutes.
Pour into a 9 x 13-inch greased and floured pan.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: italian love cake
directions: Prepare cake mix as directed on package. Pour into greased and floured 9 x 13-inch pan. Set aside.

title: fruited pork salad
directions: In jar with tight fitting lid, shake together the first 6 ingredients.
Set aside.
Spray large nonstick skillet with vegetable cooking spray; heat to medium hot.
Lettuce on individual plates.
Top with fruit and pork.
Spoon dressing over salads. Serves 4.

title: sweet and sour pork chops
directions: Season chops with salt and pepper; brown in hot oil.
Drain well.
Place chops in a shallow dish; top with lemon slices. Combine ketchup, water and sugar.
Blend well.
Pour sauce over chops.
Top with thick slices of Vidalia onion.
Cover with foil and bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Serves 4.

title: grated sweet potato dish
directions: Grate raw sweet potatoes.
Mix with sugar and milk.
Put in baking dish.
Sprinkle with cinnamon.
Dot with butter.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Take out of oven and top with marshmallows. Brown in oven 5 minutes.

title: gingerbread men
directions: In large bowl, beat sugar and butter until well blended.
Add molasses and eggs.
Stir in remaining ingredients.
Cover and chill 1 hour.
Roll dough on well floured board until 1/8-inch thick.
Cut into shapes.
Place on greased baking sheet.
Bake 10 minutes at 350°.
Decorate as desired.

title: cool whip and fruit pie
directions: Mix all ingredients well and let stand for 1 hour in refrigerator before serving.

title: sour cream cookies
directions: Beat eggs.
Add sugar, shortening and sour cream.
Add vanilla.
Add dry ingredients.
Bake at 375° for 10 minutes.
Drop from tablespoon on greased cookie sheet.
May add 1/2 cup raisins or dates.

title: raisin bran muffins
directions: Cream the sugar, oil and eggs.
Add buttermilk and dry ingredients.
Mix well.
Stir in cereal last.
Bake at 400° for 15 minutes in greased muffin pans.
Makes 6 dozen.

title: pineapple cake
directions: Sift flour, sugar and soda.
Add eggs and pineapple with juice.
Pour into a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: pea and cheese salad
directions: Mix well; salt to taste.
Let stand a couple of hours.

title: chocolate ice cream
directions: Mix well and freeze.

title: honey baked chicken breasts
directions: Place chicken in a shallow baking pan.
Combine the rest of the ingredients and pour over the chicken.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour and 15 minutes, basting every 15 minutes or so, until chicken is tender and nicely browned.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Stew chicken and bone. Melt butter or margarine. Put all of the dressing, except 1/4 cup, in bottom of baking dish.
Pour melted margarine over dressing. Place chicken over dressing.

title: taffy apple salad
directions: Mix flour, sugar, pineapple and juice, egg and apple cider vinegar in small pan. Stir over medium heat until thick. Refrigerate until cool. Fold into Cool Whip with chopped apples and 1/2 cup peanuts. Sprinkle remaining peanuts on top.

title: layer salad
directions: In large Tupperware bowl with lid, layer in this order: lettuce, cauliflower, onion and bacon.
In small bowl, mix Miracle Whip, Parmesan cheese and sugar until well blended.
Pour over salad mixture and spread well.
(Do not toss.) Refrigerate 6 to 12 hours.
Toss well before serving.

title: hot turkey or chicken salad
directions: Mix together and put in buttered casserole dish.
Top with crushed cornflakes.
Bake 45 minutes at 325°.

title: taco salad
directions: In an oblong glass dish, layer 1/2 bag tortilla chips (crushed); next sprinkle 1/2 of shredded Cheddar cheese, then pour heated chili on cheese.
Repeat with other half of tortilla chips and end with layer of cheese.
Place in microwave or oven and heat until cheese melts.
Layer onion, tomato and lettuce on top. Serve while warm.
Also serve sour cream on side if desired.

title: chocolate mayonnaise cake
directions: Combine all ingredients; beat at "frosting-speed" for 10 minutes.
Flavor if desired.

title: no bake cherry cheese cake
directions: Combine cracker crumbs, sugar and butter. Press into a 9 x 13 pan.

title: creamed vegetables
directions: Combine all ingredients in a dish (except crackers).
Mix well. Top with cracker crumbs and pat with butter.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: tostado dip
directions: Layer in any order.
Beans can be heated.
Suggested order: beans, chilies, Cheddar cheese, tomatoes, beans, chilies, tomatoes, olives, sour cream and Cheddar cheese.

title: fresh strawberry pie
directions: Arrange
berries
in pie crust.
Mix cornstarch, sugar, water and
jello.
Cook over low heat until thick.
Pour over berries and chill in refrigerator 1 hour.

title: triple sensation cheesecake(for the not so health conscious.)
directions: You will need an 8 or 9-inch round, 3-inch deep, one piece pan, buttered lightly, completely and 1 pan large enough to hold round pan but no deeper than 3-inches.

title: beef tips(crock-pot recipe)
directions: Mix ingredients.
Cook in crock-pot on low for 4 to 6 hours or in oven, covered, at 350° for 2 to 3 hours.
Stir occasionally.

title: strawberry cream cheese ice cream
directions: Combine eggs, sugar
and
1 1/2 cups half and half in a small saucepan.
Cook
and stir over medium heat until mixture just comes
to
boil.
Remove
from heat.
Transfer to a large bowl. Stir
in
remaining
half
and
half,
vanilla and food coloring. Cover and chill.
Mix cream cheese in a large mixer bowl until fluffy.
Gradually beat in the 2 cups berries until berries are coarsely
crushed.	Gradually
beat in the cooled egg mixture. Stir
in the 1 cup chopped berries.
Freeze in a 4 to
quart ice
cream freezer according to manufacturer's directions.	Makes 2 quarts.

title: hummingbird cake
directions: Blend first 5 ingredients well in large bowl, then add all other ingredients.
Stir only by hand until well mixed.
Pour into a greased tube or Bundt pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour and 5 minutes.
Cool 1 hour before removing from pan.

title: light spinach-bacon deviled eggs
directions: Cut eggs in half lengthwise.
Scoop out yolks into a small mixing bowl and mash with a fork.
Add remaining ingredients and mix well.
Spoon yolk mixture into egg white halves.
Chill until ready to serve.

title: strange cake
directions: Mix cake mix, egg, margarine and vanilla in 1 bowl.
Place in a 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Pat down.
In another bowl, mix cream cheese, eggs, powdered sugar, vanilla and chopped pecans.
Pour over cake mix.
Bake 45 minutes at 350°.

title: mound bars
directions: Melt butter and mix into cracker crumbs and sugar.
Press into a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake in 400° oven for 7 to 10 minutes.
Mix remaining ingredients together except Hershey bars and spread over baked crust.
Bake 10 minutes.
Place Hershey bars on top while bars are hot, then spread chocolate when melted.

title: suet pudding
directions: Mix all ingredients and pour in greased coffee can.
Steam 2 1/2 hours.
Makes 8 to 10 slices.
Serve hot with the Sauce.

title: peach pie supreme
directions: Mix sugar and flour in bowl.
Add vanilla, salt and cream; stir completely.
Slice peaches into pie crust.
Pour mixture over peaches.
Bake 50 to 60 minutes at 400°.

title: fried apples
directions: Wash apples, cut in quarters and remove cores.
Melt margarine in large frying pan.
Add apples, sugar and water.
Cover and steam a few minutes until apples are tender.
Remove lid and cook over low heat until syrup thickens.

title: chicken and noodle casserole
directions: Boil and debone chickens.
Cook noodles in cans of chicken broth.
Add cream of chicken soup to noodles and broth.
Mix well and add chicken.

title: mango salsa
directions: Combine all ingredients and refrigerate over night.
Serve with scoop Fritos.

title: joe's steak casserole
directions: Layer all ingredients starting with meat.
Layer soups with water; next, stewed tomatoes, green beans, mushrooms and last onion rings.
Cook, covered, at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: chocolate chip bars
directions: Preheat oven at 375°.
Combine 1/2 of cake mix and all ingredients except chocolate chips and nuts.
Mix thoroughly. Blend in remaining cake mix.
Stir in chips and nuts.
Spread in a greased and floured pan, 15 1/2 x 10 1/2 x 1-inch.
Bake 20 to 25 minutes.
Cool and cut into bars.

title: baked macaroni and cheese
directions: In top of double boiler, melt oleo.
Add flour and stir until smooth.
Add milk; stir constantly until slightly thickened.
Add Velveeta and Cheddar cheese.
Stir until melted.

title: homemade ice cream
directions: Using electric ice cream machine, blend Eagle Brand milk, eggs, sugar and vanilla; mix well.
Add milk to the line on the container, then follow directions on machine.

title: marinated vegie salad
directions: Pour liquids over vegetables and let stand overnight in refrigerator.

title: nuts and bolts
directions: Melt and mix the following:
oleo, bacon drippings, Tabasco, Worcestershire and garlic salt.
Bake at 250° for 1 hour, stirring every 15 minutes.
Salt to taste.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Measure all ingredients into a large bowl except flour, zucchini and nuts.
Beat until smooth; stir flour into mixture. Add zucchini and nuts.
Divide dough into 6 (5 1/2 x 3 x 2 1/4-inch) loaf pans.
Bake 60 to 65 minutes at 350°.
Cool on a wire rack.

title: breakfast for many
directions: You can also use ham and cooked bacon.

title: meat loaf
directions: Mix above ingredients and bake in a loaf pan at 350 degrees for one hour.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: jalapeno artichoke dip
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Bake in 350° oven for 25 to 30 minutes in 8 x 8-inch baking dish.
Serve with sliced French baguettes or crackers.

title: hawaiian cheese ball
directions: Mix all ingredients, add a dash of savory salt.
Chill, roll in chopped pecans.
Chill and serve.

title: fruit pizza
directions: Cut cookie dough in 1/8-inch slices.
Arrange in 14-inch pizza pan.
Press to seal.
Bake as per package instruction.
Cool.

title: deer and pepperoni pizza
directions: Mix crust mix and 1/2 cup hot tap water in mixing bowl; stir with a fork until blended (about 40 strokes).
Form a ball; grease ball with 1 teaspoon of oil.
Set in warm place for 5 minutes.

title: strawberry bread
directions: Combine eggs, oil and berries.
In a separate bowl, mix dry ingredients together well.
Then, add berry mixture.
Bake in a greased, floured pan at 350° for 1 hour.

title: m.s.u.  workout
directions: Pour rum into tall glass prepared with ice cubes.
Squeeze lime juice from 1 lime wedge.
Drop in wedge and fill with diet cola.

title: copper pennies
directions: Cook carrots; cool.
Chop onion and pepper; add to carrots (do not cook).
Heat soup, sugar, vinegar, mustard, Worcestershire sauce and oil.
Refrigerate.

title: beer batter for seafood
directions: Place flour and egg into mixing bowl and mix enough to break up egg.
Slowly add beer, mixing vigorously until all lumps are dissolved.
Add in Old Bay seasoning and refrigerate for 30 minutes to allow gas from beer to escape.
If batter seems too thick, water may be added slowly for proper consistency.
